WEBVTT

1
00:00:58.526 --> 00:01:01.029
<i>Within the next five days.</i>

2
00:01:01.061 --> 00:01:02.764
<i>Muzan will come.</i>

3
00:01:09.269 --> 00:01:12.205
I will be the bait you use.

4
00:01:12.239 --> 00:01:15.677
When he comes.
I need you to behead him.

5
00:01:19.146 --> 00:01:23.417
- Master. what leads you
to believe he'll find you?

6
00:01:26.086 --> 00:01:28.690
My intuition. That's all.

7
00:01:29.691 --> 00:01:31.425
Nothing beyond that.

8
00:01:31.458 --> 00:01:35.228
But listen.
the others can't know.

9
00:01:35.262 --> 00:01:40.233
They would never agree
to using me as bait like this.

10
00:01:40.267 --> 00:01:43.203
They would sooner die
than do it.

11
00:01:43.236 --> 00:01:47.508
You're the only one
that I can ask. Gyomei.

12
00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:53.380
Even if you behead him.
he won't die.

13
00:01:54.716 --> 00:01:58.753
There's likely only one way
to destroy Muzan.

14
00:01:58.786 --> 00:02:03.256
trapping him in place until
sunlight shines upon him.

15
00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:06.060
If beheading
isn't enough to kill him.

16
00:02:06.094 --> 00:02:08.696
there's only one option left.

17
00:02:08.730 --> 00:02:13.200
You all must endure a battle
until the sun rises.

18
00:02:14.134 --> 00:02:15.803
- Yes. sir.

19
00:02:17.105 --> 00:02:19.807
<i>If that is your wish.</i>
<i>then so be it. Master.</i>

20
00:02:23.343 --> 00:02:25.278
<i>- Thank goodness.</i>

21
00:02:30.952 --> 00:02:32.285
<i>Gyomei...</i>

22
00:02:32.319 --> 00:02:34.656
<i>after I have perished.</i>

23
00:02:34.689 --> 00:02:37.391
<i>please do not let</i>
<i>any more of my children</i>

24
00:02:37.424 --> 00:02:39.927
<i>be sent to their graves.</i>

25
00:02:39.961 --> 00:02:42.030
<i>That is my wish.</i>

26
00:02:59.379 --> 00:03:01.683
<i>You think you've</i>
<i>driven me into a corner</i>

27
00:03:01.716 --> 00:03:03.183
<i>with your little plan?</i>

28
00:03:04.852 --> 00:03:08.388
But you are all about to be
going straight to hell!

29
00:03:08.422 --> 00:03:10.490
Mark my words. Demon Slayers.

30
00:03:10.525 --> 00:03:14.227
I'll massacre every one of you
before sunrise!

31
00:03:18.298 --> 00:03:21.002
You're the only one
going to hell.

32
00:03:21.035 --> 00:03:23.270
and you won't get away!

33
00:03:23.303 --> 00:03:26.074
- Oh. is that so?

34
00:03:26.107 --> 00:03:28.643
Let's see you try.

35
00:03:28.676 --> 00:03:30.878
Tanjiro Kamado!

36
00:03:32.947 --> 00:03:35.282
- I will defeat you!

37
00:03:36.751 --> 00:03:39.053
<i>Muzan Kibutsuji!</i>

38
00:03:50.998 --> 00:03:53.201
<i>What is this place?</i>

39
00:03:53.233 --> 00:03:56.137
<i>Everything's upside down.</i>

40
00:03:56.170 --> 00:03:59.874
<i>Was all of this made using</i>
<i>the enemy's Blood Demon Art?</i>

41
00:04:02.810 --> 00:04:04.946
<i>I don't understand</i>
<i>what's happening.</i>

42
00:04:04.979 --> 00:04:08.281
<i>except that Ms. Tamayo</i>
<i>was restraining Muzan.</i>

43
00:04:09.083 --> 00:04:10.250
<i>Even so...</i>

44
00:04:10.283 --> 00:04:12.720
<i>how long can she</i>
<i>keep that up?</i>

45
00:04:15.223 --> 00:04:17.091
- Calm down. Kanroji!

46
00:04:17.125 --> 00:04:19.160
- I-- Yes!

47
00:04:19.193 --> 00:04:20.661
- Stay with me!

48
00:05:15.583 --> 00:05:18.085
<i>I need to reach</i>
<i>Muzan as soon as possible</i>

49
00:05:18.119 --> 00:05:19.020
<i>and defeat him!</i>

50
00:05:19.053 --> 00:05:21.321
<i>By whatever means!</i>

51
00:05:29.831 --> 00:05:30.598
<i>That's the bottom!</i>

52
00:05:30.631 --> 00:05:33.201
<i>I'll be killed at this speed!</i>

53
00:05:33.234 --> 00:05:35.435
<i>I'll use a move</i>
<i>to change directions.</i>

54
00:05:35.468 --> 00:05:37.672
<i>then find something</i>
<i>to grab on to.</i>

55
00:05:40.440 --> 00:05:42.643
<i>It didn't work.</i>

56
00:05:42.677 --> 00:05:45.112
<i>I can't break away</i>
<i>from this freefall.</i>

57
00:06:34.328 --> 00:06:35.897
You all right?

58
00:06:37.298 --> 00:06:38.431
- Yes!

59
00:06:38.465 --> 00:06:40.268
Thanks for your help.

60
00:06:41.969 --> 00:06:43.304
You really saved--

61
00:06:45.006 --> 00:06:50.044
Water Breathing First Form:
Water Surface Slash.

62
00:06:51.846 --> 00:06:52.947
- Tanjiro!

63
00:07:14.869 --> 00:07:16.971
<i>- Water Breathing...</i>
<i>- Water Breathing...</i>

64
00:07:17.004 --> 00:07:18.339
<i>- Sixth Form...</i>

65
00:07:18.372 --> 00:07:19.707
<i>- Third Form...</i>

66
00:07:20.975 --> 00:07:23.244
<i>Whirlpool.</i>

67
00:07:23.277 --> 00:07:24.712
<i>- Flowing Dance.</i>

68
00:07:32.053 --> 00:07:34.789
<i>Mr. Giyu's amazing.</i>

69
00:07:34.822 --> 00:07:38.326
<i>He can tell exactly</i>
<i>which move I'm gonna use.</i>

70
00:07:38.359 --> 00:07:39.694
<i>Then he follows up with one</i>

71
00:07:39.727 --> 00:07:42.897
<i>that prevents any kind</i>
<i>of friendly fire.</i>

72
00:07:42.930 --> 00:07:44.966
<i>He's unbelievable.</i>

73
00:07:44.999 --> 00:07:47.835
<i>Just what's</i>
<i>behind those eyes?!</i>

74
00:07:50.338 --> 00:07:53.507
- If I'm not mistaken.
this is the place

75
00:07:53.541 --> 00:07:56.043
that Shinazugawa
and Iguro mentioned.

76
00:07:59.246 --> 00:08:03.718
Which means Kibutsuji's plan
was to gather everyone here.

77
00:08:03.751 --> 00:08:07.154
then kill us all
in one fell swoop.

78
00:08:07.188 --> 00:08:12.460
From here on out. we'll need
to be even more vigilant.

79
00:08:12.492 --> 00:08:13.894
- Right.

80
00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:16.697
- Let's go.

81
00:08:16.731 --> 00:08:17.631
- Right!

82
00:08:40.054 --> 00:08:43.090
- Serpent Breathing
Fifth Form...

83
00:08:50.097 --> 00:08:52.666
- Slithering Serpent!

84
00:08:54.635 --> 00:08:56.337
You demon scum...

85
00:08:56.370 --> 00:08:58.507
stay away from Kanroji!

86
00:09:00.274 --> 00:09:02.810
<i>Mr. Iguro is so cool!</i>

87
00:09:03.677 --> 00:09:04.645
- Are you hurt?

88
00:09:04.678 --> 00:09:05.880
- No. not at all!

89
00:09:05.913 --> 00:09:06.814
- Then let's go.

90
00:09:06.847 --> 00:09:07.548
- Okay!

91
00:09:28.436 --> 00:09:29.370
Tokito!

92
00:09:36.010 --> 00:09:38.913
There's a whole lot
of demons. huh?

93
00:09:38.946 --> 00:09:40.515
- It would seem
they've been given

94
00:09:40.549 --> 00:09:42.249
the strength
of the Lower Ranks.

95
00:09:42.283 --> 00:09:46.087
It's clear that they're being
used to try and exhaust us.

96
00:09:49.558 --> 00:09:50.691
- Hmm.

97
00:09:51.492 --> 00:09:52.993
What of the Master?

98
00:09:53.828 --> 00:09:56.597
- He has departed
from this world.

99
00:09:57.431 --> 00:10:00.034
It was a truly noble end.

100
00:10:01.001 --> 00:10:02.203
- Knowing him...

101
00:10:02.236 --> 00:10:05.940
he never would have allowed
himself to be caught unawares.

102
00:10:06.740 --> 00:10:09.578
Did he sacrifice himself?

103
00:10:09.610 --> 00:10:10.978
- Indeed.

104
00:10:11.011 --> 00:10:13.647
The Master did not
have much time left.

105
00:10:20.589 --> 00:10:21.989
<i>Master...</i>

106
00:10:28.729 --> 00:10:31.600
Back when I was mortally
wounded by a demon.

107
00:10:31.632 --> 00:10:33.502
and found myself
teetering on the edge

108
00:10:33.535 --> 00:10:35.269
between life and death...

109
00:10:36.303 --> 00:10:38.038
he stayed by my side.

110
00:10:40.708 --> 00:10:43.444
He did the same
for every Corps member

111
00:10:43.477 --> 00:10:45.379
who was
on the brink of death...

112
00:10:47.681 --> 00:10:49.183
like a father.

113
00:10:51.385 --> 00:10:53.687
- Yes. I know.

114
00:10:53.721 --> 00:10:57.291
- Muzan not only took
my brother from me.

115
00:10:57.324 --> 00:10:59.293
but our father as well.

116
00:10:59.326 --> 00:11:01.462
That bastard.

117
00:11:01.495 --> 00:11:02.696
Damn him!

118
00:11:02.730 --> 00:11:05.534
I swear I'll make him suffer!

119
00:11:05.567 --> 00:11:07.735
I'll send him
straight to hell!

120
00:11:08.537 --> 00:11:10.237
- You're not alone.

121
00:11:14.475 --> 00:11:17.678
Trust me.
We all feel the same.

122
00:11:24.752 --> 00:11:27.354
<i>Forgive me. Master.</i>

123
00:11:28.623 --> 00:11:30.824
<i>I couldn't protect you.</i>

124
00:11:46.040 --> 00:11:49.310
- There's no end
to you lowlifes. huh.

125
00:11:52.313 --> 00:11:54.616
That's just fine by me.

126
00:11:54.649 --> 00:11:56.551
I'll kill all of you!

127
00:12:04.626 --> 00:12:06.160
- Yaah!

128
00:12:06.193 --> 00:12:07.529
Make way!

129
00:12:07.562 --> 00:12:09.196
I'm comin' through!

130
00:12:11.799 --> 00:12:14.835
Whole lotta fallin'
happening here!

131
00:12:16.170 --> 00:12:19.306
Pretty rude to just drop me
in here outta nowhere!

132
00:12:19.340 --> 00:12:20.609
Though. I've been itching

133
00:12:20.642 --> 00:12:22.409
to see how
my training's paid off.

134
00:12:22.443 --> 00:12:23.877
so with that in mind.

135
00:12:23.911 --> 00:12:26.347
let's test it out
on you chumps!

136
00:12:28.048 --> 00:12:29.216
Let's go!

137
00:12:36.423 --> 00:12:38.092
<i>Where am I?</i>

138
00:12:38.125 --> 00:12:40.961
<i>The demon headquarters?</i>
<i>Where are the others?</i>

139
00:12:41.762 --> 00:12:43.665
<i>Big Brother.</i>

140
00:12:43.698 --> 00:12:47.067
<i>I hope you're safe. too.</i>

141
00:12:50.904 --> 00:12:53.140
<i>- I just heard a sound.</i>

142
00:12:53.173 --> 00:12:55.677
<i>Could it be</i>
<i>that</i> he's <i>somewhere nearby?</i>

143
00:13:01.315 --> 00:13:02.950
- You'll regret this.

144
00:13:04.051 --> 00:13:08.355
I won't forgive you.
not in a million years.

145
00:13:32.681 --> 00:13:34.281
<i>- I smell blood.</i>

146
00:13:43.057 --> 00:13:45.192
What is this place?

147
00:14:02.109 --> 00:14:03.110
Hmm?

148
00:14:04.445 --> 00:14:06.246
Oh. my. You're here?

149
00:14:07.147 --> 00:14:09.517
Ohh! And you're a girl. too!

150
00:14:09.551 --> 00:14:13.921
What a young and
tasty morsel we have! Heh!

151
00:14:13.954 --> 00:14:18.192
I'll have to properly
thank Nakime for this later.

152
00:14:33.974 --> 00:14:35.376
- Shinobu...

153
00:14:35.409 --> 00:14:38.580
you must leave
the Demon Slayer Corps.

154
00:14:40.314 --> 00:14:44.051
I know that you've
trained really hard...

155
00:14:44.084 --> 00:14:46.420
and you're fighting
to make a difference.

156
00:14:47.555 --> 00:14:49.957
But I don't think you'll...

157
00:14:55.396 --> 00:14:59.967
I want you to live the life
of a happy. normal girl.

158
00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:03.170
to be able to see
your own hair turn gray.

159
00:15:05.507 --> 00:15:08.409
Really. you've done enough.

160
00:15:08.442 --> 00:15:10.512
- No! Can't stop now!

161
00:15:10.545 --> 00:15:13.848
I will avenge you
if it's the last thing I do!

162
00:15:13.882 --> 00:15:16.283
This demon. I need to know.

163
00:15:16.316 --> 00:15:18.853
I have to know
what it looked like!

164
00:15:18.887 --> 00:15:20.187
Please. Big Sister.

165
00:15:20.220 --> 00:15:23.157
I'm begging you. tell me!

166
00:15:23.190 --> 00:15:25.058
I could never live
a normal life

167
00:15:25.092 --> 00:15:27.461
knowing someone
did this to you!

168
00:15:27.494 --> 00:15:29.296
Please!

169
00:15:33.835 --> 00:15:35.169
<i>It was a demon...</i>

170
00:15:35.202 --> 00:15:38.238
<i>with a bloodstained pattern</i>
<i>on his head.</i>

171
00:15:39.406 --> 00:15:42.877
- I must say. it's very nice
to meet you. miss!

172
00:15:42.911 --> 00:15:45.979
You may refer to me as Doma.

173
00:15:46.013 --> 00:15:49.983
Ah. what a wonderful night.

174
00:15:51.018 --> 00:15:54.288
<i>- Such a warm smile</i>
<i>and gentle voice.</i>

175
00:15:54.321 --> 00:15:57.991
<i>There's a soft.</i>
<i>benevolent presence to him.</i>

176
00:15:59.092 --> 00:16:00.260
Please...

177
00:16:00.294 --> 00:16:01.596
h-help me.

178
00:16:02.630 --> 00:16:03.698
Please help me!

179
00:16:03.731 --> 00:16:05.466
- Shh!

180
00:16:05.499 --> 00:16:07.769
Can't you see
that we're talking?

181
00:16:11.506 --> 00:16:12.640
Huh?

182
00:16:12.674 --> 00:16:14.709
- Are you all right?

183
00:16:14.742 --> 00:16:17.612
- Wow! That was fast.

184
00:16:17.645 --> 00:16:19.279
Are you a Hashira?

185
00:16:27.889 --> 00:16:29.490
- Oh. don't worry about that!

186
00:16:29.524 --> 00:16:31.926
You can just
leave her right there.

187
00:16:31.960 --> 00:16:34.161
I'll make a proper meal
of her later.

188
00:16:37.498 --> 00:16:38.766
- And this demon...

189
00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:41.769
the weapon he used...

190
00:16:41.803 --> 00:16:43.705
it was a pair of sharp fans.

191
00:16:46.574 --> 00:16:50.143
- As the founder of
the Eternal Paradise Faith.

192
00:16:50.177 --> 00:16:51.478
it is my sworn duty

193
00:16:51.513 --> 00:16:55.182
to see that all my followers
attain happiness.

194
00:16:55.215 --> 00:16:58.051
I'll be sure
to consume her completely.

195
00:16:59.821 --> 00:17:01.121
<i>- There's no doubt.</i>

196
00:17:01.154 --> 00:17:04.358
<i>This is the demon</i>
<i>who killed my sister.</i>

197
00:17:05.192 --> 00:17:07.094
Attaining happiness?

198
00:17:07.127 --> 00:17:08.997
For who. exactly?

199
00:17:09.029 --> 00:17:12.734
This girl was horrified.
crying out for help.

200
00:17:12.767 --> 00:17:14.368
- And that's why I saved her.

201
00:17:15.235 --> 00:17:18.138
Her suffering
has come to an end.

202
00:17:18.171 --> 00:17:21.609
No more pain. No more fear.

203
00:17:22.644 --> 00:17:25.212
Everyone is afraid of death.

204
00:17:25.245 --> 00:17:28.315
so I help them
by consuming them.

205
00:17:28.348 --> 00:17:33.021
This way. they get to live on
within me for all eternity.

206
00:17:33.086 --> 00:17:35.657
I take in their entire being--

207
00:17:35.690 --> 00:17:40.394
blood. desires. even
the last bit of their sinew--

208
00:17:40.427 --> 00:17:43.531
and help
their souls transcend.

209
00:17:43.565 --> 00:17:46.734
- What you're spouting
is sheer nonsense.

210
00:17:46.768 --> 00:17:49.136
And to say it with such glee.

211
00:17:49.169 --> 00:17:51.338
You truly make me sick.

212
00:17:51.371 --> 00:17:52.941
- Huh?

213
00:17:52.974 --> 00:17:57.645
I can't believe you'd say that
after we'd only just met.

214
00:17:57.679 --> 00:17:59.146
Oh. I see!

215
00:17:59.179 --> 00:18:01.181
Aw. you poor thing.

216
00:18:01.214 --> 00:18:04.151
Did something
unfortunate happen?

217
00:18:04.184 --> 00:18:05.720
Let's hear it.

218
00:18:05.753 --> 00:18:07.354
Go on. tell me.

219
00:18:08.422 --> 00:18:11.726
"Unfortunate" doesn't begin
to describe it!

220
00:18:11.759 --> 00:18:15.162
You were the one who killed
my Big Sister. weren't you?!

221
00:18:15.195 --> 00:18:17.999
Does the haori I'm wearing
mean nothing to you?!

222
00:18:18.032 --> 00:18:19.801
- Huh?

223
00:18:30.945 --> 00:18:32.547
- That's right.

224
00:18:32.580 --> 00:18:35.917
It belonged to the girl
who used Flower Breathing.

225
00:18:35.950 --> 00:18:38.753
Such a sweet. gentle child.

226
00:18:39.921 --> 00:18:42.590
The sun came up
and cut our time short.

227
00:18:42.624 --> 00:18:43.791
I remember.

228
00:18:43.825 --> 00:18:45.459
It's a shame I didn't get

229
00:18:45.492 --> 00:18:46.527
to eat-- her.

230
00:18:48.228 --> 00:18:51.131
<i>Insect Breathing</i>
<i>Dance of the Bee Sting...</i>

231
00:18:51.164 --> 00:18:52.533
<i>True Flutter!</i>

232
00:18:53.735 --> 00:18:55.335
- A marvelous thrust!

233
00:18:55.369 --> 00:18:57.505
I hardly even saw it!

234
00:18:59.741 --> 00:19:01.308
Blood Demon Art...

235
00:19:02.209 --> 00:19:04.478
Frozen Lotus.

236
00:19:05.513 --> 00:19:06.948
<i>- So cold.</i>

237
00:19:06.981 --> 00:19:09.416
<i>It feels like</i>
<i>my lungs are bursting!</i>

238
00:19:10.250 --> 00:19:12.587
- Hmm. Look at that!

239
00:19:12.620 --> 00:19:13.688
You are fast!

240
00:19:13.721 --> 00:19:16.256
Unfortunately for you.

241
00:19:16.289 --> 00:19:19.326
those thrusts aren't enough
to kill a demon.

242
00:19:22.797 --> 00:19:24.799
Aim for here.

243
00:19:24.832 --> 00:19:27.167
You need to chop off my head.

244
00:19:29.469 --> 00:19:32.707
- My thrusts alone
may not be enough.

245
00:19:32.740 --> 00:19:34.241
But what of this?

246
00:19:38.478 --> 00:19:42.583
<i>- Time to see whether this</i>
<i>toxin works on an Upper Rank.</i>

247
00:19:44.152 --> 00:19:45.352
<i>Sister...</i>

248
00:19:45.385 --> 00:19:48.756
<i>lend me your strength.</i>
<i>please.</i>

249
00:19:50.925 --> 00:19:52.727
This poison...

250
00:19:52.760 --> 00:19:55.830
it's clearly far stronger
than the strain you used

251
00:19:55.863 --> 00:19:57.598
up on Rui's mountain.

252
00:19:58.733 --> 00:20:02.036
<i>- So they did</i>
<i>exchange information.</i>

253
00:20:02.070 --> 00:20:04.271
<i>This is the drawback</i>
<i>to using poison.</i>

254
00:20:04.304 --> 00:20:06.040
- He told me that...

255
00:20:06.074 --> 00:20:08.408
you've been
changing the concoction...

256
00:20:08.442 --> 00:20:10.912
for each demon you face.

257
00:20:19.252 --> 00:20:20.755
Oh. my.

258
00:20:20.788 --> 00:20:21.823
it would seem that I've

259
00:20:21.856 --> 00:20:25.159
already neutralized
all of your poison.

260
00:20:25.193 --> 00:20:26.527
How rude of me.

261
00:20:26.561 --> 00:20:29.931
And after you'd made it
just for me.

262
00:20:29.964 --> 00:20:32.332
That sword of yours...

263
00:20:32.365 --> 00:20:36.137
it makes quite an interesting
sound when you sheath it.

264
00:20:36.170 --> 00:20:40.240
Is that where you change
what poison you use?

265
00:20:40.273 --> 00:20:42.844
Yay! This is fun!

266
00:20:42.877 --> 00:20:46.714
Who knew being poisoned
was so invigorating?!

267
00:20:46.748 --> 00:20:48.549
It's almost addictive.

268
00:20:48.583 --> 00:20:50.450
What'll the next formula
be like?

269
00:20:50.484 --> 00:20:53.554
Come on.
let's give it a try!

270
00:20:59.761 --> 00:21:01.729
- Very well. then.

271
00:21:01.763 --> 00:21:03.197
I'll oblige.

272
00:21:03.231 --> 00:21:04.431
See...

273
00:21:07.802 --> 00:21:11.304
I'd already anticipated
this would happen.

274
00:21:12.774 --> 00:21:14.909
Is your next batch set?

275
00:21:14.942 --> 00:21:16.778
I'm ready whenever you are.

276
00:21:21.115 --> 00:21:23.985
I know I just said
to give it a try...

277
00:21:25.418 --> 00:21:28.623
but you could at least
change up your offense.

278
00:21:43.370 --> 00:21:44.705
- What's this?

279
00:21:44.739 --> 00:21:47.542
You seem to be
slower than earlier.

280
00:21:47.575 --> 00:21:48.843
So sad.

281
00:21:48.876 --> 00:21:52.013
<i>- Insect Breathing</i>
<i>Dance of the Horsefly...</i>

282
00:21:52.046 --> 00:21:54.549
<i>Enticing Slash!</i>

283
00:22:01.722 --> 00:22:04.959
- Oh. my.
You were able to land a hit.

284
00:22:04.992 --> 00:22:09.329
The way you got through
all my defenses. it's amazing!

285
00:22:09.362 --> 00:22:10.965
I'm truly impressed!

286
00:22:10.998 --> 00:22:14.168
It's almost enough
to bring a tear to my eye.

287
00:22:14.202 --> 00:22:16.504
Come on.
What are you waiting for?

288
00:22:16.537 --> 00:22:20.373
Hurry up and attack me again
before I stop the poison.

289
00:22:20.407 --> 00:22:22.610
Please? You're doing so well!

290
00:22:22.643 --> 00:22:24.979
Maybe the next attack
kills me!

291
00:22:30.918 --> 00:22:33.054
Yes! That's the spirit!

292
00:22:36.624 --> 00:22:40.895
<i>Ever since I was a child.</i>
<i>I was kind and clever.</i>

293
00:22:40.928 --> 00:22:43.731
<i>I always helped</i>
<i>those who were in need</i>

294
00:22:43.764 --> 00:22:47.034
<i>and led them</i>
<i>to the path of happiness.</i>

295
00:22:47.068 --> 00:22:49.369
<i>It was my duty. after all.</i>

296
00:22:50.738 --> 00:22:53.975
His eyes have
the colors of a rainbow.

297
00:22:54.008 --> 00:22:58.246
And this gray hair
is proof of his innocence.

298
00:22:58.279 --> 00:23:00.915
This child is truly special.

299
00:23:00.948 --> 00:23:04.384
- Surely he can hear
the voices of the gods.

300
00:23:05.720 --> 00:23:10.124
<i>- My parents were</i>
<i>hopelessly naive simpletons.</i>

301
00:23:10.157 --> 00:23:13.261
<i>You'd have to be.</i>
<i>in order to found a religion</i>

302
00:23:13.294 --> 00:23:16.130
<i>like the Eternal</i>
<i>Paradise Faith.</i>

303
00:23:16.163 --> 00:23:18.065
<i>I pitied them.</i>

304
00:23:18.099 --> 00:23:21.636
<i>so I always played along</i>
<i>with their make-believe ideas.</i>

305
00:23:22.670 --> 00:23:26.240
<i>I never once heard</i>
<i>the voice of the gods.</i>

306
00:23:26.274 --> 00:23:29.176
<i>At first.</i>
<i>I didn't know how to deal</i>

307
00:23:29.210 --> 00:23:33.446
<i>with the hordes of people</i>
<i>worshipping and praying to me.</i>

308
00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:36.918
<i>Seeing these grownups</i>
<i>come crying to a child.</i>

309
00:23:36.951 --> 00:23:40.054
<i>saying they were suffering.</i>
<i>pleading for help.</i>

310
00:23:40.087 --> 00:23:43.658
<i>made me worry</i>
<i>if they were sick in the head.</i>

311
00:23:44.725 --> 00:23:46.627
<i>After nearly</i>
<i>putting me to sleep</i>

312
00:23:46.661 --> 00:23:49.764
<i>with their personal stories.</i>
<i>they would bow to me.</i>

313
00:23:49.797 --> 00:23:52.967
<i>asking to be guided</i>
<i>to Paradise.</i>

314
00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:54.835
<i>I cried.</i>

315
00:23:55.803 --> 00:23:58.306
<i>"You poor things." I thought.</i>

316
00:23:58.339 --> 00:24:01.008
<i>"Paradise doesn't even exist."</i>

317
00:24:01.042 --> 00:24:05.579
<i>It's just a fairy tale</i>
<i>concocted by deluded humans.</i>

318
00:24:06.414 --> 00:24:09.283
<i>There are no gods or buddhas.</i>

319
00:24:09.317 --> 00:24:11.953
<i>These people</i>
<i>had lived for decades.</i>

320
00:24:11.986 --> 00:24:15.856
<i>yet they still couldn't grasp</i>
<i>that simple truth.</i>

321
00:24:15.890 --> 00:24:19.260
<i>When you die.</i>
<i>you return to nothingness.</i>

322
00:24:19.293 --> 00:24:21.195
<i>All feeling ceases.</i>

323
00:24:21.228 --> 00:24:23.531
<i>Your heart stops.</i>

324
00:24:23.564 --> 00:24:25.533
<i>Your brain stops.</i>

325
00:24:25.566 --> 00:24:28.035
<i>You rot and</i>
<i>return to the earth.</i>

326
00:24:28.069 --> 00:24:31.605
<i>Such is the fate</i>
<i>of every living creature.</i>

327
00:24:33.641 --> 00:24:37.345
<i>To be too foolish</i>
<i>to accept reality...</i>

328
00:24:37.378 --> 00:24:40.014
<i>what a hard life that must be.</i>

329
00:24:40.047 --> 00:24:44.218
<i>I want to bring happiness</i>
<i>to these pitiful people.</i>

330
00:24:44.251 --> 00:24:46.020
<i>I want to save them.</i>

331
00:24:47.021 --> 00:24:49.090
<i>I truly believe...</i>

332
00:24:49.123 --> 00:24:51.258
<i>that is my purpose here.</i>

333
00:24:57.465 --> 00:25:00.167
Aww. still nothing.

334
00:25:00.201 --> 00:25:01.669
And that was number five.

335
00:25:01.702 --> 00:25:03.437
What will you do?

336
00:25:03.471 --> 00:25:06.240
The toxin's
getting less effective.

337
00:25:06.273 --> 00:25:10.244
How many more times
do you think you can adapt it?

338
00:25:10.277 --> 00:25:11.979
Oh! Are you out of breath now?

339
00:25:12.013 --> 00:25:14.682
Look at all that sweat.

340
00:25:14.715 --> 00:25:15.883
Are you all right?

341
00:25:15.916 --> 00:25:19.253
<i>- So this is the power</i>
<i>of an Upper Rank.</i>

342
00:25:20.321 --> 00:25:22.623
<i>None of my poisons</i>
<i>are working.</i>

343
00:25:23.624 --> 00:25:26.694
<i>He's adapting too fast</i>
<i>to keep up with!</i>

344
00:25:28.596 --> 00:25:31.065
Your alveoli must be dead now.

345
00:25:33.401 --> 00:25:34.602
Painful.

346
00:25:34.635 --> 00:25:36.337
You did breathe it in...

347
00:25:36.370 --> 00:25:38.773
my Blood Demon Art.

348
00:25:39.907 --> 00:25:42.877
<i>- He turns his frozen blood</i>
<i>into mist</i>

349
00:25:42.910 --> 00:25:45.279
<i>and disperses it</i>
<i>with his fans.</i>

350
00:25:45.312 --> 00:25:48.849
<i>Even breathing around him</i>
<i>is dangerous now.</i>

351
00:25:56.490 --> 00:25:57.758
<i>This time...</i>

352
00:25:57.792 --> 00:26:00.728
<i>I'll increase the dose</i>
<i>with multiple strikes!</i>

353
00:26:01.530 --> 00:26:02.763
<i>Insect Breathing...</i>

354
00:26:02.797 --> 00:26:04.398
<i>Dance of the Dragonfly...</i>

355
00:26:11.540 --> 00:26:13.841
<i>Compound Eye Hexagon!</i>

356
00:26:16.377 --> 00:26:17.645
- I can't believe it.

357
00:26:17.678 --> 00:26:19.747
Such blazing speed.

358
00:26:19.780 --> 00:26:23.818
You might be the fastest
Hashira I've ever met!

359
00:26:27.288 --> 00:26:28.523
<i>He...</i>

360
00:26:28.557 --> 00:26:29.490
<i>got me.</i>

361
00:26:31.325 --> 00:26:32.893
- Forget the poison.

362
00:26:32.927 --> 00:26:35.729
Why not try to decapitate me?

363
00:26:35.763 --> 00:26:38.165
With your speed.
you might have won.

364
00:26:39.166 --> 00:26:41.335
Maybe not.

365
00:26:41.368 --> 00:26:44.171
I mean. you are small.

366
00:26:47.208 --> 00:26:50.744
<i>Why</i> are <i>my hands</i>
<i>so small. I wonder?</i>

367
00:26:52.113 --> 00:26:55.683
<i>How come I was never</i>
<i>able to grow taller?</i>

368
00:26:57.118 --> 00:27:00.321
<i>If my stature were</i>
<i>just a little bigger.</i>

369
00:27:00.354 --> 00:27:04.559
<i>could I have been able</i>
<i>to behead and defeat a demon?</i>

370
00:27:04.593 --> 00:27:07.294
<i>The longer</i>
<i>your arms and legs are.</i>

371
00:27:07.328 --> 00:27:08.963
<i>the more muscles you have.</i>

372
00:27:08.996 --> 00:27:11.999
<i>which means more strength</i>
<i>in your attacks.</i>

373
00:27:14.835 --> 00:27:17.771
<i>My sister was also</i>
<i>of small frame.</i>

374
00:27:17.805 --> 00:27:20.007
<i>but she was taller than I.</i>

375
00:27:21.842 --> 00:27:25.112
<i>How I envy Mr. Himejima.</i>

376
00:27:25.146 --> 00:27:27.681
<i>Seeing someone like him</i>
<i>come to their rescue</i>

377
00:27:27.715 --> 00:27:29.750
<i>would give anyone relief.</i>

378
00:27:33.588 --> 00:27:36.490
<i>I know what my sister</i>
<i>really wanted to say</i>

379
00:27:36.525 --> 00:27:39.260
<i>but didn't have the heart to.</i>

380
00:27:42.696 --> 00:27:44.465
- Oh. no.

381
00:27:44.498 --> 00:27:46.767
Have our games come to an end?

382
00:27:46.800 --> 00:27:48.302
That's too bad.

383
00:27:51.472 --> 00:27:55.176
<i>- "I don't think you'll win</i>
<i>against that demon."</i>

384
00:27:55.209 --> 00:27:57.711
<i>That's what you</i>
<i>were going to say.</i>

385
00:27:57.745 --> 00:28:00.381
<i>but you stopped yourself.</i>
<i>didn't you?</i>

386
00:28:00.414 --> 00:28:03.117
Pull yourself together.

387
00:28:08.289 --> 00:28:10.191
This is no time for tears.

388
00:28:11.358 --> 00:28:13.327
<i>- Sister.</i>

389
00:28:13.360 --> 00:28:15.162
- Stand up.

390
00:28:15.196 --> 00:28:16.363
- I can't.

391
00:28:16.397 --> 00:28:18.199
I've lost so much blood.

392
00:28:18.232 --> 00:28:22.403
My left lung is punctured.
and I can't even breathe.

393
00:28:22.436 --> 00:28:24.539
- You can. and you will.

394
00:28:24.573 --> 00:28:25.773
Stand up.

395
00:28:25.806 --> 00:28:28.543
You are a Hashira. Shinobu!

396
00:28:30.177 --> 00:28:33.615
- If you've made up your mind
to defeat him. then do so.

397
00:28:33.648 --> 00:28:36.050
No excuses.

398
00:28:36.083 --> 00:28:39.954
Win by whatever means you can.

399
00:28:39.987 --> 00:28:43.891
Remember your promise
to me and Kanao.

400
00:28:45.660 --> 00:28:47.795
<i>- Kanao.</i>

401
00:28:50.565 --> 00:28:52.466
Forgive me.

402
00:28:52.499 --> 00:28:54.835
You must be suffering
right now.

403
00:28:59.139 --> 00:29:02.142
- I know that you
have it in you.

404
00:29:02.176 --> 00:29:03.777
Do your best.

405
00:29:04.679 --> 00:29:05.946
- Huh?

406
00:29:09.883 --> 00:29:11.686
Wait. are you...

407
00:29:11.720 --> 00:29:12.987
standing up?

408
00:29:14.656 --> 00:29:16.056
Scary.

409
00:29:16.090 --> 00:29:18.425
Are you actually a human?

410
00:29:18.459 --> 00:29:23.230
I slashed your collarbone.
your lungs. and your ribs.

411
00:29:23.264 --> 00:29:25.299
At your diminutive size

412
00:29:25.332 --> 00:29:28.135
and the amount
of blood you've lost.

413
00:29:28.168 --> 00:29:30.304
how are you
not dead right now?

414
00:29:31.472 --> 00:29:32.741
- See? Right there!

415
00:29:32.773 --> 00:29:35.876
There clearly is blood
gurgling in your lungs.

416
00:29:35.909 --> 00:29:38.979
The pain must be unimaginable.

417
00:29:39.013 --> 00:29:41.782
Surrender. and I'll put
an end to your suffering.

418
00:29:41.815 --> 00:29:43.183
It'll be quick!

419
00:29:44.018 --> 00:29:46.120
It's too late for you.

420
00:29:46.153 --> 00:29:47.656
so just let go.

421
00:29:47.689 --> 00:29:50.391
<i>- I'll make a go</i>
<i>for his neck this time</i>

422
00:29:50.424 --> 00:29:53.894
<i>and put everything I have</i>
<i>left into this strike!</i>

423
00:29:53.927 --> 00:29:56.430
Insect Breathing...

424
00:29:56.463 --> 00:29:58.399
Dance of the Centipede...

425
00:29:58.432 --> 00:30:00.000
- Hmm?

426
00:30:00.034 --> 00:30:02.202
- Hundred-legged Zigzag.

427
00:30:18.285 --> 00:30:19.453
Huh?

428
00:30:24.958 --> 00:30:28.429
<i>It feels like</i>
<i>she's everywhere at once.</i>

429
00:30:28.462 --> 00:30:30.931
<i>Just her movement</i>
<i>destroyed the bridge.</i>

430
00:30:33.635 --> 00:30:34.868
<i>- So fast.</i>

431
00:30:34.902 --> 00:30:36.504
<i>I can't follow her.</i>

432
00:30:42.644 --> 00:30:43.545
<i>From below?</i>

433
00:30:57.057 --> 00:31:00.227
<i>Back when I was a child...</i>

434
00:31:00.260 --> 00:31:02.496
<i>I thought of happiness</i>
<i>like a road.</i>

435
00:31:02.530 --> 00:31:05.332
<i>one that stretched on</i>
<i>into the distance</i>

436
00:31:05.366 --> 00:31:07.234
<i>with no end in sight.</i>

437
00:31:10.938 --> 00:31:13.107
<i>It wasn't</i>
<i>until it was destroyed</i>

438
00:31:13.140 --> 00:31:15.476
<i>that I finally realized</i>

439
00:31:15.510 --> 00:31:19.446
<i>the road beneath my feet was</i>
<i>but a thin sheet of glass.</i>

440
00:31:22.249 --> 00:31:26.920
<i>However. some haven't</i>
<i>had the glass broken yet.</i>

441
00:31:27.789 --> 00:31:30.057
<i>All I wanted</i>
<i>after being saved</i>

442
00:31:30.090 --> 00:31:32.527
<i>was to become stronger</i>

443
00:31:32.560 --> 00:31:37.197
<i>so that someday</i>
<i>I could protect those people.</i>

444
00:31:38.833 --> 00:31:42.604
<i>So we made a promise...</i>

445
00:31:44.405 --> 00:31:49.243
<i>to vanquish the demons.</i>
<i>as many as we could.</i>

446
00:31:49.276 --> 00:31:50.512
<i>together.</i>

447
00:31:53.247 --> 00:31:56.250
<i>In hopes that the pain</i>
<i>we suffered</i>

448
00:31:56.283 --> 00:31:58.952
<i>would never be felt</i>
<i>by another.</i>

449
00:32:07.161 --> 00:32:09.363
<i>Even if I'm weak...</i>

450
00:32:12.867 --> 00:32:16.136
<i>even if I can't</i>
<i>decapitate demons.</i>

451
00:32:16.170 --> 00:32:20.875
<i>if I can take down just one.</i>
<i>I can save dozens of lives.</i>

452
00:32:20.909 --> 00:32:22.877
<i>And if that demon's</i>
<i>an Upper Rank.</i>

453
00:32:22.911 --> 00:32:25.713
<i>it could mean</i>
<i>saving hundreds!</i>

454
00:32:27.448 --> 00:32:31.051
<i>It's not a matter</i>
<i>of can or cannot.</i>

455
00:32:31.084 --> 00:32:33.588
<i>This is something</i>
<i>I have to do.</i>

456
00:32:38.860 --> 00:32:40.394
- Are you angry?

457
00:32:42.196 --> 00:32:45.733
<i>- Yes. I am angry. Tanjiro.</i>

458
00:32:45.767 --> 00:32:47.167
<i>I'm furious.</i>

459
00:32:48.101 --> 00:32:52.574
<i>In fact. I'm always angry.</i>

460
00:32:52.607 --> 00:32:54.374
<i>How could I not be?</i>

461
00:32:56.778 --> 00:32:59.313
<i>My parents were killed.</i>

462
00:33:00.147 --> 00:33:03.484
<i>My older sister was killed.</i>

463
00:33:03.518 --> 00:33:06.621
<i>My Tsuguko. other than Kanao.</i>
<i>were killed.</i>

464
00:33:08.055 --> 00:33:09.891
<i>And those poor girls...</i>

465
00:33:09.924 --> 00:33:12.527
<i>if it weren't for the demons.</i>

466
00:33:12.560 --> 00:33:16.029
<i>if it weren't for the demons</i>
<i>that killed their loved ones.</i>

467
00:33:16.063 --> 00:33:19.500
<i>they'd be living happily</i>
<i>with their families.</i>

468
00:33:21.769 --> 00:33:25.138
<i>It's all so infuriating.</i>

469
00:33:25.172 --> 00:33:27.407
<i>Stop messing with me.</i>
<i>damn it!</i>

470
00:33:27.441 --> 00:33:32.312
<i>Why the hell isn't my poison</i>
<i>working on this prick?</i>

471
00:33:33.347 --> 00:33:34.816
<i>You bastard!</i>

472
00:33:46.026 --> 00:33:46.961
- I'm moved!

473
00:33:46.995 --> 00:33:48.730
You did your best.

474
00:33:48.763 --> 00:33:50.965
Even though you're so weak!

475
00:33:50.999 --> 00:33:52.934
You must have worked
so incredibly hard

476
00:33:52.967 --> 00:33:55.135
to get to this point.

477
00:33:55.168 --> 00:33:57.337
You're weaker
than your sister.

478
00:33:57.371 --> 00:33:59.941
and yet you
somehow outlived her.

479
00:34:01.074 --> 00:34:03.545
It's a miracle
you survived this long.

480
00:34:06.079 --> 00:34:07.347
Even when hope is gone.

481
00:34:07.381 --> 00:34:10.518
humans always fight
to the bitter end.

482
00:34:10.552 --> 00:34:12.286
Humans are so foolish!

483
00:34:12.319 --> 00:34:15.957
But that's what makes them
so beautiful.

484
00:34:15.990 --> 00:34:19.059
I deem you worthy
of becoming part of me.

485
00:34:19.092 --> 00:34:22.062
You and I
shall share eternity!

486
00:34:25.232 --> 00:34:27.869
Do you have any last words?

487
00:34:27.902 --> 00:34:29.771
I'm listening.

488
00:34:34.141 --> 00:34:37.077
Rot in hell. you bastard.

489
00:34:42.082 --> 00:34:43.751
Master!

490
00:35:14.716 --> 00:35:17.785
<i>I can't shake</i>
<i>the feeling he's here.</i>

491
00:35:17.819 --> 00:35:19.386
<i>He must be.</i>

492
00:35:19.419 --> 00:35:22.023
<i>He's got a score to settle</i>
<i>with me. too.</i>

493
00:35:29.262 --> 00:35:30.430
<i>The people we love.</i>

494
00:35:30.464 --> 00:35:34.401
<i>the people we hold dear</i>
<i>are so precious.</i>

495
00:35:34.434 --> 00:35:37.404
<i>We take for granted</i>
<i>that they'll always be there.</i>

496
00:35:38.205 --> 00:35:39.239
<i>However...</i>

497
00:35:39.272 --> 00:35:41.809
<i>that's just</i>
<i>a selfish delusion.</i>

498
00:35:41.843 --> 00:35:43.911
- Flower Breathing...

499
00:35:43.945 --> 00:35:46.346
<i>Because the thought</i>
<i>of living without them</i>

500
00:35:46.380 --> 00:35:48.049
<i>is simply unbearable.</i>

501
00:35:48.082 --> 00:35:49.416
- Fourth Form...

502
00:35:50.217 --> 00:35:52.720
Crimson Hanagoromo!

503
00:35:59.192 --> 00:36:02.295
- Wow.
You nearly got me there.

504
00:36:05.733 --> 00:36:08.636
<i>They'll always</i>
<i>be alive and close by...</i>

505
00:36:09.637 --> 00:36:12.607
<i>it's a naive thought.</i>
<i>I know.</i>

506
00:36:12.640 --> 00:36:14.742
<i>But we all want</i>
<i>to believe it.</i>

507
00:36:18.046 --> 00:36:19.847
- Would you mind
holding off your attacks

508
00:36:19.881 --> 00:36:21.314
for just a second?

509
00:36:21.348 --> 00:36:23.183
I'm trying to absorb her.

510
00:36:31.993 --> 00:36:33.928
- How strange.

511
00:36:33.961 --> 00:36:36.263
You're not taking the bait.
are you?

512
00:36:37.297 --> 00:36:38.599
What she did earlier.

513
00:36:38.633 --> 00:36:41.736
that motion she made
with her fingers.

514
00:36:41.769 --> 00:36:45.372
was that her
warning you of my powers?

515
00:36:45.405 --> 00:36:48.943
I'm impressed she thought
to do that so quickly.

516
00:36:48.976 --> 00:36:50.812
Good job. You did it!

517
00:36:50.845 --> 00:36:52.947
Too bad it doesn't matter.

518
00:36:55.315 --> 00:36:58.452
Well. in case
you were wondering.

519
00:36:58.485 --> 00:37:02.190
your Master was tastier
than I imagined.

520
00:37:04.025 --> 00:37:05.660
And now you're here.

521
00:37:05.693 --> 00:37:09.262
It's just one feast
after another. it seems.

522
00:37:09.296 --> 00:37:13.901
Ah. this truly is...

523
00:37:13.935 --> 00:37:16.236
a wonderful night.

524
00:37:29.416 --> 00:37:31.619
- You can't hide.

525
00:37:31.652 --> 00:37:32.920
Come out.

526
00:37:33.921 --> 00:37:36.657
Have some dignity and face me.

527
00:37:37.959 --> 00:37:41.529
Sounds like someone ought
to teach you some manners.

528
00:37:41.562 --> 00:37:43.731
Did you forget
that I'm your senior?

529
00:37:43.765 --> 00:37:47.769
You look a little stronger
than the last time I saw you.

530
00:37:47.802 --> 00:37:52.707
It's too bad you still reek
of being a pathetic weakling.

531
00:37:57.477 --> 00:38:01.916
It's been a while.
hasn't it. Zenitsu?

532
00:38:04.519 --> 00:38:08.321
- Kaigaku.
you don't get my respect.

533
00:38:08.355 --> 00:38:10.323
You're a demon.

534
00:38:10.357 --> 00:38:12.425
You'll be treated as such.

535
00:38:25.640 --> 00:38:28.375
<i>Water Breathing Ninth Form...</i>

536
00:38:29.844 --> 00:38:32.445
<i>Splashing Water Flow.</i>
<i>Turbulent!</i>

537
00:38:34.882 --> 00:38:36.050
- Stay focused!

538
00:38:36.083 --> 00:38:37.417
- All right!

539
00:38:38.519 --> 00:38:40.688
<i>This place is insane.</i>

540
00:38:40.721 --> 00:38:43.157
<i>The building keeps shifting</i>
<i>and rearranging itself.</i>

541
00:38:43.191 --> 00:38:45.226
<i>as if it's alive!</i>

542
00:38:45.259 --> 00:38:48.896
<i>I can tell that it's</i>
<i>trying to separate us!</i>

543
00:38:48.930 --> 00:38:51.265
<i>We have to regroup</i>
<i>with the other Corps members</i>

544
00:38:51.299 --> 00:38:53.935
<i>and stay together</i>
<i>'til we reach Muzan!</i>

545
00:38:57.905 --> 00:38:59.372
- Caw!

546
00:39:00.274 --> 00:39:01.976
Caw!

547
00:39:02.009 --> 00:39:03.443
Attention!

548
00:39:03.476 --> 00:39:05.680
Shinobu Kocho is dead!

549
00:39:05.713 --> 00:39:08.983
She fought valiantly
against Upper Two

550
00:39:09.016 --> 00:39:10.751
but was defeated!

551
00:39:51.959 --> 00:39:53.060
<i>- Strange.</i>

552
00:39:53.094 --> 00:39:55.830
<i>There's a piece of paper</i>
<i>wrapped around its neck.</i>

553
00:39:55.863 --> 00:39:58.099
<i>How are the crows</i>
<i>already here?</i>

554
00:40:02.536 --> 00:40:04.372
- Shinobu is dead.

555
00:40:04.404 --> 00:40:06.774
But we must push forward.

556
00:40:06.807 --> 00:40:10.044
Think only of what
must be done for victory.

557
00:40:10.077 --> 00:40:11.078
- Right.
- Right.

558
00:40:13.381 --> 00:40:14.715
- And what about the others?

559
00:40:14.749 --> 00:40:17.151
I need reports
on their whereabouts.

560
00:40:18.653 --> 00:40:20.288
Center of the 40th vertical

561
00:40:20.321 --> 00:40:21.956
and 12th horizontal levels.

562
00:40:23.891 --> 00:40:25.760
The Corps members
are fighting off

563
00:40:25.793 --> 00:40:28.996
what appears to be
at least ten demons.

564
00:40:35.670 --> 00:40:37.470
However. more than 30 demons

565
00:40:37.505 --> 00:40:40.341
are moving in their direction
from behind the walls.

566
00:40:46.479 --> 00:40:48.582
<i>Using Mr. Yushiro's eyes.</i>

567
00:40:48.616 --> 00:40:50.952
<i>we're able to see</i>
<i>Blood Demon Arts.</i>

568
00:40:50.985 --> 00:40:54.088
<i>something that isn't possible</i>
<i>to do with the human eye.</i>

569
00:40:55.022 --> 00:40:57.258
<i>Each red light</i>
<i>is a Blood Demon Art.</i>

570
00:40:57.291 --> 00:41:00.795
<i>The more intense they glow.</i>
<i>the more potent their power.</i>

571
00:41:01.629 --> 00:41:02.930
<i>And this place...</i>

572
00:41:02.964 --> 00:41:05.366
<i>the entire area.</i>
<i>buildings and all..</i>

573
00:41:05.399 --> 00:41:08.669
<i>must also be</i>
<i>a Blood Demon Art.</i>

574
00:41:08.703 --> 00:41:11.539
<i>There's seemingly</i>
<i>no end in sight to it.</i>

575
00:41:13.741 --> 00:41:15.876
<i>What incredible power.</i>

576
00:41:17.211 --> 00:41:18.512
<i>A demon labyrinth</i>

577
00:41:18.546 --> 00:41:21.182
<i>with the ability</i>
<i>to branch out endlessly.</i>

578
00:41:24.552 --> 00:41:26.120
<i>And here we lie</i>
<i>at its center.</i>

579
00:41:26.153 --> 00:41:29.757
<i>trapped within the walls</i>
<i>of this infinite castle.</i>

580
00:41:29.790 --> 00:41:31.625
- This one's finished.
- ...goes over there.

581
00:41:31.659 --> 00:41:32.660
- Okay. Goes right there.

582
00:41:32.693 --> 00:41:33.694
- Bring it over here.

583
00:41:33.728 --> 00:41:35.029
<i>- However...</i>
- Yes. that's right.

584
00:41:35.062 --> 00:41:37.198
<i>- ...it's not as if we've</i>
<i>been caught off guard.</i>

585
00:41:37.231 --> 00:41:41.802
<i>My father prepared</i>
<i>for this day meticulously.</i>

586
00:41:41.836 --> 00:41:44.005
<i>With Gyomei's cooperation.</i>

587
00:41:44.038 --> 00:41:46.040
<i>he had the Hashira</i>
<i>within arm's reach</i>

588
00:41:46.073 --> 00:41:47.708
<i>to mobilize at any time.</i>

589
00:41:47.742 --> 00:41:50.611
<i>To prevent the Corps members</i>
<i>from being isolated.</i>

590
00:41:50.644 --> 00:41:53.481
<i>he sent the Kasugai Crows</i>
<i>to gather them into groups</i>

591
00:41:53.514 --> 00:41:54.849
<i>and waited.</i>

592
00:41:54.882 --> 00:41:59.220
<i>He enlisted the aid of</i>
<i>Ms. Tamayo and Mr. Yushiro.</i>

593
00:41:59.253 --> 00:42:00.454
<i>And finally.</i>

594
00:42:00.488 --> 00:42:03.557
<i>to ensure that their plan</i>
<i>would succeed.</i>

595
00:42:03.591 --> 00:42:06.961
<i>my sisters and our parents</i>

596
00:42:06.994 --> 00:42:09.163
<i>readily sacrificed</i>
<i>their lives.</i>

597
00:42:12.466 --> 00:42:15.936
We cannot lose.
no matter what.

598
00:42:22.511 --> 00:42:24.311
<i>Amongst the Blood Demon Arts.</i>

599
00:42:24.345 --> 00:42:25.713
<i>there are</i>
<i>five traces of power</i>

600
00:42:25.746 --> 00:42:27.481
<i>that tower over the rest.</i>

601
00:42:27.516 --> 00:42:29.884
<i>as if flaunting</i>
<i>their strength.</i>

602
00:42:29.917 --> 00:42:32.453
<i>These must be Upper Ranks.</i>

603
00:42:32.486 --> 00:42:34.822
<i>One of them</i>
<i>is at the same spot</i>

604
00:42:34.855 --> 00:42:36.924
<i>where Shinobu</i>
<i>was last seen fighting.</i>

605
00:42:37.625 --> 00:42:38.959
- Found another!

606
00:42:38.993 --> 00:42:42.296
Upper Six and Zenitsu have
just encountered each other!

607
00:42:42.329 --> 00:42:43.931
- An Upper Rank!

608
00:42:43.964 --> 00:42:44.965
Is he alone?

609
00:42:44.999 --> 00:42:47.668
- He is.
It looks to be a one-on-one.

610
00:42:47.701 --> 00:42:50.505
A Hinoe can't beat
an Upper Rank by themself.

611
00:42:50.539 --> 00:42:51.872
Send backup!

612
00:42:58.712 --> 00:43:00.781
What. you frozen in fear?

613
00:43:00.815 --> 00:43:02.817
Guess some things
never change.

614
00:43:02.850 --> 00:43:05.586
Once a coward.
always a coward.

615
00:43:05.619 --> 00:43:08.122
Did you ever
become a Hashira?

616
00:43:08.155 --> 00:43:10.191
Guess not.

617
00:43:10.224 --> 00:43:12.193
That's too bad.

618
00:43:12.226 --> 00:43:14.195
Got any new techniques?

619
00:43:14.228 --> 00:43:16.697
Or still just First Form?

620
00:43:16.730 --> 00:43:18.833
For an Upper Rank
bottom feeder

621
00:43:18.866 --> 00:43:20.935
who's nothing more
than a spare blade.

622
00:43:20.968 --> 00:43:23.337
you're sure acting
awfully proud.

623
00:43:24.371 --> 00:43:25.906
- Wow.

624
00:43:27.041 --> 00:43:30.711
Who taught you to talk
like that? New friends?

625
00:43:30.744 --> 00:43:33.614
- Why the hell
did you become a demon?

626
00:43:34.549 --> 00:43:35.816
You'd never understan--

627
00:43:35.850 --> 00:43:38.385
- You were supposed
to succeed Thunder Breathing.

628
00:43:38.419 --> 00:43:39.954
but you tarnished it!

629
00:43:41.222 --> 00:43:42.524
- Huh?

630
00:43:42.557 --> 00:43:44.925
- After you became a demon...

631
00:43:44.959 --> 00:43:46.827
he...

632
00:43:47.628 --> 00:43:50.030
he committed seppuku!

633
00:43:51.065 --> 00:43:52.500
Even worse...

634
00:43:52.534 --> 00:43:55.035
he did it by himself.

635
00:43:56.137 --> 00:43:58.105
He was all alone.

636
00:43:59.340 --> 00:44:00.575
Because of that.

637
00:44:00.609 --> 00:44:02.743
no one was there
to put him out his misery.

638
00:44:02.776 --> 00:44:05.679
He bled out
and died a painful death.

639
00:44:05.713 --> 00:44:07.715
It's your fault.

640
00:44:07.748 --> 00:44:11.152
Gramps died the most
agonizing death possible!

641
00:44:11.185 --> 00:44:13.220
All because
the Thunder Breathing ranks

642
00:44:13.254 --> 00:44:14.321
produced a demon!

643
00:44:16.290 --> 00:44:18.627
- Why the hell should I care?

644
00:44:18.659 --> 00:44:21.362
Gramps died? So what.

645
00:44:21.395 --> 00:44:22.730
Want me to cry?

646
00:44:22.763 --> 00:44:25.199
Did you expect me
to give a damn?

647
00:44:25.232 --> 00:44:26.367
Well. I don't.

648
00:44:26.400 --> 00:44:27.902
In fact.
I don't care for anyone

649
00:44:27.935 --> 00:44:30.104
who doesn't appreciate me.

650
00:44:30.137 --> 00:44:31.805
No matter what.

651
00:44:31.839 --> 00:44:33.741
this is who I am.

652
00:44:33.774 --> 00:44:36.645
Take the side
of whoever knows my worth.

653
00:44:37.978 --> 00:44:41.315
If the old geezer
really did die in agony.

654
00:44:41.348 --> 00:44:42.917
then I couldn't be happier.

655
00:44:42.950 --> 00:44:46.086
I slaved away
for that ungrateful bastard.

656
00:44:46.120 --> 00:44:48.523
And what does he do
to repay me?

657
00:44:48.557 --> 00:44:50.224
He makes you my co-successor

658
00:44:50.257 --> 00:44:52.426
instead of just letting me
carry the torch.

659
00:44:52.459 --> 00:44:54.461
I hope he rots!

660
00:44:54.495 --> 00:44:56.697
Former Hashira or not.

661
00:44:56.730 --> 00:45:00.100
I would never shed a tear
over some senile geezer.

662
00:45:05.674 --> 00:45:08.309
Gramps knew exactly
what he was doing.

663
00:45:08.342 --> 00:45:11.879
We were made co-successors
because we're weak.

664
00:45:11.912 --> 00:45:14.048
I was only able
to use the First Form.

665
00:45:14.081 --> 00:45:16.917
while you could use
everything but First Form.

666
00:45:16.951 --> 00:45:19.554
I can't help
but feel sorry for Gramps

667
00:45:19.588 --> 00:45:22.022
that he has
two useless successors!

668
00:45:22.056 --> 00:45:23.924
- Don't lump us together.

669
00:45:23.958 --> 00:45:26.493
I'm nothing like you!

670
00:45:26.528 --> 00:45:29.363
Thunder Breathing
Fourth Form...

671
00:45:29.396 --> 00:45:30.731
Distant Thunder!

672
00:45:38.640 --> 00:45:41.108
- You're so slow. scum.

673
00:45:46.581 --> 00:45:47.781
<i>What the hell?</i>

674
00:45:47.815 --> 00:45:50.851
<i>He got me.</i>
<i>His speed is unreal.</i>

675
00:45:50.884 --> 00:45:53.254
<i>He never moved like that.</i>

676
00:45:53.287 --> 00:45:55.256
<i>He's changed.</i>

677
00:45:56.691 --> 00:45:59.126
<i>But he's not the only one.</i>

678
00:46:09.136 --> 00:46:12.674
<i>There's no shame in kneeling</i>
<i>down before the powerful</i>

679
00:46:12.707 --> 00:46:14.908
<i>if it means surviving.</i>

680
00:46:14.942 --> 00:46:19.079
<i>As long as you're alive.</i>
<i>you can still win.</i>

681
00:46:19.980 --> 00:46:23.417
<i>Only once you die</i>
<i>have you lost.</i>

682
00:46:23.450 --> 00:46:26.820
<i>Even if you have to beg</i>
<i>on your hands and knees.</i>

683
00:46:26.854 --> 00:46:28.657
<i>even if you're without a home</i>

684
00:46:28.690 --> 00:46:31.125
<i>and have to drink</i>
<i>from a puddle.</i>

685
00:46:31.158 --> 00:46:35.029
<i>even if they condemn you</i>
<i>for stealing money.</i>

686
00:46:35.062 --> 00:46:36.864
<i>as long as you're alive.</i>

687
00:46:36.897 --> 00:46:39.800
<i>there's still a future</i>
<i>where you can win.</i>

688
00:46:39.833 --> 00:46:43.538
<i>Believing that is</i>
<i>all that's kept me going.</i>

689
00:46:45.640 --> 00:46:47.941
- Forfeit your humanity.

690
00:46:47.975 --> 00:46:51.879
and limitless power
will be within reach.

691
00:46:51.912 --> 00:46:55.182
Should my Lord choose
to acknowledge you.

692
00:46:55.215 --> 00:46:58.385
demon blood shall coarse
through your veins.

693
00:47:02.524 --> 00:47:04.258
- The stronger the swordsman.

694
00:47:04.291 --> 00:47:08.429
the longer it takes
for him to become a demon.

695
00:47:08.462 --> 00:47:12.032
It took me three days
to fully transform.

696
00:47:12.066 --> 00:47:15.436
Turning a Breathing
Technique user into a demon

697
00:47:15.469 --> 00:47:17.237
is no small feat.

698
00:47:17.271 --> 00:47:18.372
Doing such a thing

699
00:47:18.405 --> 00:47:22.042
will require an exorbitant
amount of my Lord's blood.

700
00:47:22.076 --> 00:47:24.713
And though it is rare.

701
00:47:24.746 --> 00:47:26.380
some people.
for whatever reason.

702
00:47:26.413 --> 00:47:29.149
are physically incapable
of becoming demons.

703
00:47:29.183 --> 00:47:30.050
- Huh?

704
00:47:30.084 --> 00:47:33.688
- I'm curious to see
how you will fare.

705
00:47:37.057 --> 00:47:39.661
You must appreciate
this blood.

706
00:47:39.694 --> 00:47:44.932
Even holding it as you are now
is an honor you cannot fathom.

707
00:47:44.965 --> 00:47:47.267
Should you spill
a single drop.

708
00:47:47.301 --> 00:47:50.137
I'll have you dismembered
in an instant.

709
00:47:50.170 --> 00:47:52.674
before it touches the ground.

710
00:47:57.512 --> 00:48:02.049
<i>Even now. I remember</i>
<i>the terror I felt.</i>

711
00:48:02.082 --> 00:48:06.253
<i>like every cell in my body</i>
<i>was screaming in anguish.</i>

712
00:48:08.989 --> 00:48:12.794
<i>Compared to what I felt then.</i>
<i>this is nothing.</i>

713
00:48:12.827 --> 00:48:15.062
<i>He's just a punk.</i>

714
00:48:15.095 --> 00:48:16.531
<i>He might be stronger.</i>

715
00:48:16.564 --> 00:48:18.600
<i>but he's not on par</i>
<i>with an Upper Rank.</i>

716
00:48:18.633 --> 00:48:23.971
<i>Zenitsu Agatsuma</i>
<i>is and always will be trash.</i>

717
00:48:24.004 --> 00:48:25.874
<i>He's a despicable crybaby</i>

718
00:48:25.906 --> 00:48:28.510
<i>without a shred</i>
<i>of dignity or valor.</i>

719
00:48:28.543 --> 00:48:30.277
- Somebody help!

720
00:48:30.310 --> 00:48:34.982
I fell in a pitfall
and twisted my ankle!

721
00:48:35.784 --> 00:48:37.284
<i>- The disrespect.</i>

722
00:48:37.317 --> 00:48:41.121
<i>As if I'd be co-successor</i>
<i>with that sniveling loser.</i>

723
00:48:41.155 --> 00:48:43.725
- Here you are. Kaigaku.

724
00:48:43.758 --> 00:48:45.627
- Hey. Gramps!

725
00:48:45.660 --> 00:48:46.828
Hmm?

726
00:48:46.861 --> 00:48:50.063
- It looks a little big on me.
don't you think?

727
00:48:50.097 --> 00:48:51.265
Maybe I'll grow into it...

728
00:48:51.298 --> 00:48:54.301
<i>- I'm supposed to be</i>
<i>that idiot's equal?</i>

729
00:48:56.069 --> 00:48:58.706
<i>- That's gotta be</i>
<i>some kind of sick joke.</i>

730
00:49:00.240 --> 00:49:02.911
The old bastard
deserved to die!

731
00:49:02.943 --> 00:49:05.212
And if you miss him so dearly.

732
00:49:05.245 --> 00:49:08.115
then I'll see to it
you join him!

733
00:49:08.148 --> 00:49:12.019
<i>- I was only ever able</i>
<i>to learn the First Form.</i>

734
00:49:12.052 --> 00:49:13.454
<i>However. you were able</i>

735
00:49:13.487 --> 00:49:15.824
<i>to learn everything</i>
<i>but the First Form.</i>

736
00:49:18.693 --> 00:49:20.360
<i>Gramps knew that.</i>

737
00:49:20.394 --> 00:49:22.429
<i>His solution</i>
<i>was having us both</i>

738
00:49:22.463 --> 00:49:25.232
<i>succeed the Thunder</i>
<i>Breathing technique.</i>

739
00:49:27.669 --> 00:49:29.303
<i>But you denied him that.</i>

740
00:49:30.103 --> 00:49:32.439
<i>You became a demon</i>

741
00:49:32.473 --> 00:49:34.408
<i>purely to reject him.</i>

742
00:49:36.711 --> 00:49:37.712
<i>It's coming.</i>

743
00:49:37.745 --> 00:49:40.347
- Thunder Breathing
Second Form...

744
00:49:41.448 --> 00:49:42.584
Rice Spirit!

745
00:49:44.985 --> 00:49:48.021
<i>He attacked five times</i>
<i>in one breath.</i>

746
00:49:50.324 --> 00:49:52.259
How many people
have you devoured?!

747
00:49:52.292 --> 00:49:55.429
You can't even tell
right from wrong anymore!

748
00:49:55.462 --> 00:49:58.265
- I'm more aware of those
than I've ever been!

749
00:49:59.667 --> 00:50:00.768
What's the matter?

750
00:50:00.802 --> 00:50:04.639
Aren't you supposed to be
the old geezer's favorite?

751
00:50:04.672 --> 00:50:06.206
If you are...

752
00:50:06.240 --> 00:50:08.576
then show me
what he passed down to you!

753
00:50:08.610 --> 00:50:12.212
It's the only technique
you've got. so use it!

754
00:50:14.883 --> 00:50:18.252
Go all out.
Use everything you got.

755
00:50:18.285 --> 00:50:20.622
And don't you dare
hold back for a second!

756
00:50:27.060 --> 00:50:28.495
Thunder Breathing...

757
00:50:30.932 --> 00:50:32.332
First Form...

758
00:50:33.701 --> 00:50:36.203
- Thunderclap and Flash!

759
00:50:42.109 --> 00:50:44.979
As if a basic attack
like charging me head on

760
00:50:45.013 --> 00:50:47.247
would ever find its mark.

761
00:50:47.281 --> 00:50:49.116
Don't make me laugh!

762
00:50:50.718 --> 00:50:52.620
Thunder Breathing...

763
00:50:52.654 --> 00:50:54.087
Third Form...

764
00:50:54.121 --> 00:50:55.557
Thunder Swarm!

765
00:51:01.094 --> 00:51:03.731
<i>He's attacking me</i>
<i>from every angle at once.</i>

766
00:51:03.765 --> 00:51:04.999
- What's the matter?

767
00:51:05.033 --> 00:51:07.602
Don't tell me
you're done already!

768
00:51:08.903 --> 00:51:10.370
<i>- Thunder Breathing</i>
<i>First Form:</i>

769
00:51:10.404 --> 00:51:13.340
<i>Thunderclap and Flash.</i>
<i>Eightfold!</i>

770
00:51:17.912 --> 00:51:19.547
- That's not gonna work!

771
00:51:20.782 --> 00:51:21.916
Thunder Breathing...

772
00:51:21.950 --> 00:51:23.818
Fifth Form...

773
00:51:26.521 --> 00:51:27.689
Heat Lightning!

774
00:51:29.489 --> 00:51:31.391
- Got ya!

775
00:51:31.425 --> 00:51:34.929
How does the bite of my Blood
Demon Art-enhanced sword feel?

776
00:51:34.963 --> 00:51:37.632
Each strike. on contact.

777
00:51:37.665 --> 00:51:40.935
leaves a wound
that burns your skin.

778
00:51:40.969 --> 00:51:43.170
This proves those
who recognize my talents

779
00:51:43.203 --> 00:51:44.539
and value are right!

780
00:51:44.572 --> 00:51:48.543
And those that dismiss
or condemn me are wrong!

781
00:51:48.576 --> 00:51:50.377
Do you get it now?

782
00:51:50.410 --> 00:51:53.014
This is the power I have!

783
00:51:53.047 --> 00:51:55.282
My power as a demon. that is!

784
00:51:55.315 --> 00:51:57.819
All you know how to do
is use First Form!

785
00:51:57.852 --> 00:52:00.955
Yet that geezer chose
to make you his successor!

786
00:52:00.989 --> 00:52:02.991
And. boy.
what a mistake that was!

787
00:52:10.064 --> 00:52:11.431
So that's it.

788
00:52:11.465 --> 00:52:14.368
This is the path
that you've chosen to take.

789
00:52:15.637 --> 00:52:17.772
I already knew.

790
00:52:17.805 --> 00:52:19.540
I knew. but...

791
00:52:24.545 --> 00:52:27.582
- With this strike.
I'll end this!

792
00:52:27.615 --> 00:52:28.883
You're finished!

793
00:52:28.916 --> 00:52:30.885
Thunder Breathing...

794
00:52:31.919 --> 00:52:33.888
Sixth Form...

795
00:52:41.996 --> 00:52:44.632
Rumble and Flash!

796
00:52:44.666 --> 00:52:48.569
That strike I landed will keep
crackling through your flesh.

797
00:52:48.603 --> 00:52:52.774
This is the power that I
gained by becoming a demon.

798
00:52:52.807 --> 00:52:54.307
Get it now?

799
00:52:54.341 --> 00:52:56.376
I've long surpassed
Thunder Breathing!

800
00:53:00.280 --> 00:53:02.382
You and I aren't equals.

801
00:53:02.416 --> 00:53:03.951
and we never have been!

802
00:53:03.985 --> 00:53:06.754
I'm better than all of you.

803
00:53:06.788 --> 00:53:08.221
Guess the old bastard

804
00:53:08.255 --> 00:53:10.758
shouldn't have put his trust
in you after all.

805
00:53:15.195 --> 00:53:18.166
Come on!
be more like Kaigaku!

806
00:53:18.198 --> 00:53:19.567
He's your senior!

807
00:53:19.600 --> 00:53:21.869
So follow his example.
you hear?

808
00:53:21.903 --> 00:53:23.838
- Hang on.
Isn't the First Form

809
00:53:23.871 --> 00:53:26.574
pretty much the entire basis
of Thunder Breathing?

810
00:53:26.607 --> 00:53:29.242
- Yeah. and it's
the only one he can't do.

811
00:53:29.276 --> 00:53:31.512
You know what that means.
don't ya?

812
00:53:31.546 --> 00:53:33.948
- That even though
he's mastered other forms.

813
00:53:33.981 --> 00:53:35.282
he's still a weakling?

814
00:53:35.315 --> 00:53:36.918
- Yup. exactly.

815
00:53:36.951 --> 00:53:38.251
The way he shows off. though?

816
00:53:38.285 --> 00:53:39.520
He's got such an ego.

817
00:53:39.554 --> 00:53:42.056
- No way he becomes a Hashira.

818
00:53:42.090 --> 00:53:44.926
- Yeah. he'll die before then.

819
00:53:44.959 --> 00:53:47.562
- What'd I do
to deserve that?!

820
00:53:48.830 --> 00:53:52.265
- I heard you went and punched
someone from a higher rank.

821
00:53:52.299 --> 00:53:54.569
Don't go around
makin' trouble. you trash!

822
00:53:54.602 --> 00:53:58.740
It's embarrassing even being
seen in the same room as you.

823
00:54:01.175 --> 00:54:04.712
<i>I was fully aware</i>
<i>that you hated me. Kaigaku.</i>

824
00:54:04.746 --> 00:54:06.848
<i>And to be</i>
<i>perfectly honest...</i>

825
00:54:06.881 --> 00:54:09.083
<i>I hated you. too.</i>

826
00:54:09.117 --> 00:54:10.752
<i>Even so.</i>

827
00:54:10.785 --> 00:54:13.855
<i>I couldn't help</i>
<i>but respect you as well.</i>

828
00:54:13.888 --> 00:54:17.290
<i>You never stopped working</i>
<i>towards your goals.</i>

829
00:54:18.126 --> 00:54:20.228
<i>Despite our differences.</i>

830
00:54:20.260 --> 00:54:23.164
<i>I looked up to you</i>
<i>as an example.</i>

831
00:54:23.197 --> 00:54:25.600
<i>You really were</i>
<i>a special guy.</i>

832
00:54:27.101 --> 00:54:28.803
<i>It wasn't just me.</i>

833
00:54:28.836 --> 00:54:31.438
<i>Gramps thought</i>
<i>you were remarkable. too.</i>

834
00:54:32.339 --> 00:54:33.574
<i>But I guess...</i>

835
00:54:33.608 --> 00:54:35.910
<i>you weren't satisfied</i>
<i>with that. were you?</i>

836
00:54:35.943 --> 00:54:38.311
<i>No matter the day.</i>

837
00:54:38.345 --> 00:54:42.216
<i>the only sound that came</i>
<i>from you was discontent.</i>

838
00:54:43.518 --> 00:54:46.721
<i>It was like the box</i>
<i>where you kept your joy</i>

839
00:54:46.754 --> 00:54:48.321
<i>had a hole in it.</i>

840
00:54:49.757 --> 00:54:52.392
<i>And that joy</i>
<i>kept leaking out.</i>

841
00:54:53.594 --> 00:54:55.863
<i>If the hole isn't mended.</i>

842
00:54:55.897 --> 00:54:58.766
<i>happiness will always</i>
<i>be out of reach.</i>

843
00:55:01.301 --> 00:55:04.404
<i>Gramps.</i>
<i>I'm sorry we're fighting.</i>

844
00:55:05.405 --> 00:55:09.744
<i>But he and I</i>
<i>must walk separate paths.</i>

845
00:55:19.554 --> 00:55:20.353
- Huh?

846
00:55:20.387 --> 00:55:23.157
<i>He's still holding on?</i>

847
00:55:32.399 --> 00:55:33.768
What the hell?!

848
00:55:42.176 --> 00:55:44.679
<i>- Brother...</i>

849
00:55:44.712 --> 00:55:45.880
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

850
00:56:05.633 --> 00:56:09.270
<i>- Thunder Breathing</i>
<i>Seventh Form...</i>

851
00:56:11.973 --> 00:56:14.976
<i>- ...God of Fire Thunder.</i>

852
00:56:21.215 --> 00:56:22.984
<i>That...</i>

853
00:56:23.017 --> 00:56:25.786
<i>was so fast.</i>

854
00:56:25.820 --> 00:56:27.021
<i>That move...</i>

855
00:56:27.054 --> 00:56:27.989
<i>what was it?!</i>

856
00:56:28.022 --> 00:56:29.924
<i>Unbelievable.</i>

857
00:56:29.957 --> 00:56:33.361
<i>How come I've never seen</i>
<i>that technique until now?</i>

858
00:56:33.393 --> 00:56:35.062
Damn you.

859
00:56:35.096 --> 00:56:36.264
Damn you!

860
00:56:36.297 --> 00:56:39.700
I always knew that stupid
geezer liked you more than me!

861
00:56:39.734 --> 00:56:42.837
Why else would he only
teach you that technique?!

862
00:56:42.870 --> 00:56:44.739
- You're wrong.

863
00:56:46.707 --> 00:56:49.677
- Gramps was never
that kind of person.

864
00:56:49.710 --> 00:56:53.547
This technique
is something I made.

865
00:56:53.581 --> 00:56:57.318
I created it all by myself.

866
00:56:57.351 --> 00:56:59.687
My hope was...

867
00:56:59.720 --> 00:57:02.957
that one day.
I'd be able to use it

868
00:57:02.990 --> 00:57:04.892
to fight by your side.

869
00:57:08.461 --> 00:57:10.898
<i>- How is this even possible?</i>

870
00:57:10.932 --> 00:57:14.168
<i>Thunder Breathing</i>
<i>only has six techniques.</i>

871
00:57:14.201 --> 00:57:17.939
<i>and yet</i> he <i>was able</i>
<i>to create a seventh</i> ?

872
00:57:17.972 --> 00:57:22.475
<i>Him? The one who can</i>
<i>only use the First Form?</i>

873
00:57:22.510 --> 00:57:26.080
<i>He's inferior to me</i>
<i>in every way!</i>

874
00:57:27.648 --> 00:57:29.116
<i>I can't accept it.</i>

875
00:57:29.150 --> 00:57:30.551
<i>I won't accept it!</i>

876
00:57:30.584 --> 00:57:33.220
<i>This must be some</i>
<i>kind of twisted joke!</i>

877
00:57:33.254 --> 00:57:37.091
<i>Someone like me</i>
<i>losing to him?!</i>

878
00:57:38.192 --> 00:57:40.594
<i>I must be going insane.</i>

879
00:57:42.363 --> 00:57:46.434
<i>Wait.</i>
<i>with his strength depleted.</i>

880
00:57:46.466 --> 00:57:48.736
<i>I can still have</i>
<i>the last laugh.</i>

881
00:57:48.769 --> 00:57:51.505
<i>This fall will kill him.</i>
<i>and he can't stop it!</i>

882
00:57:51.539 --> 00:57:54.809
<i>I'll be taking him</i>
<i>to hell with me.</i>

883
00:57:56.377 --> 00:57:57.945
Those who never give to others

884
00:57:57.979 --> 00:58:00.514
are never able
to receive in return.

885
00:58:02.316 --> 00:58:04.118
- People who have
nothing but desire

886
00:58:04.151 --> 00:58:06.721
are no different than those
who have nothing at all.

887
00:58:06.754 --> 00:58:10.791
And one cannot create
anything out of nothing.

888
00:58:11.792 --> 00:58:14.729
Dying alone is pathetic.
wouldn't you say?

889
00:58:37.018 --> 00:58:38.285
Where am I?

890
00:58:46.527 --> 00:58:47.762
Gramps!

891
00:58:50.898 --> 00:58:51.932
I'm sorry!

892
00:58:51.966 --> 00:58:54.602
I-I couldn't
get along with Kaigaku!

893
00:58:54.635 --> 00:58:56.937
I even tried
writing him letters.

894
00:58:56.971 --> 00:58:59.607
but-- but he never
wrote me back. and...

895
00:58:59.640 --> 00:59:01.642
If it weren't for me.

896
00:59:01.675 --> 00:59:04.412
he might not have ended up
the way he did.

897
00:59:04.445 --> 00:59:06.981
I'm really sorry! Forgive me!

898
00:59:07.014 --> 00:59:10.117
I wasn't able to pay you back
for everything.

899
00:59:10.151 --> 00:59:13.320
I really wanted you
to see me as a Hashira.

900
00:59:13.354 --> 00:59:15.222
to make you proud.

901
00:59:15.256 --> 00:59:16.590
I'm sorry.

902
00:59:16.624 --> 00:59:18.359
I failed you. Gramps!

903
00:59:21.195 --> 00:59:24.365
I understand
if you hate me now.

904
00:59:24.398 --> 00:59:27.735
Please. just say something.
anything!

905
00:59:29.538 --> 00:59:30.438
Damn it!

906
00:59:30.471 --> 00:59:32.840
What's this grabbing my leg?

907
00:59:34.141 --> 00:59:36.143
Gramps! I just...

908
00:59:36.177 --> 00:59:38.145
I need--

909
00:59:39.914 --> 00:59:41.148
Damn it.

910
00:59:43.217 --> 00:59:44.919
- Zenitsu.

911
00:59:52.226 --> 00:59:53.694
Listen to me. lad.

912
00:59:53.727 --> 00:59:56.197
You are my pride and joy.

913
01:00:19.386 --> 01:00:21.722
Well?
Can you save him?

914
01:00:21.755 --> 01:00:23.424
He's someone that I know.

915
01:00:23.457 --> 01:00:24.859
I can't watch him die.

916
01:00:24.892 --> 01:00:26.627
Please tell me there's a way!

917
01:00:26.660 --> 01:00:28.863
- Keep your voice down.
You're not helping.

918
01:00:28.896 --> 01:00:31.298
Just watch out
for enemy ambushes.

919
01:00:31.332 --> 01:00:34.201
Least then. you'll actually
be doing something useful.

920
01:00:35.302 --> 01:00:38.172
'Scuse me?! And just
who the hell are you. huh?!

921
01:00:38.205 --> 01:00:41.175
I better not find out
you're a lower rank than I am!

922
01:00:41.208 --> 01:00:42.076
<i>- I'm a demon.</i>

923
01:00:42.109 --> 01:00:45.646
<i>I don't care</i>
<i>about your hierarchy.</i>

924
01:00:45.679 --> 01:00:47.381
This'll slow
the Blood Demon Art.

925
01:00:47.414 --> 01:00:49.584
but if these cracks
keep spreading.

926
01:00:49.618 --> 01:00:52.186
it'll travel
all the way to his eyes.

927
01:00:53.220 --> 01:00:55.022
Hey. can you hear me?

928
01:00:58.459 --> 01:01:01.395
- Your bedside manner
really sucks! You know that?!

929
01:01:01.428 --> 01:01:02.963
- I'm also using a hemostatic.

930
01:01:02.997 --> 01:01:04.832
but I still can't get
the bleeding to stop.

931
01:01:04.865 --> 01:01:06.100
- What did I say?!

932
01:01:06.133 --> 01:01:07.268
Don't listen to him!

933
01:01:07.301 --> 01:01:08.435
You're gonna be fine!

934
01:01:08.469 --> 01:01:09.803
I swear
you'll pull through this!

935
01:01:09.837 --> 01:01:11.272
- Yeah. you can do it!

936
01:01:11.305 --> 01:01:12.607
- Fight on! Fight on!

937
01:01:12.641 --> 01:01:15.042
- The only reason
you're alive right now

938
01:01:15.075 --> 01:01:16.777
is because
the Upper Rank you fought

939
01:01:16.810 --> 01:01:19.581
still hadn't mastered
his own techniques.

940
01:01:19.614 --> 01:01:21.650
That was lucky for you.

941
01:01:21.682 --> 01:01:23.817
If you'd fought him
a year from now.

942
01:01:23.851 --> 01:01:25.654
you would have died instantly.

943
01:01:27.254 --> 01:01:29.524
Could you stop
with the doom and gloom?

944
01:01:29.558 --> 01:01:31.660
Consider his feelings!

945
01:01:37.932 --> 01:01:41.268
Hey. don't pretend like
I'm the one in the wrong here.

946
01:01:42.069 --> 01:01:43.404
What?

947
01:01:43.437 --> 01:01:44.673
What are you pointing at?

948
01:01:44.705 --> 01:01:47.542
- Your screaming let
the demons know we're here.

949
01:01:49.476 --> 01:01:51.178
- Don't say I didn't warn you.

950
01:01:52.614 --> 01:01:54.748
- Hey. it was Yushiro. right?

951
01:01:54.782 --> 01:01:57.184
Take care of Agatsuma.

952
01:01:57.218 --> 01:01:58.385
Charge!

953
01:02:00.387 --> 01:02:03.625
- Murata. please take care
of them quickly. okay?

954
01:02:03.658 --> 01:02:05.993
- I am gonna give you
such an earful later!

955
01:02:06.026 --> 01:02:07.094
- Damn.

956
01:02:08.729 --> 01:02:11.265
- Water Breathing
Second Form...

957
01:02:11.298 --> 01:02:12.567
Water Wheel!

958
01:02:15.670 --> 01:02:17.037
We're gonna head them off!

959
01:02:17.071 --> 01:02:18.739
Follow my lead. everyone!

960
01:02:35.724 --> 01:02:37.024
<i>This is bad.</i>

961
01:02:37.057 --> 01:02:38.759
They're gonna run into <i>him</i> .

962
01:02:42.062 --> 01:02:44.832
<i>- We haven't encountered</i>
<i>any Upper Ranks.</i>

963
01:02:44.865 --> 01:02:47.134
<i>Are we still</i>
<i>that far from Muzan?</i>

964
01:02:47.167 --> 01:02:49.370
<i>I hope the others</i>
<i>are all right.</i>

965
01:02:52.574 --> 01:02:54.074
<i>Ms. Shinobu.</i>

966
01:02:54.975 --> 01:02:57.278
<i>We're going to win</i>
<i>this battle...</i>

967
01:02:57.311 --> 01:02:59.913
<i>for you. for everyone.</i>

968
01:03:02.684 --> 01:03:04.753
- That jolt. what was that?

969
01:03:04.785 --> 01:03:06.487
- M-Mr. Giyu!

970
01:03:06.521 --> 01:03:08.255
- Stay there! Keep calm.

971
01:03:11.091 --> 01:03:13.027
<i>- Is someone else fighting?</i>

972
01:03:13.060 --> 01:03:15.329
<i>Are we about to lose</i>
<i>another comrade?</i>

973
01:03:21.035 --> 01:03:23.937
<i>No. it's something else...</i>

974
01:03:23.971 --> 01:03:25.806
<i>and it's coming this way.</i>

975
01:03:28.409 --> 01:03:30.578
<i>This-- This scent...</i>

976
01:03:38.653 --> 01:03:39.920
Above us!

977
01:03:39.953 --> 01:03:41.255
Get back. Tanjiro!

978
01:03:45.627 --> 01:03:47.895
- Long time no see.

979
01:03:49.263 --> 01:03:52.600
It's commendable
you got this far.

980
01:03:52.634 --> 01:03:55.603
Especially for a puny insect.

981
01:03:56.805 --> 01:03:58.439
Don't you agree...

982
01:03:58.472 --> 01:03:59.674
Tanjiro?!

983
01:04:02.242 --> 01:04:05.112
Akaza!

984
01:04:37.411 --> 01:04:38.879
<i>This place...</i>

985
01:04:38.912 --> 01:04:41.148
<i>if I had to guess.</i>
<i>this fleshy cocoon</i>

986
01:04:41.181 --> 01:04:43.450
<i>is breaking down</i>
<i>and disposing the drug</i>

987
01:04:43.484 --> 01:04:46.286
<i>that's rescinding</i>
<i>his demon form.</i>

988
01:04:47.555 --> 01:04:49.123
<i>Muzan Kibutsuji...</i>

989
01:04:49.156 --> 01:04:53.894
<i>I had sworn to destroy you</i>
<i>by any means necessary.</i>

990
01:04:54.729 --> 01:04:56.096
<i>Yet at this moment.</i>

991
01:04:56.130 --> 01:04:58.899
<i>I am powerless to do so.</i>

992
01:05:06.641 --> 01:05:07.941
Soon enough...

993
01:05:07.975 --> 01:05:10.010
I'll be absorbed as well.

994
01:05:10.812 --> 01:05:12.614
Please. someone...

995
01:05:12.647 --> 01:05:15.048
anyone. come quickly!

996
01:05:15.850 --> 01:05:17.519
I beg you!

997
01:05:26.994 --> 01:05:29.096
Yeah. I've got that one.

998
01:05:29.129 --> 01:05:31.064
- Speed is important.
but accuracy is more so.

999
01:05:31.098 --> 01:05:34.968
<i>According to Father.</i>
<i>if Muzan should die.</i>

1000
01:05:35.002 --> 01:05:37.104
<i>the other demons</i>
<i>will also perish.</i>

1001
01:05:37.137 --> 01:05:38.773
- Uh. that one is...
- Can you help me?

1002
01:05:38.807 --> 01:05:43.177
<i>- By that logic. it's clear</i>
<i>that Muzan is still alive.</i>

1003
01:05:43.977 --> 01:05:45.312
<i>At this very moment.</i>

1004
01:05:45.345 --> 01:05:48.449
<i>Ms. Tamayo must be</i>
<i>suppressing his powers.</i>

1005
01:05:49.483 --> 01:05:50.752
<i>If she weren't.</i>

1006
01:05:50.785 --> 01:05:54.188
<i>he would surely be aware</i>
<i>of Yushiro's watchful gaze.</i>

1007
01:05:55.222 --> 01:05:57.491
<i>Before Muzan's powers</i>
<i>are fully restored.</i>

1008
01:05:57.525 --> 01:06:01.228
<i>we must do whatever it takes</i>
<i>to see that he's defeated.</i>

1009
01:06:02.963 --> 01:06:04.331
<i>I have to wonder. though.</i>

1010
01:06:04.364 --> 01:06:08.235
<i>Inside of this</i>
<i>"Infinite Castle..."</i>

1011
01:06:08.268 --> 01:06:11.238
<i>will we really</i>
<i>be able to find him</i>

1012
01:06:11.271 --> 01:06:13.207
<i>and put an end to it all?</i>

1013
01:06:18.479 --> 01:06:20.949
- No need to be nervous.

1014
01:06:20.981 --> 01:06:23.417
You're doing a fine job.
my child.

1015
01:06:24.953 --> 01:06:28.989
Muzan will surely
reveal himself once more.

1016
01:06:29.022 --> 01:06:31.626
just as he did
when he found me.

1017
01:06:33.962 --> 01:06:36.230
When it comes to this man.

1018
01:06:36.263 --> 01:06:38.465
that's simply his nature.

1019
01:06:42.670 --> 01:06:44.906
- Excuse me. The one
on the top actually goes here.

1020
01:06:44.939 --> 01:06:46.406
<i>- I understand. Father...</i>

1021
01:06:46.440 --> 01:06:48.308
<i>I will see to it</i>
<i>our plan succeeds.</i>

1022
01:06:48.342 --> 01:06:50.143
- Something like that?
- Move it back down.

1023
01:06:50.177 --> 01:06:52.179
<i>We must find him</i>

1024
01:06:52.212 --> 01:06:54.516
<i>before the Corps members'</i>
<i>strength is fully depleted</i>

1025
01:06:54.549 --> 01:06:57.451
<i>and settle this</i>
<i>once and for all!</i>

1026
01:07:07.929 --> 01:07:09.597
Protect them!

1027
01:07:09.631 --> 01:07:10.999
- Everybody. group up!

1028
01:07:11.031 --> 01:07:12.366
We have to form a wall.

1029
01:07:12.399 --> 01:07:14.401
get their attention
off the Hashira!

1030
01:07:14.434 --> 01:07:16.938
- Please. sir.
go on ahead without us!

1031
01:07:16.971 --> 01:07:19.574
- You as well! We got this!

1032
01:07:19.607 --> 01:07:20.775
- Are you certain?

1033
01:07:29.216 --> 01:07:31.986
- We are!
Just defeat Kibutsuji!

1034
01:07:32.020 --> 01:07:33.186
- Please. sir!

1035
01:07:33.220 --> 01:07:35.255
- Very well. then.

1036
01:07:35.289 --> 01:07:38.425
I will put my faith
in your efforts here.

1037
01:07:38.458 --> 01:07:39.827
Tokito!

1038
01:07:40.995 --> 01:07:42.229
All right!

1039
01:07:42.262 --> 01:07:45.465
Let's show them the fruits
of our Hashira training!

1040
01:07:45.499 --> 01:07:46.701
- Right!
- Right!

1041
01:07:54.008 --> 01:07:56.678
<i>Everyone. thank you.</i>

1042
01:07:56.711 --> 01:07:58.111
<i>I know Father would be proud</i>

1043
01:07:58.145 --> 01:08:00.113
<i>to see you</i>
<i>giving it your all.</i>

1044
01:08:11.091 --> 01:08:12.392
Stop that.

1045
01:08:12.426 --> 01:08:15.697
- You must keep
your hands moving.

1046
01:08:15.730 --> 01:08:17.865
Right now. we need to focus.

1047
01:08:19.767 --> 01:08:20.868
- Yes.

1048
01:08:24.005 --> 01:08:27.575
- Master Kiriya.
he's quite impressive.

1049
01:08:27.609 --> 01:08:30.044
It's clear
he's still in mourning

1050
01:08:30.078 --> 01:08:31.946
over the loss of the Master.

1051
01:08:31.980 --> 01:08:34.816
yet his duty is unwavering.

1052
01:08:34.849 --> 01:08:38.586
He's led the Demon Slayer
Corps rather splendidly.

1053
01:08:39.954 --> 01:08:42.657
Wouldn't you agree.
Mr. Rengoku?

1054
01:08:43.691 --> 01:08:45.292
- I would. indeed.

1055
01:08:46.594 --> 01:08:49.363
These children are
still young in years.

1056
01:08:49.396 --> 01:08:52.567
but their resolve
is anything but childish.

1057
01:08:53.835 --> 01:08:56.203
I swear to protect them.

1058
01:08:56.236 --> 01:08:59.272
just as Kyojuro did before me.

1059
01:08:59.306 --> 01:09:01.909
I will risk my own life
to do so.

1060
01:09:14.889 --> 01:09:18.559
<i>- I didn't think</i>
<i>she would suffer this much.</i>

1061
01:09:18.593 --> 01:09:22.864
<i>The Master was working</i>
<i>with a demon named Tamayo.</i>

1062
01:09:22.897 --> 01:09:25.232
<i>who delivered this antidote.</i>

1063
01:09:25.265 --> 01:09:28.301
<i>I've administered it</i>
<i>as she instructed.</i>

1064
01:09:29.671 --> 01:09:30.972
<i>Even so...</i>

1065
01:09:31.005 --> 01:09:35.710
<i>will Nezuko be able to turn</i>
<i>back into a human. I wonder.</i>

1066
01:09:35.743 --> 01:09:39.179
<i>If Nezuko does</i>
<i>become human again.</i>

1067
01:09:39.212 --> 01:09:42.382
<i>Muzan's grand scheme</i>
<i>will collapse.</i>

1068
01:09:42.416 --> 01:09:44.552
<i>His thousand-year quest</i>
<i>for a vessel</i>

1069
01:09:44.585 --> 01:09:48.623
<i>which can resist the sun</i>
<i>will be no more.</i>

1070
01:09:48.656 --> 01:09:51.358
<i>and all of the progress</i>
<i>he's made</i>

1071
01:09:51.391 --> 01:09:54.294
<i>will be wound back</i>
<i>like a clock.</i>

1072
01:09:55.630 --> 01:09:59.801
<i>In the many years that we've</i>
<i>had to endure this nightmare.</i>

1073
01:09:59.834 --> 01:10:01.669
<i>Nezuko is the only demon</i>

1074
01:10:01.703 --> 01:10:04.872
<i>who has been able to live</i>
<i>in the sunlight.</i>

1075
01:10:20.487 --> 01:10:22.523
<i>"The final battle..."</i>

1076
01:10:22.557 --> 01:10:25.727
<i>these words echo in my mind.</i>

1077
01:10:29.197 --> 01:10:31.065
<i>And each time they do.</i>

1078
01:10:31.099 --> 01:10:34.468
<i>I can't help but tremble</i>
<i>as my heart beats louder.</i>

1079
01:10:35.703 --> 01:10:40.641
<i>This battle may finally reach</i>
<i>its conclusion tonight.</i>

1080
01:10:40.675 --> 01:10:45.646
<i>I never dreamed that I'd be</i>
<i>alive to witness it myself.</i>

1081
01:10:46.681 --> 01:10:50.518
<i>Tanjiro. I sometimes</i>
<i>think back to the day</i>

1082
01:10:50.551 --> 01:10:53.921
<i>when you brought</i>
<i>your demon sister to me.</i>

1083
01:10:53.955 --> 01:10:58.291
<i>Ever since then. it feels</i>
<i>like a giant wheel of fate</i>

1084
01:10:58.325 --> 01:11:00.895
<i>has been slowly turning.</i>

1085
01:11:00.928 --> 01:11:02.797
<i>Perhaps it would be best</i>

1086
01:11:02.830 --> 01:11:05.233
<i>to compare</i>
<i>the sum of our battles</i>

1087
01:11:05.265 --> 01:11:08.335
<i>to a giant. dormant machine.</i>

1088
01:11:08.368 --> 01:11:10.738
<i>You and Nezuko</i>
<i>are the small cogs</i>

1089
01:11:10.772 --> 01:11:15.109
<i>that have joined together and</i>
<i>awoken it from its slumber.</i>

1090
01:11:15.143 --> 01:11:17.444
<i>What was once</i>
<i>frozen in place...</i>

1091
01:11:17.477 --> 01:11:19.914
<i>has now been set into motion.</i>

1092
01:11:22.550 --> 01:11:25.887
Don't give up. Nezuko.

1093
01:11:27.320 --> 01:11:29.991
<i>Keep up the fight. Tanjiro!</i>

1094
01:11:31.025 --> 01:11:32.459
<i>You both</i>
<i>have to pull through.</i>

1095
01:11:32.492 --> 01:11:34.128
<i>no matter what!</i>

1096
01:11:34.162 --> 01:11:35.997
<i>- Hinokami Kagura...</i>

1097
01:11:36.030 --> 01:11:37.765
<i>Fire Wheel!</i>

1098
01:11:40.300 --> 01:11:41.569
<i>Go through!</i>

1099
01:11:41.602 --> 01:11:43.137
<i>If I can't even</i>
<i>sever his arm.</i>

1100
01:11:43.171 --> 01:11:44.806
<i>I'll never sever his head!</i>

1101
01:11:51.679 --> 01:11:52.580
<i>I got one!</i>

1102
01:11:52.613 --> 01:11:55.216
<i>I was able to dodge</i>
<i>his attack. too.</i>

1103
01:11:55.249 --> 01:11:56.951
<i>I can do this!</i>

1104
01:11:56.984 --> 01:11:58.853
<i>I couldn't aim for his head.</i>

1105
01:11:58.886 --> 01:12:00.453
<i>but this time. for sure!</i>

1106
01:12:01.421 --> 01:12:03.057
<i>Hinokami Kagura...</i>

1107
01:12:03.090 --> 01:12:04.091
<i>Fake Rainbow!</i>

1108
01:12:16.737 --> 01:12:18.573
- Huh?

1109
01:12:19.907 --> 01:12:21.042
<i>Tanjiro...</i>

1110
01:12:21.075 --> 01:12:24.312
<i>you've really sharpened</i>
<i>your skills. haven't you?</i>

1111
01:12:24.344 --> 01:12:26.614
<i>It wouldn't be</i>
<i>an exaggeration</i>

1112
01:12:26.647 --> 01:12:29.817
<i>to say he's at the level</i>
<i>of a Hashira now.</i>

1113
01:12:29.851 --> 01:12:34.822
<i>To think that he'd do this</i>
<i>well against Upper Three.</i>

1114
01:12:40.027 --> 01:12:42.096
<i>That day...</i>

1115
01:12:42.129 --> 01:12:45.365
<i>I remember a boy who felt</i>
<i>completely helpless</i>

1116
01:12:45.398 --> 01:12:48.336
<i>as he collapsed</i>
<i>onto the cold snow.</i>

1117
01:12:48.368 --> 01:12:50.872
<i>begging through tears</i>
<i>for his sister's life.</i>

1118
01:12:58.512 --> 01:13:01.115
<i>But you are helpless</i>
<i>no longer.</i>

1119
01:13:01.148 --> 01:13:04.585
<i>You have the strength to</i>
<i>fight not only for your life</i>

1120
01:13:04.619 --> 01:13:07.622
<i>but also</i>
<i>for what's precious to you.</i>

1121
01:13:08.923 --> 01:13:11.259
- "This boy is not weak.

1122
01:13:11.292 --> 01:13:13.460
Don't insult him."

1123
01:13:13.493 --> 01:13:17.698
I must admit that Kyojuro
was right when he said that.

1124
01:13:17.732 --> 01:13:20.935
You are certainly not weak.

1125
01:13:20.968 --> 01:13:23.604
In fact. I commend you.

1126
01:13:26.507 --> 01:13:28.843
Technique Development.

1127
01:13:32.780 --> 01:13:36.017
Now let's kick things off.
shall we?

1128
01:13:37.018 --> 01:13:38.986
It's time we had some fun.

1129
01:14:25.399 --> 01:14:27.234
<i>- Water Breathing...</i>

1130
01:14:27.268 --> 01:14:28.402
<i>Third Form...</i>

1131
01:14:28.436 --> 01:14:29.870
<i>Flowing Dance.</i>

1132
01:14:31.038 --> 01:14:32.974
- You're a Water Hashira!

1133
01:14:33.007 --> 01:14:34.742
How lucky for me!

1134
01:14:34.775 --> 01:14:37.712
It's been 50 years
since I fought one.

1135
01:14:45.519 --> 01:14:48.789
Destructive Death: Disorder!

1136
01:14:50.558 --> 01:14:53.594
Water Breathing
Eleventh Form...

1137
01:14:54.395 --> 01:14:55.329
Dead Calm.

1138
01:15:00.534 --> 01:15:03.270
- I've never seen
that move before.

1139
01:15:03.304 --> 01:15:05.740
Perhaps the last
Water Hashira I killed

1140
01:15:05.773 --> 01:15:08.275
never had a chance to use it!

1141
01:15:08.309 --> 01:15:09.977
<i>- Hinokami Kagura...</i>

1142
01:15:10.011 --> 01:15:11.545
<i>Raging Sun!</i>

1143
01:15:13.247 --> 01:15:14.849
<i>He vanished.</i>

1144
01:15:15.850 --> 01:15:16.751
<i>Behind me!</i>

1145
01:15:16.784 --> 01:15:18.853
<i>Fake Rai-- Kagura--</i>

1146
01:15:19.754 --> 01:15:22.923
<i>- Water Breathing</i>
<i>Second Form...</i>

1147
01:15:22.957 --> 01:15:24.792
<i>Water Wheel.</i>

1148
01:15:36.470 --> 01:15:38.072
<i>- Hinokami Kagura...</i>

1149
01:15:39.340 --> 01:15:40.641
<i>Flame Dance!</i>

1150
01:15:40.674 --> 01:15:43.077
<i>- Destructive Death:</i>
<i>Leg Type.</i>

1151
01:15:43.110 --> 01:15:45.179
<i>Crown Splitter!</i>

1152
01:15:45.212 --> 01:15:48.082
<i>- I blocked it with my sword!</i>

1153
01:15:52.353 --> 01:15:54.388
<i>His move barely grazed me.</i>

1154
01:15:54.422 --> 01:15:56.690
<i>and it still did</i>
<i>this kind of damage?</i>

1155
01:16:01.262 --> 01:16:02.830
How marvelous!

1156
01:16:04.432 --> 01:16:06.634
That elegant sword skill
you're using.

1157
01:16:06.667 --> 01:16:07.968
it's magnificent!

1158
01:16:08.002 --> 01:16:09.470
I must know now.

1159
01:16:09.503 --> 01:16:10.771
What is your name?

1160
01:16:10.805 --> 01:16:12.940
I want to remember you!

1161
01:16:14.909 --> 01:16:17.678
- I don't have a name
to give to a demon like you!

1162
01:16:17.711 --> 01:16:20.881
I hate talking.
so don't speak to me!

1163
01:16:21.682 --> 01:16:22.917
- Is that so?

1164
01:16:22.950 --> 01:16:25.719
You're not much
for small talk. are you?

1165
01:16:25.753 --> 01:16:28.189
Well. I happen
to quite enjoy it!

1166
01:16:28.222 --> 01:16:30.257
So I'll ask you again...

1167
01:16:30.291 --> 01:16:32.193
What is your name?

1168
01:16:38.432 --> 01:16:41.669
Destructive Death: Leg Type...

1169
01:16:41.702 --> 01:16:43.904
Explosive Fury!

1170
01:16:56.417 --> 01:16:58.119
- Mr. Giyu!

1171
01:16:59.954 --> 01:17:01.088
- I see.

1172
01:17:01.122 --> 01:17:02.223
That's his name.

1173
01:17:02.256 --> 01:17:04.158
Thank you for letting me know.

1174
01:17:07.628 --> 01:17:09.163
- Hinokami Kagura...

1175
01:17:09.196 --> 01:17:12.333
- Destructive Death:
Eight-layered Demon Core!

1176
01:17:12.366 --> 01:17:14.702
- ...Burning Bones.
Summer Sun!

1177
01:17:29.650 --> 01:17:31.285
- Excellent form.

1178
01:17:31.318 --> 01:17:35.322
To improve this much in such
a short time is impressive.

1179
01:17:35.356 --> 01:17:37.592
I'll give you my praise.

1180
01:17:37.626 --> 01:17:39.226
It seems obvious to me

1181
01:17:39.260 --> 01:17:42.196
that Kyojuro must have
really inspired you.

1182
01:17:42.229 --> 01:17:46.467
The night we met. you were
merely a weak. mournful child

1183
01:17:46.500 --> 01:17:48.369
crumpled on the ground.

1184
01:17:48.402 --> 01:17:50.804
not even worthy
of being killed.

1185
01:17:50.838 --> 01:17:52.873
But just look at you now!

1186
01:17:52.907 --> 01:17:54.909
This leap
in your abilities...

1187
01:17:54.942 --> 01:17:57.278
it's like you've been reborn!

1188
01:17:57.311 --> 01:17:59.313
My heart won't stop racing.

1189
01:17:59.346 --> 01:18:01.715
I'm truly overjoyed!

1190
01:18:04.185 --> 01:18:08.590
The night Kyojuro died.
I was glad that it happened.

1191
01:18:08.623 --> 01:18:10.090
- Huh?

1192
01:18:10.124 --> 01:18:12.026
- How tragic
would it have been

1193
01:18:12.059 --> 01:18:14.962
if he had never
gotten any stronger?

1194
01:18:14.995 --> 01:18:17.198
Such a stubborn man.
not letting go

1195
01:18:17.231 --> 01:18:20.401
of those worthless values
of staying human.

1196
01:18:21.670 --> 01:18:24.205
- How dare you.

1197
01:18:30.645 --> 01:18:31.613
Shut up.

1198
01:18:31.646 --> 01:18:33.447
Just shut up!

1199
01:18:37.552 --> 01:18:40.821
Don't you dare
even speak his name!

1200
01:18:40.854 --> 01:18:42.823
- What's the matter?

1201
01:18:42.856 --> 01:18:45.426
I'm only paying the man
a compliment.

1202
01:18:45.459 --> 01:18:46.994
I'm being sincere.

1203
01:18:47.027 --> 01:18:49.063
These are
high words of praise.

1204
01:18:49.096 --> 01:18:50.130
- You're wrong.

1205
01:18:50.164 --> 01:18:52.701
All you're doing
is insulting him.

1206
01:18:52.733 --> 01:18:56.837
You're just spitting
on his memory. on all of us!

1207
01:18:57.771 --> 01:19:00.542
- You couldn't
be more wrong. Tanjiro.

1208
01:19:00.575 --> 01:19:01.809
As you'll recall.

1209
01:19:01.842 --> 01:19:05.779
the only thing I despise
is weak human beings.

1210
01:19:05.813 --> 01:19:08.482
Only a feeble weakling
is deserving of my scorn

1211
01:19:08.516 --> 01:19:10.451
and no one else.

1212
01:19:10.484 --> 01:19:12.654
That's right.

1213
01:19:12.687 --> 01:19:15.856
The mere sight of them
makes my skin crawl.

1214
01:19:15.889 --> 01:19:18.058
They make me retch!

1215
01:19:18.092 --> 01:19:19.960
Through the laws of nature.

1216
01:19:19.994 --> 01:19:21.663
they are weeded out
from this world.

1217
01:19:21.696 --> 01:19:24.231
just as they should be!

1218
01:19:24.265 --> 01:19:28.302
- Everything you just said
is wrong!

1219
01:19:28.335 --> 01:19:30.170
- Huh?

1220
01:19:30.204 --> 01:19:32.906
- The fact you're
even alive right now.

1221
01:19:32.940 --> 01:19:35.276
isn't that proof enough?

1222
01:19:35.309 --> 01:19:39.079
As an infant.
we're all helpless.

1223
01:19:39.113 --> 01:19:42.049
We can't live
without someone else's help.

1224
01:19:42.082 --> 01:19:44.785
You're no different. Akaza.

1225
01:19:44.818 --> 01:19:47.121
Even if you don't remember.

1226
01:19:47.154 --> 01:19:49.056
there was a time
when you were protected

1227
01:19:49.089 --> 01:19:51.992
and cared for by someone.
I know it!

1228
01:19:52.026 --> 01:19:54.895
That's why you're alive.

1229
01:19:58.899 --> 01:20:02.303
The strong should aid
and protect the weak.

1230
01:20:02.336 --> 01:20:04.338
And in turn.
the weak become strong

1231
01:20:04.371 --> 01:20:07.709
and aid and protect those
weaker than themselves.

1232
01:20:07.742 --> 01:20:10.911
That is the law of nature!

1233
01:20:10.944 --> 01:20:15.015
Akaza. I can't tolerate
your way of thinking.

1234
01:20:15.049 --> 01:20:19.286
Here on out. I won't
let you do as you please!

1235
01:20:24.325 --> 01:20:26.160
<i>I get it now.</i>

1236
01:20:28.495 --> 01:20:30.331
<i>I have a disgust for this boy</i>

1237
01:20:30.364 --> 01:20:32.900
<i>that's almost</i>
<i>primal in nature.</i>

1238
01:20:33.702 --> 01:20:35.402
<i>Even if he's stronger.</i>

1239
01:20:35.436 --> 01:20:37.338
<i>that feeling hasn't faded.</i>

1240
01:20:42.042 --> 01:20:44.211
- No matter who they are.

1241
01:20:44.244 --> 01:20:47.348
everyone begins life
as a newborn.

1242
01:20:47.381 --> 01:20:51.586
We learn by getting help
from those around us.

1243
01:20:51.619 --> 01:20:54.188
We are not competing
with others.

1244
01:20:54.221 --> 01:20:58.526
The only opponent
you have in life is yourself.

1245
01:20:58.560 --> 01:21:00.662
Just focus
on becoming stronger

1246
01:21:00.695 --> 01:21:03.097
than you were yesterday.

1247
01:21:03.130 --> 01:21:07.535
If you can stay this path
for a decade or even two.

1248
01:21:07.569 --> 01:21:09.503
that would be commendable.

1249
01:21:09.537 --> 01:21:11.004
And before you know it.

1250
01:21:11.038 --> 01:21:13.641
you will be
helping others in turn.

1251
01:21:21.549 --> 01:21:22.883
<i>What was that?</i>

1252
01:21:22.916 --> 01:21:25.018
<i>He just swung his fist</i>
<i>at nothing.</i>

1253
01:21:30.958 --> 01:21:32.560
- Tanjiro...

1254
01:21:33.762 --> 01:21:36.397
you still repulse me
to my core.

1255
01:21:37.297 --> 01:21:39.734
<i>Destructive Death:</i>
<i>Crushing Type.</i>

1256
01:21:39.768 --> 01:21:42.503
<i>Ten Thousand Leaves</i>
<i>Flashing Willow!</i>

1257
01:21:45.640 --> 01:21:47.575
<i>- This speed. it's blinding!</i>

1258
01:21:47.609 --> 01:21:50.110
<i>No. it's not just his speed.</i>

1259
01:21:50.144 --> 01:21:53.548
<i>It's his precision.</i>
<i>his aura. and also...</i>

1260
01:21:57.918 --> 01:22:00.622
- Destructive Death:
Leg Type.

1261
01:22:00.655 --> 01:22:01.589
<i>- Below?</i>

1262
01:22:03.957 --> 01:22:06.193
- Flying Planet
Thousand Wheels!

1263
01:22:12.065 --> 01:22:14.435
<i>Even if I could</i>
<i>anticipate his strikes.</i>

1264
01:22:14.468 --> 01:22:17.739
<i>they're so powerful. I can't</i>
<i>completely deflect them.</i>

1265
01:22:17.772 --> 01:22:19.507
<i>His techniques</i>
<i>are so precise.</i>

1266
01:22:19.541 --> 01:22:22.677
<i>they can pierce through any</i>
<i>opening. no matter how small.</i>

1267
01:22:25.412 --> 01:22:28.282
<i>- It's like a magnet</i>
<i>is attracting his attacks</i>

1268
01:22:28.315 --> 01:22:30.618
<i>straight toward</i>
<i>my weak points!</i>

1269
01:22:30.652 --> 01:22:33.521
<i>But how? What's happening?</i>

1270
01:22:33.555 --> 01:22:36.524
<i>What could be causing</i>
<i>this behavior?</i>

1271
01:22:36.558 --> 01:22:38.526
<i>Come on. think.</i>

1272
01:22:39.894 --> 01:22:41.428
<i>What's the answer?</i>

1273
01:22:41.462 --> 01:22:44.965
<i>There must be a clue</i>
<i>in what Akaza's said or done.</i>

1274
01:22:47.836 --> 01:22:52.239
<i>- Hinokami Kagura:</i>
<i>Solar Heat Haze!</i>

1275
01:23:01.415 --> 01:23:03.751
What an interesting move.

1276
01:23:03.785 --> 01:23:07.755
I dodged it at first. but then
the blade seemed to extend.

1277
01:23:07.789 --> 01:23:10.658
I don't know what kind
of swing you put behind it.

1278
01:23:10.692 --> 01:23:11.793
but the tip of your blade

1279
01:23:11.826 --> 01:23:13.928
wavered like it
was in a heat haze.

1280
01:23:13.962 --> 01:23:15.295
How fascinating!

1281
01:23:26.240 --> 01:23:28.408
<i>- Hinokami Kagura...</i>

1282
01:23:28.442 --> 01:23:29.476
<i>Dance!</i>

1283
01:23:31.913 --> 01:23:33.113
<i>- My sword...</i>

1284
01:23:34.014 --> 01:23:35.517
<i>he'll break it!</i>

1285
01:23:40.053 --> 01:23:42.222
- That was a strong headbutt!

1286
01:23:43.825 --> 01:23:46.059
- Damn you! Let go of me!

1287
01:23:46.895 --> 01:23:48.462
<i>No good.</i>

1288
01:23:48.495 --> 01:23:51.164
<i>I can't get him</i>
<i>to loosen his grip!</i>

1289
01:24:03.076 --> 01:24:04.846
- Mr. Giyu!

1290
01:24:08.181 --> 01:24:11.051
You're starting
to get on my nerves.

1291
01:24:11.084 --> 01:24:14.254
Thanks to you.
my back is killing me now.

1292
01:24:14.288 --> 01:24:17.625
I'm not fond of being
hurled like a ragdoll.

1293
01:24:17.659 --> 01:24:19.459
I'm gonna make you pay.

1294
01:24:22.195 --> 01:24:23.463
<i>Personally...</i>

1295
01:24:23.497 --> 01:24:26.901
<i>I'd rather not draw</i>
<i>my sword if I can help it.</i>

1296
01:24:26.935 --> 01:24:28.168
<i>and I have a hard time</i>

1297
01:24:28.201 --> 01:24:31.673
<i>justifying using deadly force</i>
<i>if unnecessary.</i>

1298
01:24:31.706 --> 01:24:35.577
<i>But at this moment.</i>
<i>I'm against an opponent</i>

1299
01:24:35.610 --> 01:24:37.879
<i>that demands</i>
<i>everything from me.</i>

1300
01:24:37.912 --> 01:24:39.313
<i>In the short time</i>
<i>we've fought.</i>

1301
01:24:39.346 --> 01:24:42.282
<i>my senses have been</i>
<i>pushed past their limits.</i>

1302
01:24:42.316 --> 01:24:45.753
<i>My dormant senses</i>
<i>have been rudely awakened.</i>

1303
01:24:45.787 --> 01:24:49.857
<i>and are dragging me forward</i>
<i>towards the enemy.</i>

1304
01:24:49.891 --> 01:24:53.595
<i>I now know how much it</i>
<i>expands one's potential</i>

1305
01:24:53.628 --> 01:24:55.495
<i>to have one's back</i>
<i>against the wall</i>

1306
01:24:55.530 --> 01:24:59.399
<i>with their sword raised</i>
<i>in the face of death.</i>

1307
01:25:02.737 --> 01:25:03.838
Mr. Giyu.

1308
01:25:20.688 --> 01:25:23.758
<i>- A mark appeared. and</i>
<i>his movements have gotten...</i>

1309
01:25:23.791 --> 01:25:25.258
- Faster!

1310
01:25:29.597 --> 01:25:33.233
<i>- Water Breathing</i>
<i>Fourth Form: Striking Tide!</i>

1311
01:25:47.247 --> 01:25:49.216
<i>- They're both so fast!</i>

1312
01:25:49.249 --> 01:25:51.552
<i>Mr. Giyu's speed</i>
<i>increased with the mark.</i>

1313
01:25:51.586 --> 01:25:54.154
<i>but Akaza</i>
<i>adapted to it instantly!</i>

1314
01:25:56.524 --> 01:25:59.426
- Don't tell me
that's all you're capable of!

1315
01:26:08.268 --> 01:26:09.737
- Show me more!

1316
01:26:09.771 --> 01:26:11.939
Don't you dare hold back!

1317
01:26:40.902 --> 01:26:44.438
Tenth Form: Constant Flux.

1318
01:27:01.522 --> 01:27:05.059
- Seventh Form:
Drop Ripple Thrust!

1319
01:27:05.093 --> 01:27:07.461
- Destructive Death: Disorder.

1320
01:27:18.139 --> 01:27:21.008
- Mr. Giyu! Akaza.

1321
01:27:23.010 --> 01:27:25.278
<i>Calm down!</i>

1322
01:27:28.916 --> 01:27:30.785
<i>Think. Don't panic.</i>

1323
01:27:30.818 --> 01:27:33.955
<i>Whatever you do.</i>
<i>don't lose focus.</i>

1324
01:27:35.355 --> 01:27:37.058
<i>- Why is it</i>
<i>that Akaza's attacks</i>

1325
01:27:37.091 --> 01:27:38.726
<i>are always so accurate?</i>

1326
01:27:39.861 --> 01:27:41.294
<i>How is he able to respond</i>

1327
01:27:41.328 --> 01:27:43.263
<i>to attacks</i>
<i>from his blind spots?</i>

1328
01:27:44.699 --> 01:27:45.700
<i>Think!</i>

1329
01:27:50.238 --> 01:27:52.272
<i>- Your fighting spirit</i>
<i>has been tempered</i>

1330
01:27:52.305 --> 01:27:54.108
<i>like quality steel.</i>

1331
01:27:54.142 --> 01:27:55.408
<i>Your name?</i>

1332
01:27:58.179 --> 01:28:00.413
<i>Back when he</i>
<i>fought Mr. Rengoku.</i>

1333
01:28:00.447 --> 01:28:05.119
<i>I remember Akaza using</i>
<i>the words "fighting spirit."</i>

1334
01:28:05.153 --> 01:28:07.454
<i>What did he mean by that?</i>

1335
01:28:07.487 --> 01:28:10.390
<i>Is he able to sense things</i>
<i>through fighting spirit?</i>

1336
01:28:10.423 --> 01:28:13.828
<i>The same way I can</i>
<i>sense things through scent?</i>

1337
01:28:28.075 --> 01:28:29.510
- Wherever the enemy's
aiming at.

1338
01:28:29.544 --> 01:28:32.312
I get this weird
tingling feeling.

1339
01:28:32.345 --> 01:28:33.514
- So that's how you knew

1340
01:28:33.548 --> 01:28:35.650
Gyutaro was attacking you
from behind.

1341
01:28:35.683 --> 01:28:38.152
You sure are incredible.
Inosuke.

1342
01:28:39.687 --> 01:28:43.124
Well. my skin is tougher
than most people's.

1343
01:28:43.157 --> 01:28:44.959
And whether it's
from behind or not.

1344
01:28:44.992 --> 01:28:46.127
if someone's looking at me.

1345
01:28:46.160 --> 01:28:48.062
I know just
where they're looking.

1346
01:28:48.095 --> 01:28:49.297
- Could you show me?

1347
01:28:51.032 --> 01:28:52.033
Sure thing!

1348
01:28:56.938 --> 01:28:57.905
- It's my right shoulder.

1349
01:28:57.939 --> 01:29:00.141
- You really got it!
That's amazing!

1350
01:29:00.174 --> 01:29:03.311
- It's even easier to know
if someone's looking at me

1351
01:29:03.343 --> 01:29:04.879
if they have killing intent.

1352
01:29:04.912 --> 01:29:08.381
Since anyone
who could harm me is bad news.

1353
01:29:08.415 --> 01:29:10.318
killing intent
kinda feels like

1354
01:29:10.350 --> 01:29:12.553
it's stabbing me
through the skin. you know.

1355
01:29:12.587 --> 01:29:14.555
<i>That's right.</i>

1356
01:29:14.589 --> 01:29:17.457
<i>Inosuke was able</i>
<i>to sense the invisible</i>

1357
01:29:17.490 --> 01:29:20.261
<i>using only</i>
<i>his honed sense of touch.</i>

1358
01:29:20.294 --> 01:29:22.230
<i>Think back.</i>

1359
01:29:22.263 --> 01:29:24.265
<i>What else did we</i>
<i>talk about...</i>

1360
01:29:24.298 --> 01:29:26.234
<i>that day?</i>

1361
01:29:26.267 --> 01:29:27.935
- Where things get real tricky

1362
01:29:27.969 --> 01:29:30.338
is when someone who
doesn't have killing intent

1363
01:29:30.370 --> 01:29:32.640
or hostility
is looking at me.

1364
01:29:32.673 --> 01:29:34.842
- Like that tiny hag!
- Huh?

1365
01:29:34.876 --> 01:29:36.409
- That old hag

1366
01:29:36.443 --> 01:29:39.947
from the house with
the wisteria mark was sneaky.

1367
01:29:39.981 --> 01:29:41.616
Before I knew it...

1368
01:29:41.649 --> 01:29:42.650
Huh?

1369
01:29:43.584 --> 01:29:45.720
...she'd be sitting
right behind me.

1370
01:29:45.753 --> 01:29:47.221
- holding rice balls!
- Whoa!

1371
01:29:48.256 --> 01:29:50.258
- Calling her a hag
isn't nice.

1372
01:29:50.291 --> 01:29:51.259
She's elderly!

1373
01:29:51.292 --> 01:29:52.260
- Elderly hag!

1374
01:29:52.293 --> 01:29:53.426
- Stop that!

1375
01:29:53.460 --> 01:29:55.263
- Well. that got me thinking.

1376
01:29:55.296 --> 01:29:58.866
If I could hide my killing
intent. then I'd be a ninja!

1377
01:29:58.900 --> 01:30:01.636
I'd be able
to sneak up on anybody!

1378
01:30:02.402 --> 01:30:03.537
- Sure.

1379
01:30:03.571 --> 01:30:06.107
But. Inosuke.
she was only sneaky

1380
01:30:06.140 --> 01:30:09.076
'cause she didn't have
the intent of harming you.

1381
01:30:09.110 --> 01:30:10.443
And I think beheading a demon

1382
01:30:10.477 --> 01:30:13.714
without killing intent
would be impossible.

1383
01:30:13.748 --> 01:30:15.116
- Hmm.

1384
01:30:15.149 --> 01:30:17.718
Yeah. you're probably right.

1385
01:30:17.752 --> 01:30:20.621
A halfhearted strike
without any killing intent

1386
01:30:20.655 --> 01:30:24.125
would never be strong enough
to cut through a demon's neck.

1387
01:30:25.192 --> 01:30:27.395
<i>- It was</i>
<i>a casual conversation.</i>

1388
01:30:27.427 --> 01:30:30.631
<i>but I think Inosuke</i>
<i>was onto something.</i>

1389
01:30:31.899 --> 01:30:35.336
<i>- What is it that Akaza</i>
<i>supposedly senses?</i>

1390
01:30:35.369 --> 01:30:37.939
<i>What does he mean</i>
<i>by "fighting spirit"?</i>

1391
01:30:37.972 --> 01:30:39.307
<i>Is it killing intent?</i>

1392
01:30:39.340 --> 01:30:40.775
<i>Is it the will to fight.</i>

1393
01:30:40.808 --> 01:30:44.545
<i>the time spent training.</i>
<i>or maybe the amount?</i>

1394
01:30:44.578 --> 01:30:45.947
<i>Is it like the way</i>

1395
01:30:45.980 --> 01:30:48.516
<i>I can anticipate</i>
<i>movements through scent?</i>

1396
01:30:49.550 --> 01:30:51.686
<i>There must be</i>
<i>something I can do...</i>

1397
01:30:51.719 --> 01:30:54.088
<i>to disrupt his compass!</i>

1398
01:31:04.198 --> 01:31:06.600
Hinokami Kagura: Dance!

1399
01:31:08.536 --> 01:31:11.539
- Just one problem
with your attack.

1400
01:31:11.572 --> 01:31:13.708
You're wide open!

1401
01:31:16.077 --> 01:31:17.178
<i>- His fist!</i>

1402
01:31:30.558 --> 01:31:34.362
<i>Fighting spirit.</i>
<i>instincts. compass.</i>

1403
01:31:34.395 --> 01:31:36.130
<i>perception...</i>

1404
01:31:36.163 --> 01:31:37.932
<i>striking with killing intent.</i>

1405
01:31:37.965 --> 01:31:41.969
<i>sensing the invisible.</i>
<i>executing the impossible.</i>

1406
01:31:42.003 --> 01:31:43.771
<i>I see.</i>

1407
01:31:45.573 --> 01:31:47.108
<i>So that's it.</i>

1408
01:31:59.220 --> 01:32:01.055
- Hey!

1409
01:32:02.957 --> 01:32:04.325
- Again! Again!

1410
01:32:04.358 --> 01:32:06.460
- Um. Father.
what do you think about

1411
01:32:06.494 --> 01:32:09.563
when you dance
the Hinokami Kagura?

1412
01:32:09.597 --> 01:32:11.432
If it's too tiring for you.

1413
01:32:11.465 --> 01:32:13.567
I can take your place
next year.

1414
01:32:13.601 --> 01:32:17.338
I don't want you
to overwork yourself.

1415
01:32:17.371 --> 01:32:20.107
- Thank you. Tanjiro.

1416
01:32:20.141 --> 01:32:22.777
But to be honest.
I haven't found the Kagura

1417
01:32:22.810 --> 01:32:26.347
to be the least bit tiring
over the last few years.

1418
01:32:26.380 --> 01:32:28.816
I can't quite explain it.

1419
01:32:28.849 --> 01:32:29.950
but back when I learned it

1420
01:32:29.984 --> 01:32:32.353
from your grandfather
years ago.

1421
01:32:32.386 --> 01:32:33.954
even though I was younger.

1422
01:32:33.988 --> 01:32:36.157
healthier.
and stronger than now.

1423
01:32:36.190 --> 01:32:39.460
I found it to be
far more tiring back then.

1424
01:32:43.064 --> 01:32:45.800
<i>For generations.</i>
<i>the Kagura was performed</i>

1425
01:32:45.833 --> 01:32:48.836
<i>by the Kamado family</i>
<i>at the start of each year.</i>

1426
01:32:48.869 --> 01:32:51.005
<i>It was an exhausting</i>
<i>performance</i>

1427
01:32:51.038 --> 01:32:53.974
<i>that would last</i>
<i>from sunset 'til dawn.</i>

1428
01:32:55.342 --> 01:32:56.777
<i>There are 12 different forms</i>

1429
01:32:56.811 --> 01:32:59.548
<i>that must be repeated</i>
<i>over and over again</i>

1430
01:32:59.580 --> 01:33:02.383
<i>thousands of times</i>
<i>before daybreak.</i>

1431
01:33:05.386 --> 01:33:06.687
- I think my exhaustion

1432
01:33:06.720 --> 01:33:09.590
was the result
of unnecessary movement.

1433
01:33:09.623 --> 01:33:12.493
Using the correct movements
and breathing patterns

1434
01:33:12.527 --> 01:33:14.061
are vital to the dance.

1435
01:33:14.095 --> 01:33:17.698
It's what allows you
to produce maximum strength

1436
01:33:17.731 --> 01:33:19.667
while using minimal actions.

1437
01:33:19.700 --> 01:33:22.636
Once you've mastered
your breathing and movement.

1438
01:33:22.670 --> 01:33:26.173
your mind
will become transparent.

1439
01:33:26.207 --> 01:33:28.776
- Transparent?

1440
01:33:28.809 --> 01:33:30.678
- But before any of that.

1441
01:33:30.711 --> 01:33:32.813
you must memorize
the moves of the dance

1442
01:33:32.847 --> 01:33:36.183
and slowly ingrain them
into your muscle memory.

1443
01:33:36.217 --> 01:33:39.753
In doing so. you'll open up
your five senses

1444
01:33:39.787 --> 01:33:42.356
and become aware of the shape
of your own body.

1445
01:33:42.389 --> 01:33:44.191
vessel by vessel.

1446
01:33:45.793 --> 01:33:48.929
That was
the truly strenuous part.

1447
01:33:48.963 --> 01:33:50.231
All you can think is that.

1448
01:33:50.264 --> 01:33:53.968
even if you go on struggling.
you'll never succeed.

1449
01:33:54.001 --> 01:33:56.403
After you've learned
all these things

1450
01:33:56.437 --> 01:33:57.838
and committed them to memory.

1451
01:33:57.872 --> 01:34:01.108
you'll understand how to
remove what you don't need.

1452
01:34:01.142 --> 01:34:05.279
only leaving behind in your
body what is required of you.

1453
01:34:05.312 --> 01:34:07.681
closing off the rest.

1454
01:34:07.715 --> 01:34:09.850
- Closing?

1455
01:34:09.884 --> 01:34:12.019
- You know how people
often close their eyes

1456
01:34:12.052 --> 01:34:14.688
when they're trying
to hear better?

1457
01:34:14.722 --> 01:34:16.323
In that same way.

1458
01:34:16.357 --> 01:34:19.426
you'll pick out the things you
need the most in the movement

1459
01:34:19.460 --> 01:34:21.929
while eliminating the rest.

1460
01:34:21.962 --> 01:34:24.965
Eventually. you'll be
able to open and close

1461
01:34:24.999 --> 01:34:27.368
the vessels and
muscles in your body.

1462
01:34:27.401 --> 01:34:29.069
as if it were second nature.

1463
01:34:29.103 --> 01:34:33.107
the same way you blink
without a second thought.

1464
01:34:33.140 --> 01:34:34.708
When that happens.

1465
01:34:34.742 --> 01:34:39.514
a path illuminated
by a bright light will open.

1466
01:34:39.548 --> 01:34:42.249
If your mind is
as clear as possible.

1467
01:34:42.283 --> 01:34:45.920
you'll begin to see the
Transparent World before you.

1468
01:34:45.953 --> 01:34:48.122
But this domain
can only be reached

1469
01:34:48.155 --> 01:34:50.224
by pushing yourself
past your limits.

1470
01:34:50.257 --> 01:34:52.927
despite the suffering
that may be required.

1471
01:34:52.960 --> 01:34:55.530
- Will I ever get to see it?

1472
01:34:55.564 --> 01:35:00.434
- If you work tirelessly.
then that's for you to decide.

1473
01:35:00.467 --> 01:35:01.468
There.

1474
01:35:01.502 --> 01:35:02.503
All done.

1475
01:35:02.537 --> 01:35:03.904
- Thank you.

1476
01:35:07.274 --> 01:35:10.277
<i>Ten days</i>
<i>before my father died.</i>

1477
01:35:10.311 --> 01:35:12.813
<i>an incident where a bear</i>
<i>began attacking people</i>

1478
01:35:12.846 --> 01:35:15.650
<i>happened</i>
<i>on a neighboring mountain.</i>

1479
01:35:15.684 --> 01:35:18.018
<i>We lit bonfires</i>
<i>around the house</i>

1480
01:35:18.052 --> 01:35:21.222
<i>and set up multiple ropes</i>
<i>lined with bells.</i>

1481
01:35:33.000 --> 01:35:34.001
- Hmm?

1482
01:35:40.007 --> 01:35:41.509
Tanjiro?

1483
01:35:45.614 --> 01:35:48.349
Yes. Father?

1484
01:35:48.382 --> 01:35:50.585
- Come with me.

1485
01:36:38.132 --> 01:36:41.001
- I understand
you must be very hungry.

1486
01:36:41.035 --> 01:36:46.273
but I'm afraid I can't
allow you to come any closer.

1487
01:36:46.307 --> 01:36:49.310
If anyone were to try
and cause harm to my family.

1488
01:36:49.343 --> 01:36:52.514
I would be forced
to show you no mercy.

1489
01:36:52.547 --> 01:36:55.015
If you disregard
this warning...

1490
01:36:57.251 --> 01:37:00.921
I'll have no choice
but to take your life.

1491
01:37:12.066 --> 01:37:15.903
<i>- The bear's head. that was</i>
<i>as thick as a human torso.</i>

1492
01:37:15.936 --> 01:37:19.440
<i>dropped to the ground</i>
<i>with the sound of the bells.</i>

1493
01:37:20.841 --> 01:37:23.043
<i>My eyes couldn't follow it.</i>

1494
01:37:23.077 --> 01:37:24.912
<i>but If I'm not mistaken.</i>

1495
01:37:24.945 --> 01:37:28.282
<i>my father slashed it twice</i>
<i>in the blink of an eye.</i>

1496
01:37:29.883 --> 01:37:31.251
<i>He must have.</i>

1497
01:37:31.285 --> 01:37:32.821
<i>His ax wouldn't</i>
<i>have been able</i>

1498
01:37:32.853 --> 01:37:35.255
<i>to cut through otherwise.</i>

1499
01:37:35.289 --> 01:37:39.460
<i>All the while. my father's</i>
<i>scent never wavered.</i>

1500
01:37:39.493 --> 01:37:42.129
<i>Before and after</i>
<i>beheading the bear.</i>

1501
01:37:42.162 --> 01:37:46.266
<i>he emitted no fear.</i>
<i>no killing intent.</i>

1502
01:37:52.306 --> 01:37:55.577
- I hope that you
were watching.

1503
01:37:55.610 --> 01:37:58.780
A day might come where you
have to do the same.

1504
01:38:01.281 --> 01:38:03.785
<i>- My father wasn't</i>
<i>the type of person</i>

1505
01:38:03.818 --> 01:38:06.053
<i>to flaunt his strength.</i>

1506
01:38:06.086 --> 01:38:08.255
<i>I realized later on.</i>

1507
01:38:08.288 --> 01:38:13.394
<i>that night. he wanted me</i>
<i>to see it in action.</i>

1508
01:38:13.427 --> 01:38:16.096
<i>the movements necessary</i>
<i>to be able to see</i>

1509
01:38:16.130 --> 01:38:19.032
<i>the Transparent World</i>
<i>he spoke of.</i>

1510
01:38:21.001 --> 01:38:23.470
<i>I'm sure my father.</i>
<i>grandfather.</i>

1511
01:38:23.504 --> 01:38:28.075
<i>and great-grandfather</i>
<i>all learned the same way.</i>

1512
01:38:29.744 --> 01:38:32.079
- Whatever you do.
never give up.

1513
01:38:32.112 --> 01:38:34.816
Always stay calm and focused.

1514
01:38:34.849 --> 01:38:38.218
Any wall you come up against
can be shattered

1515
01:38:38.252 --> 01:38:40.954
if you just work tirelessly.

1516
01:38:41.856 --> 01:38:44.158
- I understand. Father.

1517
01:38:44.191 --> 01:38:47.361
<i>In that moment.</i>
<i>that's why I was able</i>

1518
01:38:47.394 --> 01:38:51.064
<i>to dodge Akaza's</i>
<i>inescapable blow to my side.</i>

1519
01:38:53.635 --> 01:38:55.269
<i>If I hadn't moved in time.</i>

1520
01:38:55.302 --> 01:38:58.505
<i>I'm positive that strike</i>
<i>would have killed me.</i>

1521
01:38:58.540 --> 01:39:01.275
<i>When I was alternating moves</i>
<i>with Mr. Giyu.</i>

1522
01:39:01.308 --> 01:39:03.678
<i>weaving my attacks</i>
<i>in between each of his...</i>

1523
01:39:03.711 --> 01:39:07.782
<i>I was protected from being</i>
<i>hit by those lethal blows.</i>

1524
01:39:07.816 --> 01:39:09.450
<i>But in that instant.</i>

1525
01:39:09.483 --> 01:39:12.887
<i>even Mr. Giyu</i>
<i>couldn't make it in time.</i>

1526
01:39:12.921 --> 01:39:15.989
<i>However. for whatever reason.</i>

1527
01:39:16.023 --> 01:39:18.893
<i>I knew dodging</i> was <i>possible.</i>

1528
01:39:18.927 --> 01:39:21.696
<i>and for just a split-second.</i>

1529
01:39:21.729 --> 01:39:24.364
<i>I was able to see it...</i>

1530
01:39:24.398 --> 01:39:26.967
<i>that world...</i>

1531
01:39:30.705 --> 01:39:33.006
<i>- ...the Transparent World.</i>

1532
01:39:35.442 --> 01:39:39.747
<i>Even his body</i>
<i>started to look transparent.</i>

1533
01:39:39.781 --> 01:39:44.151
<i>The same as when Hantengu was</i>
<i>hiding inside his own heart.</i>

1534
01:39:44.184 --> 01:39:47.321
<i>I don't know if I saw him</i>
<i>or smelled him.</i>

1535
01:39:51.358 --> 01:39:53.026
<i>Dodge.</i>

1536
01:39:53.060 --> 01:39:56.531
<i>I used only the senses</i>
<i>that would let me do that.</i>

1537
01:39:56.564 --> 01:39:57.899
<i>Without thinking.</i>

1538
01:39:57.932 --> 01:40:01.536
<i>my body moved faster</i>
<i>than ever before.</i>

1539
01:40:01.569 --> 01:40:02.904
<i>When I'm inside</i>

1540
01:40:02.937 --> 01:40:05.540
<i>the Transparent World</i>
<i>my father spoke of.</i>

1541
01:40:05.573 --> 01:40:08.710
<i>my battle instincts</i>
<i>improve drastically.</i>

1542
01:40:10.778 --> 01:40:13.080
<i>I can see</i>
<i>my opponent's lungs</i>

1543
01:40:13.113 --> 01:40:15.917
<i>and the blood moving</i>
<i>throughout their body.</i>

1544
01:40:15.950 --> 01:40:18.385
<i>I can see</i>
<i>my own muscles contracting</i>

1545
01:40:18.418 --> 01:40:21.288
<i>Faster and</i>
<i>clearer than before.</i>

1546
01:40:24.926 --> 01:40:26.961
<i>If I close off</i>
<i>the fighting spirit</i>

1547
01:40:26.995 --> 01:40:29.329
<i>that Akaza must be</i>
<i>detecting me with.</i>

1548
01:40:29.363 --> 01:40:31.900
<i>I can go for his neck.</i>

1549
01:40:44.546 --> 01:40:47.615
<i>See it. See it.</i>

1550
01:40:50.350 --> 01:40:52.085
- It looks like you've thrown

1551
01:40:52.119 --> 01:40:54.388
about every last
Water Form at me.

1552
01:40:54.421 --> 01:40:58.191
Enough is enough.
wouldn't you say?

1553
01:40:58.225 --> 01:41:00.028
I'm putting an end to this.

1554
01:41:00.060 --> 01:41:03.196
but you have my respect
for lasting so long!

1555
01:41:03.998 --> 01:41:06.366
<i>- What?</i>

1556
01:41:06.400 --> 01:41:08.836
<i>In the middle</i>
<i>of my downswing...</i>

1557
01:41:10.203 --> 01:41:12.439
<i>he hit it from the side...</i>

1558
01:41:13.340 --> 01:41:16.109
<i>and snapped my sword!</i>

1559
01:41:16.143 --> 01:41:17.612
- Goodbye. Giyu.

1560
01:41:47.675 --> 01:41:51.211
<i>- He stopped the attack</i>
<i>by cutting off his fist.</i>

1561
01:41:51.244 --> 01:41:53.180
<i>His breathing is different</i>

1562
01:41:53.213 --> 01:41:54.849
<i>and his appearance.</i>

1563
01:41:55.917 --> 01:41:58.485
<i>I've been saved by Tanjiro.</i>

1564
01:41:59.887 --> 01:42:01.789
<i>- All of the cells</i>
<i>in my body.</i>

1565
01:42:01.823 --> 01:42:03.390
<i>down to the ones in my hair.</i>

1566
01:42:03.423 --> 01:42:08.261
<i>are screaming at me to kill</i>
<i>him as soon as possible.</i>

1567
01:42:08.295 --> 01:42:11.633
<i>I don't know what kind of</i>
<i>change he underwent. but...</i>

1568
01:42:12.800 --> 01:42:14.535
<i>he's dangerous.</i>

1569
01:42:16.004 --> 01:42:17.872
<i>- His focus is on Tanjiro.</i>

1570
01:42:19.206 --> 01:42:20.875
<i>Now's my chance.</i>

1571
01:42:25.278 --> 01:42:27.982
<i>Technique Development:</i>
<i>Final Form.</i>

1572
01:42:28.016 --> 01:42:31.184
<i>Blue Silver</i>
<i>Chaotic Afterglow!</i>

1573
01:42:34.154 --> 01:42:36.490
<i>- His attack speed</i>
<i>boosted again!</i>

1574
01:42:36.524 --> 01:42:38.926
<i>And the force has increased!</i>

1575
01:42:38.960 --> 01:42:40.695
<i>My only chance now...</i>

1576
01:42:40.728 --> 01:42:42.864
<i>is with Dead Calm.</i>

1577
01:43:04.384 --> 01:43:07.522
<i>- This must be what Father</i>
<i>was talking about.</i>

1578
01:43:07.555 --> 01:43:11.458
<i>This is it.</i>
<i>the Transparent World.</i>

1579
01:43:19.567 --> 01:43:21.268
<i>Strange.</i>

1580
01:43:21.301 --> 01:43:23.037
<i>It feels like...</i>

1581
01:43:23.071 --> 01:43:25.707
<i>time is passing by so slowly.</i>

1582
01:43:27.407 --> 01:43:31.746
<i>Or maybe their movements</i>
<i>just</i> look <i>slower now.</i>

1583
01:43:37.451 --> 01:43:39.887
<i>It's no use.</i>

1584
01:43:39.921 --> 01:43:43.124
<i>A hundred strikes at once</i>
<i>is unavoidable.</i>

1585
01:43:43.157 --> 01:43:44.792
<i>Even with Dead Calm.</i>

1586
01:43:44.826 --> 01:43:48.228
<i>I still wasn't able</i>
<i>to block all of 'em.</i>

1587
01:43:49.496 --> 01:43:51.199
- Stand proud. Giyu.

1588
01:43:51.231 --> 01:43:54.135
Most wouldn't have
been able to survive that.

1589
01:43:54.168 --> 01:43:56.971
You must have evaded
my fatal blows.

1590
01:43:57.972 --> 01:43:59.507
There's no need for you to die

1591
01:43:59.540 --> 01:44:01.909
like Kyojuro and Tanjiro did.

1592
01:44:01.943 --> 01:44:05.546
Give up your pride
and become a demon. Giyu.

1593
01:44:06.514 --> 01:44:08.415
<i>Tanjiro's behind him...</i>

1594
01:44:08.448 --> 01:44:10.618
<i>and he hasn't noticed?</i>

1595
01:44:10.651 --> 01:44:13.320
- Even you can't deny...
<i>- Is he masking his presence?</i>

1596
01:44:13.353 --> 01:44:14.421
<i>Now's our chance.</i>

1597
01:44:14.454 --> 01:44:15.823
- ...to the death.

1598
01:44:15.857 --> 01:44:17.491
<i>- Tanjiro. do it!</i>

1599
01:44:17.525 --> 01:44:20.360
<i>If you have the strength.</i>
<i>behead him!</i>

1600
01:44:20.393 --> 01:44:22.295
<i>Before he notices you!</i>

1601
01:44:22.329 --> 01:44:23.965
<i>Go for it!</i>

1602
01:44:23.998 --> 01:44:25.298
- Akaza!

1603
01:44:25.332 --> 01:44:27.869
Prepare to be decapitated!

1604
01:44:27.902 --> 01:44:28.770
- Huh?

1605
01:44:33.574 --> 01:44:36.844
<i>- He willingly</i>
<i>gave himself away!</i>

1606
01:44:36.878 --> 01:44:38.880
<i>- He's still alive?</i>

1607
01:44:38.913 --> 01:44:40.782
<i>I never would have</i>
<i>thought someone like him</i>

1608
01:44:40.815 --> 01:44:43.217
<i>could survive</i>
<i>an attack like that.</i>

1609
01:44:43.251 --> 01:44:46.220
<i>Well. it doesn't matter.</i>
<i>After all.</i>

1610
01:44:46.254 --> 01:44:47.955
<i>my Destructive Death:</i>
<i>Compass Needle</i>

1611
01:44:47.989 --> 01:44:49.924
<i>can detect any attack.</i>

1612
01:44:49.957 --> 01:44:53.227
<i>The stronger my opponent's</i>
<i>fighting spirit is.</i>

1613
01:44:53.261 --> 01:44:56.197
<i>the greater</i>
<i>my Compass Needle's reaction.</i>

1614
01:44:59.033 --> 01:45:01.602
<i>Wh-What is this?</i>

1615
01:45:01.636 --> 01:45:04.371
<i>What is this odd presence</i>
<i>he's emitting?</i>

1616
01:45:04.404 --> 01:45:06.240
<i>It feels like</i>
<i>he's turned himself</i>

1617
01:45:06.274 --> 01:45:09.544
<i>into some other creature.</i>
<i>It's like...</i>

1618
01:45:11.112 --> 01:45:13.714
<i>His fighting spirit is gone.</i>

1619
01:45:13.748 --> 01:45:14.481
<i>But how?</i>

1620
01:45:14.515 --> 01:45:18.085
<i>I have to calm down. Focus!</i>

1621
01:45:24.025 --> 01:45:26.194
<i>- Hinokami Kagura</i>

1622
01:45:26.227 --> 01:45:28.796
<i>Setting Sun Transformation.</i>

1623
01:45:50.184 --> 01:45:52.820
<i>- This can't be possible.</i>

1624
01:45:59.193 --> 01:46:01.896
<i>- In the last</i>
<i>several hundred years.</i>

1625
01:46:01.929 --> 01:46:05.967
<i>I've never once seen a human</i>
<i>without any fighting spirit.</i>

1626
01:46:06.000 --> 01:46:09.604
<i>Even newborn children</i>
<i>had traces of it.</i>

1627
01:46:09.637 --> 01:46:14.008
<i>And yet. in that instant.</i>
<i>his fighting spirit vanished</i>

1628
01:46:14.041 --> 01:46:16.677
<i>as if it were never there</i>
<i>to begin with.</i>

1629
01:46:20.214 --> 01:46:21.549
<i>It's as if I was facing</i>

1630
01:46:21.582 --> 01:46:23.885
<i>an anomaly</i>
<i>that shouldn't even exist.</i>

1631
01:46:23.918 --> 01:46:27.355
<i>so my senses were thrown</i>
<i>into confusion.</i>

1632
01:46:27.387 --> 01:46:30.958
<i>My Compass Needle</i>
<i>detected nothing.</i>

1633
01:46:32.093 --> 01:46:35.596
<i>But that's not the biggest</i>
<i>issue at hand here.</i>

1634
01:46:35.630 --> 01:46:37.397
<i>When on the battlefield.</i>

1635
01:46:37.430 --> 01:46:39.867
<i>there's no telling</i>
<i>what could come your way.</i>

1636
01:46:39.901 --> 01:46:42.502
<i>It's vital that you're able</i>
<i>to deal with the unexpected</i>

1637
01:46:42.536 --> 01:46:44.605
<i>at a moment's notice.</i>

1638
01:46:44.639 --> 01:46:46.741
<i>And I'm able to do that!</i>

1639
01:46:47.642 --> 01:46:50.544
<i>Or at least. I thought so.</i>

1640
01:46:51.411 --> 01:46:54.215
<i>But during that short battle.</i>

1641
01:46:54.248 --> 01:46:56.150
<i>he was able</i>
<i>to grasp something</i>

1642
01:46:56.183 --> 01:46:59.320
<i>and use it surpass my speed.</i>

1643
01:46:59.353 --> 01:47:00.487
<i>Whatever it was he learned</i>

1644
01:47:00.521 --> 01:47:02.056
<i>was able to shatter</i>
<i>centuries worth</i>

1645
01:47:02.089 --> 01:47:05.993
<i>of martial arts techniques</i>
<i>with a single head-on attack.</i>

1646
01:47:06.794 --> 01:47:08.396
<i>Within those eyes of his.</i>

1647
01:47:08.428 --> 01:47:10.731
<i>there was no hatred.</i>
<i>no rage.</i>

1648
01:47:10.765 --> 01:47:14.568
<i>no killing intent.</i>
<i>or fighting spirit.</i>

1649
01:47:14.602 --> 01:47:17.538
<i>He must have somehow seen</i>
<i>what I've been looking for.</i>

1650
01:47:17.571 --> 01:47:19.807
<i>the domain that lies within.</i>

1651
01:47:19.840 --> 01:47:21.842
<i>the realm of the highest...</i>

1652
01:47:23.611 --> 01:47:26.180
<i>none other</i>
<i>than the selfless state.</i>

1653
01:47:28.448 --> 01:47:30.618
<i>For some time now.</i>
<i>I've had a vague sense</i>

1654
01:47:30.651 --> 01:47:33.554
<i>that this state</i>
<i>of mind existed.</i>

1655
01:47:33.587 --> 01:47:36.123
<i>and yet. even after</i>
<i>all these centuries.</i>

1656
01:47:36.157 --> 01:47:37.959
<i>I've yet to attain it.</i>

1657
01:47:47.168 --> 01:47:48.903
<i>- Not yet!</i>

1658
01:47:48.936 --> 01:47:50.604
<i>I can still fight!</i>

1659
01:47:50.638 --> 01:47:53.541
<i>I will continue</i>
<i>to become stronger!</i>

1660
01:47:59.447 --> 01:48:03.017
<i>- This is bad.</i>
<i>He's reattaching his head!</i>

1661
01:48:11.592 --> 01:48:13.894
<i>I can't die here.</i>

1662
01:48:15.463 --> 01:48:17.164
<i>Not like this!</i>

1663
01:48:20.134 --> 01:48:23.004
<i>I have to become stronger.</i>

1664
01:48:24.972 --> 01:48:28.409
<i>Stronger than anyone else</i>
<i>in the whole world!</i>

1665
01:48:28.442 --> 01:48:30.811
<i>Stronger!</i>

1666
01:48:32.513 --> 01:48:35.850
<i>I have to find a way</i>
<i>to become stronger.</i>

1667
01:48:45.192 --> 01:48:46.394
<i>That's it.</i>

1668
01:48:46.427 --> 01:48:48.029
<i>It's over.</i>

1669
01:48:49.897 --> 01:48:51.098
<i>We won!</i>

1670
01:48:55.603 --> 01:48:58.005
So lightheaded.

1671
01:48:59.607 --> 01:49:01.675
<i>My muscles are cramping up.</i>

1672
01:49:01.709 --> 01:49:04.145
<i>My body's reached its limit.</i>

1673
01:49:06.714 --> 01:49:08.249
- Tanjiro! Are you all ri--

1674
01:49:09.383 --> 01:49:12.853
<i>His body hasn't</i>
<i>disintegrated yet.</i>

1675
01:49:12.887 --> 01:49:16.123
<i>Does-- Does this mean...</i>

1676
01:49:16.157 --> 01:49:17.224
Tan--

1677
01:49:28.069 --> 01:49:31.072
<i>- He's moving.</i>
<i>His body is still intact!</i>

1678
01:49:31.105 --> 01:49:33.641
<i>The severed part</i>
<i>is closing up!</i>

1679
01:49:36.644 --> 01:49:38.746
<i>I can't see straight.</i>

1680
01:49:51.225 --> 01:49:53.928
<i>No-- No way!</i>

1681
01:49:53.961 --> 01:49:56.397
<i>Slashing his neck</i>
<i>didn't kill him!</i>

1682
01:49:56.430 --> 01:49:58.199
<i>Is there some kind</i>
<i>of condition.</i>

1683
01:49:58.232 --> 01:50:00.401
<i>like with Gyutaro and Daki?</i>

1684
01:50:00.434 --> 01:50:01.402
<i>That can't be it.</i>

1685
01:50:01.435 --> 01:50:03.704
<i>His head disintegrated.</i>

1686
01:50:03.737 --> 01:50:05.806
<i>yet he hasn't given up!</i>

1687
01:50:05.840 --> 01:50:09.143
<i>Its like</i>
<i>he's trying to evolve!</i>

1688
01:50:15.449 --> 01:50:16.817
<i>- If we don't do something.</i>

1689
01:50:16.851 --> 01:50:19.653
<i>his head will stop being</i>
<i>his weak point. like Muzan!</i>

1690
01:50:20.555 --> 01:50:22.490
This battle isn't over yet.

1691
01:50:22.524 --> 01:50:23.991
I have to...

1692
01:50:24.024 --> 01:50:25.326
fight.

1693
01:50:25.359 --> 01:50:26.460
- Tanjiro!

1694
01:50:26.494 --> 01:50:28.229
He's fainted.

1695
01:50:28.262 --> 01:50:29.663
Of course he has!

1696
01:50:29.697 --> 01:50:32.266
He's long since
passed his limit.

1697
01:50:41.842 --> 01:50:43.344
<i>Water Breathing...</i>

1698
01:50:43.377 --> 01:50:45.246
Fourth Form...

1699
01:50:47.616 --> 01:50:49.316
Striking Tide!

1700
01:50:54.121 --> 01:50:55.723
<i>Ridiculous!</i>

1701
01:50:55.756 --> 01:50:56.891
<i>He lost his head</i>

1702
01:50:56.924 --> 01:50:59.760
<i>and can still</i>
<i>regenerate that quickly?!</i>

1703
01:51:23.450 --> 01:51:25.686
<i>I can't hear</i>
<i>out of my left ear.</i>

1704
01:51:25.719 --> 01:51:28.289
<i>and my right hand</i>
<i>has gone numb.</i>

1705
01:51:28.322 --> 01:51:33.127
<i>I can still grip my sword.</i>
<i>but who knows for how long?</i>

1706
01:51:41.702 --> 01:51:43.204
Wait!

1707
01:51:43.237 --> 01:51:47.041
I-I'm here.

1708
01:51:47.074 --> 01:51:49.009
I'm still alive!

1709
01:51:49.043 --> 01:51:51.111
If you want to kill Tanjiro.

1710
01:51:51.145 --> 01:51:53.781
you'll have
to defeat me first!

1711
01:51:57.519 --> 01:51:59.954
<i>An indomitable spirit.</i>

1712
01:51:59.987 --> 01:52:01.255
<i>It will never bend.</i>

1713
01:52:01.288 --> 01:52:04.593
<i>no matter what crisis</i>
<i>it finds itself in.</i>

1714
01:52:04.626 --> 01:52:07.962
<i>We don't fight</i>
<i>the way samurai do.</i>

1715
01:52:07.995 --> 01:52:10.130
<i>We don't carry weapons.</i>

1716
01:52:10.164 --> 01:52:13.300
<i>Though we carry</i>
<i>our convictions like swords.</i>

1717
01:52:14.735 --> 01:52:18.806
- Though we carry
our convictions like swords.

1718
01:52:18.839 --> 01:52:23.410
our battles
are waged with our fists.

1719
01:52:24.411 --> 01:52:27.448
<i>- You are such an eyesore.</i>

1720
01:52:37.992 --> 01:52:39.460
Please stop.

1721
01:52:45.766 --> 01:52:47.301
<i>Who is that?</i>

1722
01:52:52.406 --> 01:52:54.643
- Mr. Hakuji...

1723
01:52:54.676 --> 01:52:56.377
please. that's enough.

1724
01:52:59.480 --> 01:53:01.448
<i>- Let go.</i>

1725
01:53:01.482 --> 01:53:03.585
<i>Let go of my hand.</i>

1726
01:53:03.618 --> 01:53:05.853
<i>Just who are you?</i>

1727
01:53:07.321 --> 01:53:09.823
- Stop.
You don't have to keep going.

1728
01:53:09.857 --> 01:53:12.926
Let's leave
this place together

1729
01:53:13.728 --> 01:53:15.329
<i>- I can't.</i>

1730
01:53:15.362 --> 01:53:19.066
<i>I've still got unfinished</i>
<i>business with those two.</i>

1731
01:53:20.434 --> 01:53:22.903
- What do you mean by that?

1732
01:53:22.936 --> 01:53:25.172
<i>- I've got</i>
<i>to become stronger.</i>

1733
01:53:25.205 --> 01:53:26.775
<i>I've got to.</i>

1734
01:53:26.807 --> 01:53:30.144
<i>I'll kill anyone</i>
<i>who gets in my way.</i>

1735
01:53:30.944 --> 01:53:32.514
- Why do you want that?

1736
01:53:33.748 --> 01:53:37.251
For what reason do you
need to become stronger?

1737
01:53:38.285 --> 01:53:39.688
<i>- Because...</i>

1738
01:53:39.721 --> 01:53:42.256
<i>unless I'm strong enough.</i>

1739
01:53:42.289 --> 01:53:45.560
<i>I won't be able to bring</i>
<i>any more back home to him.</i>

1740
01:53:47.729 --> 01:53:50.097
<i>He needs medicine.</i>

1741
01:53:52.399 --> 01:53:54.902
<i>I must become stronger.</i>

1742
01:53:57.004 --> 01:53:59.473
<i>If I don't.</i>
<i>I won't be able to get away</i>

1743
01:53:59.506 --> 01:54:00.709
<i>with the money I stole.</i>

1744
01:54:02.009 --> 01:54:03.877
<i>If I happen to be caught.</i>

1745
01:54:03.911 --> 01:54:06.715
<i>I won't be able</i>
<i>to defend myself.</i>

1746
01:54:06.748 --> 01:54:09.517
<i>If I'm not strong enough.</i>

1747
01:54:09.551 --> 01:54:10.951
<i>the magistrate</i>
<i>will catch me</i>

1748
01:54:10.984 --> 01:54:13.588
<i>and have me</i>
<i>beaten and lashed.</i>

1749
01:54:16.558 --> 01:54:17.826
- We've already given you

1750
01:54:17.858 --> 01:54:20.961
three tattoos on each arm
for stealing.

1751
01:54:20.994 --> 01:54:23.698
Next time.
we'll chop off your hand.

1752
01:54:31.573 --> 01:54:33.307
- Bow your head and repent!

1753
01:54:33.340 --> 01:54:35.643
- If you're gonna chop it off.
then do it!

1754
01:54:35.677 --> 01:54:38.847
Go ahead and take both of 'em
if you're really serious.

1755
01:54:38.879 --> 01:54:41.048
I'll just
use my feet to steal!

1756
01:54:41.081 --> 01:54:42.617
You're not gonna
catch me again.

1757
01:54:42.650 --> 01:54:44.586
so make it count!

1758
01:54:46.420 --> 01:54:49.957
- To hear this from someone
at such a young age.

1759
01:54:49.990 --> 01:54:52.660
This boy of 11 has
already taken on punishments

1760
01:54:52.694 --> 01:54:55.597
that would make
a grown man faint.

1761
01:54:56.598 --> 01:54:58.265
You are a demon child!

1762
01:54:58.298 --> 01:55:00.434
- Go and call me
whatever names you want!

1763
01:55:00.467 --> 01:55:03.003
"Demon child"
suits me just damn fine!

1764
01:55:03.036 --> 01:55:05.472
They say I already
had teeth when I was born.

1765
01:55:05.506 --> 01:55:06.641
so I guess I am!

1766
01:55:06.674 --> 01:55:07.609
- Be quiet!

1767
01:55:07.642 --> 01:55:08.843
- Dirty little punk!

1768
01:55:08.877 --> 01:55:12.112
- Don't you mean
"Demon Child." you bastard?!

1769
01:55:15.650 --> 01:55:17.017
Hmph.

1770
01:55:21.523 --> 01:55:22.824
- Hakuji!

1771
01:55:22.857 --> 01:55:24.925
Ah! There you are!

1772
01:55:24.958 --> 01:55:27.227
When you were caught
for stealing again.

1773
01:55:27.261 --> 01:55:31.131
word about it made
its way back to your father.

1774
01:55:31.165 --> 01:55:33.768
He hung himself. Hakuji!

1775
01:55:33.802 --> 01:55:35.169
- Huh?

1776
01:55:38.606 --> 01:55:41.810
<i>Dear Hakuji.</i>

1777
01:55:41.843 --> 01:55:44.144
<i>Live an honest life.</i>

1778
01:55:44.178 --> 01:55:46.581
<i>You can still start over.</i>

1779
01:55:53.954 --> 01:55:56.256
<i>What kind</i>
<i>of world is this?</i>

1780
01:55:56.290 --> 01:55:59.059
<i>Are the poor</i>
<i>not even allowed to live?</i>

1781
01:56:04.364 --> 01:56:05.432
<i>Dad.</i>

1782
01:56:07.702 --> 01:56:09.771
<i>To hell with</i>
<i>this rotten world.</i>

1783
01:56:09.804 --> 01:56:10.872
<i>to all of it!</i>

1784
01:56:14.241 --> 01:56:16.678
<i>Every rotten human.</i>

1785
01:56:16.711 --> 01:56:18.646
<i>they can all burn in hell!</i>

1786
01:56:22.517 --> 01:56:25.620
<i>Why do scumbags like them</i>
<i>get the privilege of living</i>

1787
01:56:25.653 --> 01:56:29.122
<i>when my father had to die</i>
<i>in such a horrible way?</i>

1788
01:56:29.156 --> 01:56:31.258
<i>He was never a burden to me.</i>

1789
01:56:31.291 --> 01:56:34.127
<i>so why would he</i>
<i>feel that way?</i>

1790
01:56:34.161 --> 01:56:36.463
<i>You didn't</i>
<i>do anything wrong. Dad!</i>

1791
01:56:36.497 --> 01:56:37.431
<i>You didn't!</i>

1792
01:56:39.868 --> 01:56:41.669
<i>I never cared</i>
<i>about getting beaten</i>

1793
01:56:41.703 --> 01:56:44.104
<i>after I was caught stealing.</i>

1794
01:56:44.137 --> 01:56:45.272
<i>Even if they beat me</i>

1795
01:56:45.305 --> 01:56:47.742
<i>until every bone</i>
<i>in my body was broken.</i>

1796
01:56:47.775 --> 01:56:51.478
<i>I could take it all for you.</i>
<i>Dad! For centuries. even!</i>

1797
01:56:51.513 --> 01:56:52.714
- Learn your lesson!

1798
01:56:52.747 --> 01:56:53.982
Live an honest life!

1799
01:56:55.282 --> 01:56:57.919
<i>Why don't you shut</i>
<i>the hell up. you scumbag?</i>

1800
01:56:57.952 --> 01:56:59.988
<i>Medicine's expensive.</i>

1801
01:57:00.020 --> 01:57:02.757
<i>The hell do you expect me</i>
<i>to do about that?</i>

1802
01:57:02.790 --> 01:57:08.161
<i>My Dad's only getting thinner</i>
<i>and thinner by the day.</i>

1803
01:57:08.195 --> 01:57:12.299
<i>He's so malnourished.</i>
<i>you can see his bones.</i>

1804
01:57:12.332 --> 01:57:15.770
<i>I just want him to have</i>
<i>something better to eat.</i>

1805
01:57:18.071 --> 01:57:20.708
<i>I would have</i>
<i>happily given my life...</i>

1806
01:57:22.644 --> 01:57:24.812
<i>if it meant saving his.</i>

1807
01:57:31.051 --> 01:57:32.954
<i>I'd have done anything...</i>

1808
01:57:32.987 --> 01:57:35.122
<i>for my father!</i>

1809
01:57:42.262 --> 01:57:42.997
Huh?

1810
01:57:43.031 --> 01:57:44.566
- Well. well.

1811
01:57:44.599 --> 01:57:46.333
I am quite impressed.

1812
01:57:46.366 --> 01:57:48.368
I was called over
because someone said

1813
01:57:48.402 --> 01:57:50.270
that a child
was about to be killed.

1814
01:57:50.304 --> 01:57:53.875
but you've laid out seven
grownups with your bare fists.

1815
01:57:53.908 --> 01:57:56.343
You've got some talent.
don't ya?

1816
01:57:56.376 --> 01:57:59.948
Not just anyone can take on
that many guys and still win.

1817
01:57:59.981 --> 01:58:02.650
That's the kind of spunk
I like to see.

1818
01:58:04.886 --> 01:58:07.055
<i>- What's going on here?</i>

1819
01:58:07.087 --> 01:58:09.389
<i>Who is this man?</i>

1820
01:58:09.423 --> 01:58:12.326
<i>Could these be my memories?</i>

1821
01:58:12.359 --> 01:58:14.428
- How 'bout you join my dojo?

1822
01:58:14.461 --> 01:58:17.130
I don't have any students
at the moment.

1823
01:58:17.164 --> 01:58:19.067
- Stay out of my way.
you old fart!

1824
01:58:19.099 --> 01:58:20.434
You lookin' to die?!

1825
01:58:20.467 --> 01:58:22.737
Those tattoos...

1826
01:58:22.770 --> 01:58:24.539
- you're a criminal from Edo.

1827
01:58:24.572 --> 01:58:26.874
I'm guessing.
after being thrown out.

1828
01:58:26.908 --> 01:58:29.376
you eventually
found your way here.

1829
01:58:29.409 --> 01:58:31.378
I never asked
for your opinion.

1830
01:58:31.411 --> 01:58:34.082
Now shut up and
get the hell out of my way!

1831
01:58:34.114 --> 01:58:35.182
- Hmph!

1832
01:58:35.215 --> 01:58:37.752
All right. Time to be reborn!

1833
01:58:38.753 --> 01:58:40.253
You ready?

1834
01:58:41.089 --> 01:58:42.056
- That's it.

1835
01:58:42.090 --> 01:58:44.592
Drop dead. old man!

1836
01:59:04.411 --> 01:59:07.314
- I'll give it to ya.
You're tough!

1837
01:59:07.347 --> 01:59:09.149
After that beating
I gave you.

1838
01:59:09.182 --> 01:59:11.318
you came to
in less than an hour.

1839
01:59:12.219 --> 01:59:14.122
The name's Keizo.

1840
01:59:14.154 --> 01:59:16.156
I teach the Soryu Style
of fighting.

1841
01:59:16.189 --> 01:59:18.626
which uses
only your bare hands.

1842
01:59:18.660 --> 01:59:22.329
Like I said. I don't have
any other students.

1843
01:59:22.362 --> 01:59:26.199
so I get by by doing whatever
odd jobs I can for people.

1844
01:59:28.670 --> 01:59:31.405
I have a daughter
who's in rather poor health.

1845
01:59:31.438 --> 01:59:34.241
I'd like you
to help look after her.

1846
01:59:34.274 --> 01:59:38.211
I'd be here if I could.
but I have to work.

1847
01:59:38.245 --> 01:59:41.082
My wife was pushed
to the edge of exhaustion

1848
01:59:41.115 --> 01:59:43.551
and drowned herself.

1849
01:59:43.584 --> 01:59:46.319
Life sure takes a bite
out of you. doesn't it?

1850
01:59:50.257 --> 01:59:52.292
- If I were
a more capable man.

1851
01:59:52.325 --> 01:59:55.195
my wife and daughter wouldn't
have suffered like this.

1852
01:59:58.231 --> 02:00:00.300
- You said
you knew I was a criminal.

1853
02:00:00.333 --> 02:00:01.468
Are you really all right

1854
02:00:01.501 --> 02:00:03.738
leaving your daughter
around me?

1855
02:00:04.772 --> 02:00:06.574
- Why wouldn't I be?

1856
02:00:06.607 --> 02:00:09.744
I pummeled the criminal
out of you earlier. didn't I?

1857
02:00:09.777 --> 02:00:11.045
It's fine.

1858
02:00:13.781 --> 02:00:15.850
<i>They</i> are <i>alike.</i>

1859
02:00:23.658 --> 02:00:25.392
<i>I get it now.</i>

1860
02:00:26.359 --> 02:00:29.496
<i>The reason</i>
<i>you disgusted me earlier.</i>

1861
02:00:29.530 --> 02:00:31.599
<i>it was because</i>
<i>you went and dredged up</i>

1862
02:00:31.632 --> 02:00:34.434
<i>memories of</i>
<i>my worthless past.</i>

1863
02:00:39.372 --> 02:00:41.943
- This is my daughter. Koyuki.

1864
02:00:44.879 --> 02:00:47.314
<i>- My worthless past.</i>

1865
02:00:50.283 --> 02:00:51.919
<i>Worthless.</i>

1866
02:01:01.028 --> 02:01:02.295
Hakuji...

1867
02:01:02.329 --> 02:01:05.233
I'm so sorry.

1868
02:01:05.298 --> 02:01:07.568
How are you feeling?

1869
02:01:09.436 --> 02:01:11.773
- You okay being up?

1870
02:01:11.806 --> 02:01:14.008
- Mm.

1871
02:01:14.041 --> 02:01:15.143
- Looks like you've got

1872
02:01:15.176 --> 02:01:17.245
more color in your cheeks
this morning.

1873
02:01:17.277 --> 02:01:19.279
That's good.

1874
02:01:21.549 --> 02:01:22.315
Huh?

1875
02:01:22.349 --> 02:01:24.786
- Oh. yeah! This boy.

1876
02:01:24.819 --> 02:01:26.254
His name is...

1877
02:01:26.286 --> 02:01:28.990
Well. I've
asked him countless times.

1878
02:01:29.023 --> 02:01:30.124
and he won't say.

1879
02:01:30.158 --> 02:01:32.226
Go on! Get inside.

1880
02:01:34.028 --> 02:01:35.730
- Have a seat.

1881
02:01:36.831 --> 02:01:39.934
- I'll wanna know his name
when I get back. okay?

1882
02:01:47.875 --> 02:01:48.943
Mm.

1883
02:01:50.178 --> 02:01:51.212
Hmm?

1884
02:01:51.245 --> 02:01:52.780
U-Um...

1885
02:01:52.814 --> 02:01:56.818
Your-- Your face.

1886
02:01:56.851 --> 02:01:58.485
You're hurt.

1887
02:01:58.519 --> 02:02:00.453
Are you all right?

1888
02:02:03.691 --> 02:02:05.693
<i>"I'll make you better."</i>

1889
02:02:05.726 --> 02:02:09.462
<i>"I'll save you.</i>
<i>protect you."</i>

1890
02:02:09.496 --> 02:02:14.535
<i>In that past life. all I did</i>
<i>was spew a bunch of lies.</i>

1891
02:02:14.569 --> 02:02:16.469
<i>I was so pathetic.</i>

1892
02:02:32.720 --> 02:02:34.689
Oh. thank you.

1893
02:02:35.923 --> 02:02:38.893
- You don't have to thank me
every time. you know.

1894
02:02:38.926 --> 02:02:40.728
Just focus on resting.

1895
02:02:42.296 --> 02:02:43.764
- I'm sorry...

1896
02:02:43.798 --> 02:02:46.234
for causing you trouble
like this.

1897
02:02:46.267 --> 02:02:48.501
- It's fine. really.

1898
02:02:50.137 --> 02:02:53.307
Koyuki. want this closed?

1899
02:02:55.176 --> 02:02:57.377
You can leave it open.

1900
02:02:59.146 --> 02:03:01.983
<i>Koyuki was</i>
<i>very delicate and frail.</i>

1901
02:03:03.351 --> 02:03:05.820
<i>I would change out</i>
<i>her towels and nightgown</i>

1902
02:03:05.853 --> 02:03:09.422
<i>and give her water.</i>
<i>even throughout the night.</i>

1903
02:03:09.456 --> 02:03:12.159
<i>And whenever she needed</i>
<i>to use the lavatory.</i>

1904
02:03:12.193 --> 02:03:13.661
<i>obviously she was too weak</i>

1905
02:03:13.694 --> 02:03:16.429
<i>to be able to go</i>
<i>without needing assistance.</i>

1906
02:03:20.101 --> 02:03:23.604
<i>I was used to taking care of</i>
<i>the sick because of my dad.</i>

1907
02:03:23.638 --> 02:03:27.275
<i>and since I had an almost</i>
<i>inhuman physical endurance.</i>

1908
02:03:27.308 --> 02:03:29.577
<i>it really wasn't</i>
<i>a big deal for me.</i>

1909
02:03:34.447 --> 02:03:36.984
Sorry to make you
help me all day.

1910
02:03:43.490 --> 02:03:46.394
<i>- Why do people who are</i>
<i>suffering from illness</i>

1911
02:03:46.426 --> 02:03:49.830
<i>always feel the need</i>
<i>to say they're sorry?</i>

1912
02:03:49.864 --> 02:03:52.333
<i>"Sorry to make you</i>
<i>do things for me."</i>

1913
02:03:52.366 --> 02:03:55.770
<i>"Sorry if my coughing's</i>
<i>bothering you."</i>

1914
02:03:55.803 --> 02:03:59.006
<i>"Sorry I can't put food</i>
<i>on the table like I should."</i>

1915
02:04:00.741 --> 02:04:03.978
<i>They didn't choose</i>
<i>to have to live this way.</i>

1916
02:04:04.011 --> 02:04:06.414
<i>'Course they</i>
<i>wanna breathe normally.</i>

1917
02:04:06.446 --> 02:04:09.817
<i>They can't help it</i>
<i>if they start coughing.</i>

1918
02:04:09.850 --> 02:04:13.854
<i>Out of everyone. they're</i>
<i>the ones suffering the most.</i>

1919
02:04:16.657 --> 02:04:19.492
- Sorry again
to make you do this.

1920
02:04:19.527 --> 02:04:21.562
Because of my sickness

1921
02:04:21.595 --> 02:04:24.198
you're not able
to do your training

1922
02:04:24.231 --> 02:04:26.701
or even go out and have fun.

1923
02:04:26.734 --> 02:04:29.270
- I don't care
about having fun.

1924
02:04:29.303 --> 02:04:31.405
I never have.

1925
02:04:31.439 --> 02:04:33.007
Far as training goes.

1926
02:04:33.040 --> 02:04:36.043
I squeeze it in
whenever I can. so it's fine.

1927
02:04:37.044 --> 02:04:38.879
- You sure?

1928
02:04:38.913 --> 02:04:42.917
Even you need to take
a little break.

1929
02:04:42.950 --> 02:04:46.520
I hear there are fireworks
happening tonight.

1930
02:04:46.554 --> 02:04:48.923
You should go see them.

1931
02:04:49.924 --> 02:04:51.692
- Fireworks. huh?

1932
02:04:51.726 --> 02:04:53.928
If you don't feel
nauseous at night.

1933
02:04:53.961 --> 02:04:57.732
I could carry you on my back
and go see them on the bridge.

1934
02:04:57.765 --> 02:04:58.866
- Huh?

1935
02:05:02.436 --> 02:05:04.205
- If you're
not feeling up to it.

1936
02:05:04.238 --> 02:05:07.475
they'll do fireworks again
next year and after that.

1937
02:05:07.508 --> 02:05:09.877
so we can just go
when you're better.

1938
02:05:18.652 --> 02:05:20.121
<i>- There was one thing</i>

1939
02:05:20.154 --> 02:05:22.356
<i>that was hard</i>
<i>about taking care of her.</i>

1940
02:05:22.390 --> 02:05:23.524
<i>and that was whenever</i>

1941
02:05:23.557 --> 02:05:25.493
<i>she would suddenly</i>
<i>break out into tears</i>

1942
02:05:25.526 --> 02:05:28.195
<i>in the middle</i>
<i>of our conversations.</i>

1943
02:05:28.229 --> 02:05:29.930
<i>I can imagine how she felt.</i>

1944
02:05:29.964 --> 02:05:32.600
<i>bedridden and sick</i>
<i>as she was...</i>

1945
02:05:32.633 --> 02:05:35.102
<i>but it still</i>
<i>made me uncomfortable.</i>

1946
02:05:50.217 --> 02:05:52.186
Ah. now I understand.

1947
02:05:52.219 --> 02:05:54.488
The symbol used for "Hakuji."

1948
02:05:54.523 --> 02:05:56.257
it's the same as "komainu."

1949
02:05:56.290 --> 02:05:58.092
Hmph. That makes sense.

1950
02:05:58.125 --> 02:06:00.628
You and I really are
the same after all.

1951
02:06:00.661 --> 02:06:03.664
We only thrive when we
have something to protect.

1952
02:06:03.697 --> 02:06:04.932
Just like the komainu

1953
02:06:04.965 --> 02:06:07.101
who protect the entrance
to the shrines.

1954
02:06:12.339 --> 02:06:15.709
<i>- There was a story as to how</i>
<i>my Master owned this land.</i>

1955
02:06:15.743 --> 02:06:17.378
<i>even though</i>
<i>he wasn't a samurai</i>

1956
02:06:17.411 --> 02:06:18.846
<i>or anything like that.</i>

1957
02:06:18.879 --> 02:06:22.850
<i>He had rescued an elderly man</i>
<i>from a group of bandits.</i>

1958
02:06:22.883 --> 02:06:25.119
<i>The old man.</i>
<i>who had no living heirs.</i>

1959
02:06:25.152 --> 02:06:27.688
<i>was so impressed</i>
<i>by his Soryu technique</i>

1960
02:06:27.721 --> 02:06:29.558
<i>that he left him</i>
<i>not only his land</i>

1961
02:06:29.590 --> 02:06:31.659
<i>but the dojo</i>
<i>that lay upon it.</i>

1962
02:06:34.595 --> 02:06:37.765
<i>However. there were</i>
<i>those with envious eyes</i>

1963
02:06:37.798 --> 02:06:41.469
<i>who wished to have the land</i>
<i>and dojo all to themselves.</i>

1964
02:06:41.502 --> 02:06:43.971
<i>The kenjutsu dojo next door</i>

1965
02:06:44.004 --> 02:06:46.807
<i>started harassing</i>
<i>the Soryu Dojo.</i>

1966
02:06:48.442 --> 02:06:50.678
<i>Because of that.</i>
<i>the Soryu Dojo</i>

1967
02:06:50.711 --> 02:06:53.080
<i>had a hard time</i>
<i>keeping any students.</i>

1968
02:07:00.488 --> 02:07:03.324
<i>But now.</i>
<i>thanks to my training here</i>

1969
02:07:03.357 --> 02:07:05.759
<i>and caring for Koyuki.</i>

1970
02:07:05.793 --> 02:07:09.864
<i>my heart has</i>
<i>finally found salvation.</i>

1971
02:07:28.883 --> 02:07:33.487
<i>Three short years went by.</i>
<i>and I turned 18.</i>

1972
02:07:33.522 --> 02:07:36.023
<i>Koyuki was 16.</i>

1973
02:07:36.056 --> 02:07:38.225
<i>She was almost</i>
<i>never bedridden anymore</i>

1974
02:07:38.259 --> 02:07:41.262
<i>and was now able</i>
<i>to live a normal life.</i>

1975
02:07:45.799 --> 02:07:47.801
- Hakuji! Come here.

1976
02:07:48.637 --> 02:07:50.104
- Yes. sir.

1977
02:07:51.405 --> 02:07:52.706
- This dojo...

1978
02:07:52.740 --> 02:07:56.243
would you be willing to
take it over for me. Hakuji?

1979
02:07:56.277 --> 02:08:01.015
Koyuki's told me that she's
quite fond of you as well.

1980
02:08:01.048 --> 02:08:02.183
- Huh?

1981
02:08:09.823 --> 02:08:12.561
<i>- As someone branded with</i>
<i>the tattoos of a criminal.</i>

1982
02:08:12.594 --> 02:08:16.830
<i>picturing any kind of future</i>
<i>for myself was hard enough.</i>

1983
02:08:16.864 --> 02:08:21.969
<i>But a future in which someone</i>
<i>could like a person like me?</i>

1984
02:08:22.002 --> 02:08:25.039
<i>I couldn't have</i>
<i>even dreamed it.</i>

1985
02:08:26.106 --> 02:08:28.742
<i>My dad asked me</i>
<i>to lead an honest life.</i>

1986
02:08:28.776 --> 02:08:31.011
<i>something I never</i>
<i>thought was possible.</i>

1987
02:08:31.045 --> 02:08:34.248
<i>But perhaps it really is.</i>

1988
02:08:34.281 --> 02:08:37.686
<i>The faint hope</i>
<i>of being able to start over</i>

1989
02:08:37.718 --> 02:08:39.887
<i>began to swell within me</i>

1990
02:08:39.920 --> 02:08:42.990
<i>until it felt like it</i>
<i>was about to burst.</i>

1991
02:08:49.196 --> 02:08:51.365
<i>But I could never have</i>
<i>predicted in that moment</i>

1992
02:08:51.398 --> 02:08:53.867
<i>that the two people</i>
<i>I wanted to protect</i>

1993
02:08:53.901 --> 02:08:57.238
<i>more than anything else</i>
<i>in this life...</i>

1994
02:08:57.271 --> 02:08:59.773
<i>would end up</i>
<i>meeting the fate they did.</i>

1995
02:09:04.912 --> 02:09:08.882
<i>I had made a trip to Edo</i>
<i>to visit my dad's grave.</i>

1996
02:09:08.916 --> 02:09:12.052
<i>I wanted to let him know</i>
<i>that I was getting married.</i>

1997
02:09:21.563 --> 02:09:25.799
<i>I returned before even a full</i>
<i>day and night had passed...</i>

1998
02:09:28.570 --> 02:09:31.438
<i>yet a sense of dread</i>
<i>came over me.</i>

1999
02:09:32.306 --> 02:09:35.075
<i>My chest started</i>
<i>to feel tight.</i>

2000
02:09:35.109 --> 02:09:38.045
<i>and a terrible feeling</i>
<i>of nausea overtook me.</i>

2001
02:09:40.615 --> 02:09:43.884
Someone put poison
in the well!

2002
02:09:43.917 --> 02:09:45.286
The other school was so angry

2003
02:09:45.319 --> 02:09:47.321
they couldn't beat you
or Mr. Keizo.

2004
02:09:47.354 --> 02:09:49.691
they went and did this
out of spite!

2005
02:09:49.724 --> 02:09:52.259
It's atrocious. unthinkable!

2006
02:09:52.293 --> 02:09:54.328
They even killed Koyuki!

2007
02:09:57.699 --> 02:09:59.900
<i>- Why? Why is it</i>

2008
02:09:59.933 --> 02:10:02.903
<i>whenever the ones I care</i>
<i>about are in mortal peril.</i>

2009
02:10:02.936 --> 02:10:05.205
<i>I'm never there for them?</i>

2010
02:10:14.014 --> 02:10:16.785
<i>I had even gone</i>
<i>and made a promise to her.</i>

2011
02:10:19.119 --> 02:10:21.922
Are you sure
that I'm the one for you?

2012
02:10:24.024 --> 02:10:25.993
- When we were children.

2013
02:10:26.026 --> 02:10:28.495
do you remember
when you talked to me

2014
02:10:28.530 --> 02:10:30.230
about seeing the fireworks?

2015
02:10:31.231 --> 02:10:32.066
- Huh?

2016
02:10:32.099 --> 02:10:35.436
Uh. no. not really.

2017
02:10:36.837 --> 02:10:39.206
- Because of those
little talks we used to have.

2018
02:10:39.239 --> 02:10:42.009
there were a lot of things
which I took with me

2019
02:10:42.042 --> 02:10:44.445
that gave me hope
for the future.

2020
02:10:44.478 --> 02:10:49.049
You said even if we couldn't
see the fireworks that year.

2021
02:10:49.083 --> 02:10:52.353
we could go to the one
happening next year

2022
02:10:52.386 --> 02:10:54.855
or the year after that.

2023
02:10:54.888 --> 02:10:57.991
The truth is. I could
never imagine a future

2024
02:10:58.025 --> 02:11:00.361
where I'd still
be alive a year later

2025
02:11:00.394 --> 02:11:03.330
and certainly
not any longer than that.

2026
02:11:04.599 --> 02:11:06.601
My mother couldn't. either.

2027
02:11:06.634 --> 02:11:09.903
I think that's why she
ended up taking her own life.

2028
02:11:09.937 --> 02:11:12.973
'cause she didn't
want to see me die.

2029
02:11:13.006 --> 02:11:14.542
Not just her.

2030
02:11:14.576 --> 02:11:17.712
I could tell my father
had given up hope. too.

2031
02:11:17.746 --> 02:11:19.413
deep down inside.

2032
02:11:20.582 --> 02:11:22.916
Because I was just so weak.

2033
02:11:24.118 --> 02:11:26.887
But you never
treated me that way.

2034
02:11:26.920 --> 02:11:29.423
You were able to see
a future for me.

2035
02:11:29.456 --> 02:11:32.926
You'd talk to me
about doing things.

2036
02:11:32.960 --> 02:11:37.097
as if-- as if it were obvious
that I'd still be here.

2037
02:11:37.131 --> 02:11:40.234
That made me so very happy.

2038
02:11:51.445 --> 02:11:54.549
So. yes. I am sure
you're the one for me.

2039
02:11:56.551 --> 02:11:57.951
Would you...

2040
02:11:58.753 --> 02:12:00.988
Would you be my husband?

2041
02:12:09.229 --> 02:12:10.497
- Yes.

2042
02:12:10.532 --> 02:12:13.868
I promise to become
stronger than anyone

2043
02:12:13.902 --> 02:12:16.370
and protect you
for the rest of my life.

2044
02:12:21.008 --> 02:12:22.677
<i>- In the end....</i>

2045
02:12:22.710 --> 02:12:24.579
<i>I was all talk.</i>

2046
02:12:24.612 --> 02:12:28.315
<i>I wasn't able to fulfill</i>
<i>any of my promises.</i>

2047
02:12:40.628 --> 02:12:42.162
- What do you want?

2048
02:12:42.996 --> 02:12:45.399
You've got some nerve!

2049
02:12:45.432 --> 02:12:46.634
- Wait.

2050
02:12:46.668 --> 02:12:48.937
You're from the Soryu Sty--

2051
02:13:10.725 --> 02:13:14.328
- The family of the Soryu Dojo
were recently poisoned.

2052
02:13:14.361 --> 02:13:16.396
and we believe
that a student of theirs

2053
02:13:16.430 --> 02:13:19.534
retaliated against
the kenjutsu dojo.

2054
02:13:19.567 --> 02:13:22.402
Sixty-seven people
were murdered inside!

2055
02:13:22.436 --> 02:13:25.105
He shattered their skulls
and crushed their organs.

2056
02:13:25.138 --> 02:13:26.440
all barehanded.

2057
02:13:26.473 --> 02:13:28.576
Not only were
most of the bodies

2058
02:13:28.610 --> 02:13:31.178
mangled and mutilated
beyond recognition.

2059
02:13:31.211 --> 02:13:34.749
most had limbs missing
that we couldn't even locate.

2060
02:13:34.782 --> 02:13:36.851
Organs. limbs. brain matter.

2061
02:13:36.885 --> 02:13:38.586
even jaws and eyeballs
were found

2062
02:13:38.620 --> 02:13:42.857
strewn across the walls and
the ceiling of the premises.

2063
02:13:42.891 --> 02:13:46.561
This killer
was no ordinary human!

2064
02:14:09.216 --> 02:14:11.084
- I heard there was
some commotion

2065
02:14:11.118 --> 02:14:13.186
about a demon sighting here.

2066
02:14:13.220 --> 02:14:16.290
even though I know
I never sent one.

2067
02:14:16.323 --> 02:14:19.159
So I decided
to come see for myself.

2068
02:14:19.192 --> 02:14:21.829
Yet all I find is a human.

2069
02:14:21.863 --> 02:14:24.298
How utterly disappointing.

2070
02:14:25.399 --> 02:14:27.035
- Move...

2071
02:14:27.100 --> 02:14:28.468
or I'll kill--

2072
02:14:33.273 --> 02:14:34.509
- It just so happens.

2073
02:14:34.542 --> 02:14:38.913
I was contemplating
creating 12 powerful demons.

2074
02:14:38.947 --> 02:14:41.081
I wonder if you'll be
able to withstand

2075
02:14:41.114 --> 02:14:43.751
the amount of blood
I'm about to give you.

2076
02:14:45.753 --> 02:14:47.087
- You...

2077
02:14:49.456 --> 02:14:50.925
do...

2078
02:14:50.959 --> 02:14:52.860
whatever you want.

2079
02:14:53.861 --> 02:14:56.598
None of it... matters.

2080
02:15:11.244 --> 02:15:13.648
<i>After becoming a demon.</i>
<i>I lost my memories</i>

2081
02:15:13.681 --> 02:15:18.052
<i>and once again</i>
<i>started to seek out power.</i>

2082
02:15:33.067 --> 02:15:34.167
It's not enough!

2083
02:15:34.201 --> 02:15:36.738
It will never be enough!

2084
02:15:40.474 --> 02:15:43.811
<i>Even though I had</i>
<i>nothing left to my name.</i>

2085
02:15:43.845 --> 02:15:47.347
<i>even though I had nothing</i>
<i>worth fighting for anymore...</i>

2086
02:15:49.550 --> 02:15:52.620
<i>even though my family</i>
<i>was no longer around.</i>

2087
02:15:52.654 --> 02:15:56.591
<i>and I had no desire to live</i>
<i>in a world without them...</i>

2088
02:15:59.259 --> 02:16:00.427
<i>for over a century.</i>

2089
02:16:00.460 --> 02:16:02.229
<i>I committed</i>
<i>senseless massacres</i>

2090
02:16:02.262 --> 02:16:04.297
<i>over and over again.</i>

2091
02:16:05.365 --> 02:16:08.736
<i>Thinking about it now.</i>
<i>it's pathetic.</i>

2092
02:16:08.770 --> 02:16:10.270
<i>it's absurd.</i>

2093
02:16:11.204 --> 02:16:13.775
<i>All those deaths</i>
<i>were meaningless.</i>

2094
02:16:19.147 --> 02:16:20.982
<i>Even if I died now.</i>

2095
02:16:21.015 --> 02:16:24.852
<i>I couldn't go where the other</i>
<i>three were waiting for me.</i>

2096
02:16:26.219 --> 02:16:29.057
<i>Damn you for dredging up</i>
<i>these memories.</i>

2097
02:16:29.090 --> 02:16:30.925
<i>You bastard!</i>

2098
02:16:33.027 --> 02:16:34.696
<i>Pathetic humans.</i>

2099
02:16:34.729 --> 02:16:38.231
<i>Clinging on to life</i>
<i>with their fragile bodies.</i>

2100
02:16:39.133 --> 02:16:43.171
<i>Even their strongest</i>
<i>eventually die</i>

2101
02:16:43.203 --> 02:16:45.505
<i>and vanish into thin air.</i>

2102
02:16:48.910 --> 02:16:50.778
<i>He's still not dead?!</i>

2103
02:16:50.812 --> 02:16:53.114
<i>You can't be serious.</i>

2104
02:16:53.147 --> 02:16:56.784
<i>I have to kill him</i>
<i>before it's too late.</i>

2105
02:16:56.818 --> 02:16:59.352
<i>If we let him regenerate.</i>

2106
02:16:59.386 --> 02:17:01.522
<i>there'll be no stopping him!</i>

2107
02:17:07.494 --> 02:17:08.830
I must have passed out.

2108
02:17:08.863 --> 02:17:10.430
What's going on?

2109
02:17:12.066 --> 02:17:13.433
His head's back!

2110
02:17:13.467 --> 02:17:15.970
But how is that
even possible?!

2111
02:17:17.138 --> 02:17:19.974
I decapitated him!

2112
02:17:25.378 --> 02:17:28.281
- Destructive Death:
Annihilation Type.

2113
02:17:29.083 --> 02:17:31.018
- Stop it!

2114
02:17:31.052 --> 02:17:33.788
<i>- Seriously?</i>
<i>He can still move?</i>

2115
02:17:33.821 --> 02:17:36.624
<i>- Mr. Giyu and I</i>
<i>are going to win!</i>

2116
02:17:36.657 --> 02:17:40.661
<i>Akaza. I'll behead you</i>
<i>as many times as it takes!</i>

2117
02:17:43.396 --> 02:17:44.899
<i>My sword...</i>

2118
02:17:46.299 --> 02:17:48.736
<i>- It slipped</i>
<i>out of his hands.</i>

2119
02:17:49.804 --> 02:17:51.471
<i>- I lost my grip.</i>

2120
02:18:00.280 --> 02:18:02.216
<i>- All right. young man.</i>

2121
02:18:02.250 --> 02:18:04.886
<i>time to be reborn.</i>

2122
02:18:06.254 --> 02:18:09.724
<i>- I despise those</i>
<i>who are weak.</i>

2123
02:18:11.759 --> 02:18:16.130
<i>Weaklings. instead of</i>
<i>fighting you fair and square.</i>

2124
02:18:16.164 --> 02:18:19.432
<i>they always resort</i>
<i>to cheap tricks.</i>

2125
02:18:19.466 --> 02:18:21.536
<i>They're atrocious.</i>

2126
02:18:21.569 --> 02:18:23.671
<i>They have no patience.</i>

2127
02:18:23.704 --> 02:18:25.907
<i>and they quickly</i>
<i>grow desperate.</i>

2128
02:18:25.940 --> 02:18:28.709
<i>Just thinking about them</i>
<i>makes me sick.</i>

2129
02:18:30.745 --> 02:18:34.148
<i>I killed people with</i>
<i>my "fists of protection."</i>

2130
02:18:34.182 --> 02:18:39.352
<i>I desecrated my master's</i>
<i>beloved Soryu with blood.</i>

2131
02:18:39.386 --> 02:18:43.024
<i>and I couldn't follow</i>
<i>my father's last wishes.</i>

2132
02:18:45.693 --> 02:18:47.295
<i>That's right.</i>

2133
02:18:47.327 --> 02:18:50.031
<i>The one I wanted to kill...</i>

2134
02:18:55.603 --> 02:18:56.838
<i>- This couldn't be worse!</i>

2135
02:18:56.871 --> 02:18:58.105
<i>I dropped my sword!</i>

2136
02:19:00.241 --> 02:19:02.342
<i>My fists</i>
<i>aren't enough to stop him!</i>

2137
02:19:12.987 --> 02:19:14.121
<i>He's about to unleash</i>

2138
02:19:14.155 --> 02:19:17.490
<i>the Annihilation Type move</i>
<i>he used on Mr. Rengoku!</i>

2139
02:19:20.460 --> 02:19:22.330
<i>I've got to take</i>
<i>Mr. Giyu with me</i>

2140
02:19:22.362 --> 02:19:23.831
<i>out of the attack range!</i>

2141
02:19:28.035 --> 02:19:30.671
Leave me!
Save yourself!

2142
02:19:36.210 --> 02:19:38.145
<i>I've got to kill...</i>

2143
02:19:40.548 --> 02:19:42.116
<i>that weakling...</i>

2144
02:19:43.117 --> 02:19:44.986
<i>I've come to hate!</i>

2145
02:20:27.595 --> 02:20:30.430
<i>He just attacked himself.</i>

2146
02:20:32.499 --> 02:20:35.435
<i>Why would he</i>
<i>turn on himself like that?</i>

2147
02:20:36.270 --> 02:20:37.638
<i>Why?</i>

2148
02:20:41.042 --> 02:20:42.143
<i>For a second.</i>

2149
02:20:42.176 --> 02:20:45.513
<i>I could pick up the scent</i>
<i>of gratitude from him.</i>

2150
02:20:46.781 --> 02:20:48.916
<i>Why did he smile at me?</i>

2151
02:20:52.653 --> 02:20:54.188
<i>That's enough.</i>

2152
02:20:54.221 --> 02:20:55.455
<i>Stop it!</i>

2153
02:20:55.488 --> 02:20:57.625
<i>I don't want to regenerate!</i>

2154
02:20:57.658 --> 02:21:00.227
<i>Don't you get it?</i>

2155
02:21:00.261 --> 02:21:02.029
<i>The battle is over!</i>

2156
02:21:03.864 --> 02:21:07.500
<i>In that decisive moment.</i>
<i>I lost.</i>

2157
02:21:07.535 --> 02:21:09.570
<i>That technique</i>
<i>he beheaded me with</i>

2158
02:21:09.603 --> 02:21:12.740
<i>was nothing short</i>
<i>of perfection.</i>

2159
02:21:12.773 --> 02:21:15.242
<i>He anticipated my movements</i>

2160
02:21:15.276 --> 02:21:17.311
<i>and pivoted</i>
<i>at the last second.</i>

2161
02:21:17.345 --> 02:21:21.048
<i>then struck me down before</i>
<i>I could unleash my attack.</i>

2162
02:21:22.216 --> 02:21:24.585
<i>It's over now.</i>

2163
02:21:24.618 --> 02:21:29.090
<i>Let me accept my fate</i>
<i>and go to hell.</i>

2164
02:21:32.360 --> 02:21:34.195
<i>- Where is he trying to go?</i>

2165
02:21:40.534 --> 02:21:43.571
<i>Huh? He stopped</i>
<i>in his tracks.</i>

2166
02:21:46.374 --> 02:21:47.842
- Dad...

2167
02:21:49.443 --> 02:21:52.013
...are you feeling better now?

2168
02:21:52.046 --> 02:21:54.615
Are you in pain anymore?

2169
02:21:54.648 --> 02:21:58.686
- No need to worry. son.
I'm fine.

2170
02:21:58.719 --> 02:22:00.554
Thank you. Hakuji.

2171
02:22:07.328 --> 02:22:09.296
- I'm sorry. Father.

2172
02:22:09.330 --> 02:22:10.531
I'm sorry.

2173
02:22:10.564 --> 02:22:13.100
I couldn't start over
like you wanted.

2174
02:22:13.134 --> 02:22:15.536
I failed you.

2175
02:22:17.571 --> 02:22:19.507
- Do not despair.

2176
02:22:19.540 --> 02:22:22.543
Regardless of who
you grow to up be.

2177
02:22:22.576 --> 02:22:26.147
you're still my son
and still my student.

2178
02:22:26.180 --> 02:22:28.816
Heaven may not accept you.

2179
02:22:29.683 --> 02:22:31.419
But you needn't worry.

2180
02:22:31.452 --> 02:22:33.320
Our hearts will be with you.

2181
02:22:34.755 --> 02:22:37.691
- Master.

2182
02:22:39.360 --> 02:22:40.928
- Didn't you say

2183
02:22:40.961 --> 02:22:43.697
you were seeking to become
stronger than anyone?

2184
02:22:43.731 --> 02:22:48.769
Don't tell me you intend to
let it end like this. Akaza.

2185
02:22:49.970 --> 02:22:53.841
<i>- That's right.</i>
<i>I can't die here.</i>

2186
02:22:53.874 --> 02:22:56.610
<i>I have to get stronger!</i>

2187
02:22:56.644 --> 02:22:59.113
<i>So what if I got beheaded?</i>

2188
02:22:59.146 --> 02:23:02.716
<i>Who cares if I win</i>
<i>or lose the fight?</i>

2189
02:23:02.750 --> 02:23:05.119
<i>If I kill those</i>
<i>who stand in my way.</i>

2190
02:23:05.152 --> 02:23:09.323
<i>then there's still hope</i>
<i>for me to get stronger!</i>

2191
02:23:11.292 --> 02:23:14.795
<i>I made a promise.</i>
<i>I'm not about to break it!</i>

2192
02:23:25.473 --> 02:23:27.007
Mr. Hakuji...

2193
02:23:27.808 --> 02:23:30.244
thank you so much.

2194
02:23:30.277 --> 02:23:32.179
You've done more than enough.

2195
02:23:36.350 --> 02:23:38.252
It's okay.

2196
02:23:38.285 --> 02:23:40.187
We're all right now.

2197
02:23:40.221 --> 02:23:41.689
- Akaza!

2198
02:23:51.899 --> 02:23:53.400
- Sorry!

2199
02:23:53.434 --> 02:23:56.637
I'm sorry
I couldn't protect you!

2200
02:23:56.670 --> 02:23:59.740
I wasn't there
when you needed me to be!

2201
02:23:59.773 --> 02:24:03.310
I couldn't keep
a single promise I made!

2202
02:24:03.344 --> 02:24:07.448
I'm sorry. Please try
to forgive me. Koyuki!

2203
02:24:07.481 --> 02:24:09.416
I'm so sorry!

2204
02:24:13.721 --> 02:24:16.090
I'm so happy
you remembered us.

2205
02:24:16.123 --> 02:24:19.727
I can't tell you
how happy that makes me.

2206
02:24:19.760 --> 02:24:23.030
And to see you now
as the man that I once knew.

2207
02:24:23.063 --> 02:24:24.633
I'm so grateful.

2208
02:24:32.907 --> 02:24:36.110
- Welcome home. Hakuji.

2209
02:24:40.481 --> 02:24:42.283
Hey. Hakuji...

2210
02:24:42.316 --> 02:24:44.485
welcome home.

2211
02:24:52.661 --> 02:24:54.795
<i>- I'm back now.</i>

2212
02:24:54.828 --> 02:24:57.097
<i>I'm finally back home.</i>

2213
02:25:00.134 --> 02:25:04.639
- Welcome back home.
my darling.

2214
02:25:34.101 --> 02:25:35.736
He vanished.

2215
02:25:46.280 --> 02:25:48.182
It's over...

2216
02:25:48.215 --> 02:25:49.684
right?

2217
02:25:53.320 --> 02:25:54.589
Gotta hurry..

2218
02:25:54.623 --> 02:25:56.890
and get to...

2219
02:25:56.924 --> 02:25:59.193
where Ms. Tamayo is.

2220
02:26:00.194 --> 02:26:01.295
And then...

2221
02:26:08.335 --> 02:26:10.371
- Tanjiro...

2222
02:26:22.950 --> 02:26:28.155
Tanjiro. Giyu
have defeated Upper Three!

2223
02:26:28.188 --> 02:26:32.326
They're unable to stay
conscious due to exhaustion!

2224
02:26:32.359 --> 02:26:33.762
They've passed out!

2225
02:26:39.500 --> 02:26:42.671
Tanjiro. Giyu...

2226
02:26:42.704 --> 02:26:45.406
have defeated Upper Three!

2227
02:26:45.439 --> 02:26:47.207
Upper Three!

2228
02:26:53.213 --> 02:26:55.382
- Akaza...

2229
02:26:55.416 --> 02:26:58.118
his presence has vanished.

2230
02:26:59.820 --> 02:27:02.557
What a baffling conclusion.

2231
02:27:05.660 --> 02:27:07.294
Akaza...

2232
02:27:08.495 --> 02:27:12.534
what happened to your
burning ambition to defeat me?

2233
02:27:14.401 --> 02:27:18.972
To think you'd abandoned
everything you stood for...

2234
02:27:20.040 --> 02:27:23.944
and turned your back
on the path to greatness.

2235
02:27:30.652 --> 02:27:33.621
Your weakness appalls me.

2236
02:27:38.760 --> 02:27:39.960
- Huh?

2237
02:27:42.463 --> 02:27:44.098
This feeling...

2238
02:27:44.131 --> 02:27:46.867
Could Lord Akaza be dead?

2239
02:27:48.035 --> 02:27:49.336
Very strange.

2240
02:27:49.370 --> 02:27:53.474
Surely my imagination
must be running wild. right?

2241
02:27:53.507 --> 02:27:58.345
It almost felt like Lord Akaza
had turned into some creature.

2242
02:28:00.615 --> 02:28:03.685
But now that he's dead.
I guess it doesn't matter!

2243
02:28:06.954 --> 02:28:10.792
Let's see. Where was I?

2244
02:28:10.825 --> 02:28:12.794
Oh. I remember!

2245
02:28:12.827 --> 02:28:16.196
I'd just asked
for your name. hadn't I?

2246
02:28:29.009 --> 02:28:33.447
- Tanjiro. Giyu
have defeated Upper Three!

2247
02:28:33.480 --> 02:28:35.449
Upper Three!

2248
02:28:35.482 --> 02:28:37.251
- Did you hear that?

2249
02:28:37.284 --> 02:28:41.523
- Yes.
Excellent work. Tomioka.

2250
02:28:41.556 --> 02:28:42.923
Excellent work. Kamado.

2251
02:28:47.995 --> 02:28:52.065
- Mr. Tomioka and Tanjiro.
they did it!

2252
02:28:52.099 --> 02:28:55.369
- Now its our turn
to follow their lead.

2253
02:28:55.402 --> 02:28:56.671
- Right!

2254
02:29:11.285 --> 02:29:13.521
Hang in there.
Agatsuma!

2255
02:29:19.126 --> 02:29:20.829
- Start flapping
those wings faster.

2256
02:29:20.862 --> 02:29:22.564
or I'm gonna
keep poking!

2257
02:29:22.597 --> 02:29:24.298
You're gonna
use those wings

2258
02:29:24.331 --> 02:29:26.500
to show me where
the strongest demon is!

2259
02:29:26.534 --> 02:29:28.202
You hear me?!

2260
02:29:28.235 --> 02:29:30.939
I'm comin' through!

2261
02:29:30.971 --> 02:29:32.372
Hyah!

2262
02:29:32.406 --> 02:29:33.507
Now we're talkin'!

2263
02:29:33.541 --> 02:29:36.578
I'm sensing a powerful
demon over here!

2264
02:29:43.150 --> 02:29:45.352
- Where is
Big Brother?

2265
02:29:55.229 --> 02:29:57.532
- Where are all
the Upper Ranks?!

2266
02:29:57.565 --> 02:29:58.566
Tell me!

2267
02:29:58.600 --> 02:29:59.968
Come on!

2268
02:30:00.000 --> 02:30:02.804
I'm gonna
bury you all!

2269
02:30:10.545 --> 02:30:12.412
The passageway
leading north

2270
02:30:12.446 --> 02:30:14.549
on the 88th level
is clear.

2271
02:30:14.582 --> 02:30:16.985
No sign of Muzan.

2272
02:30:17.017 --> 02:30:18.686
The 127th levels

2273
02:30:18.720 --> 02:30:19.988
in the southeast
are clear.

2274
02:30:20.020 --> 02:30:22.256
No sign of Muzan.

2275
02:30:22.289 --> 02:30:25.527
- He's in here.
He has to be.

2276
02:30:25.560 --> 02:30:27.361
But where is he?

2277
02:30:27.394 --> 02:30:28.897
There's
no sign of Muzan

2278
02:30:28.930 --> 02:30:29.898
on any
of the levels

2279
02:30:29.931 --> 02:30:32.099
from 90 to 100.
either.

2280
02:30:34.167 --> 02:30:37.104
- Covering the entire
100th and 33rd levels.

2281
02:30:37.137 --> 02:30:38.673
No sign of Muzan.

2282
02:30:40.107 --> 02:30:42.376
- Our crows
will find you.

2283
02:30:42.409 --> 02:30:45.078
You can only hide
from us for so long.

2284
02:30:45.112 --> 02:30:48.983
We'll search every inch
of this infinity castle.

2285
02:30:49.017 --> 02:30:50.852
Even if you try
to run from us.

2286
02:30:50.885 --> 02:30:53.588
we will
hunt you down.

2287
02:31:07.769 --> 02:31:11.138
- Multilayered structures
are headed northeast.

2288
02:31:11.171 --> 02:31:13.041
- Attention. the
castle's expanding

2289
02:31:13.073 --> 02:31:14.909
in every direction!

2290
02:31:14.943 --> 02:31:16.711
Folding over
themselves...

2291
02:31:20.782 --> 02:31:22.517
And becoming one.

2292
02:31:29.122 --> 02:31:31.926
You can't
be serious.

2293
02:31:31.960 --> 02:31:33.493
No...

2294
02:31:33.528 --> 02:31:34.729
it's fine.

2295
02:31:34.762 --> 02:31:36.531
We've come
too far to lose!

2296
02:31:37.331 --> 02:31:39.499
Crows.
push forward...

2297
02:31:39.534 --> 02:31:41.134
and find Muzan!

2298
02:31:46.340 --> 02:31:49.343
Try all you
want. Demon Slayers.

2299
02:31:49.376 --> 02:31:51.311
but each one of you
will meet your end

2300
02:31:51.345 --> 02:31:53.848
before ever
reaching me.

2301
02:31:53.881 --> 02:31:55.215
You may be
feeling smug

2302
02:31:55.248 --> 02:31:57.250
after beheading one
of my Upper Ranks.

2303
02:31:57.284 --> 02:31:59.119
but unless
you can kill me.

2304
02:31:59.152 --> 02:32:01.421
your triumph
is meaningless!

2305
02:32:05.459 --> 02:32:08.228
You're all going to die
the most pointless deaths.

2306
02:32:08.261 --> 02:32:11.331
all the while
never seeing my face.

2307
02:32:11.365 --> 02:32:13.200
I can't think
of a more fitting end

2308
02:32:13.233 --> 02:32:16.104
for the Demon Slayer Corps.

2309
02:32:16.136 --> 02:32:18.338
Mark my words.
When I'm done here.

2310
02:32:18.372 --> 02:32:21.341
I'm going to make you regret
the day you were born!

2311
02:32:22.543 --> 02:32:23.578
Just wait.

2312
02:32:23.611 --> 02:32:26.614
You're each going to squirm
and writhe in pain.

2313
02:32:26.648 --> 02:32:28.716
Draw your final breaths.

2314
02:32:28.750 --> 02:32:32.120
because for every one
of you Demon Slayers.

2315
02:32:32.152 --> 02:32:35.489
there is no tomorrow!

2316
02:32:45.800 --> 02:32:47.200
- Please. Giyu...

2317
02:32:50.838 --> 02:32:52.607
don't die.

2318
02:32:59.047 --> 02:33:03.985
We can't have you
dying on us. Tanjiro.
